57 class AMDGPUOperand : public MCParsedAsmOperand {
58  enum KindTy {
59  Token,
60  Immediate,
61  Register,
62  Expression
63  } Kind;
64 
65  SMLoc StartLoc, EndLoc;
66  const AMDGPUAsmParser *AsmParser;
67 
68 public:
69  AMDGPUOperand(KindTy Kind_, const AMDGPUAsmParser *AsmParser_)
70  : Kind(Kind_), AsmParser(AsmParser_) {}
71 
72  using Ptr = std::unique_ptr<AMDGPUOperand>;
73 
74  struct Modifiers {
75  bool Abs = false;
76  bool Neg = false;
77  bool Sext = false;
78 
79  bool hasFPModifiers() const { return Abs || Neg; }
80  bool hasIntModifiers() const { return Sext; }
81  bool hasModifiers() const { return hasFPModifiers() || hasIntModifiers(); }
82 
83  int64_t getFPModifiersOperand() const {
84  int64_t Operand = 0;
85  Operand |= Abs ? SISrcMods::ABS : 0u;
86  Operand |= Neg ? SISrcMods::NEG : 0u;
87  return Operand;
88  }
89 
90  int64_t getIntModifiersOperand() const {
91  int64_t Operand = 0;
92  Operand |= Sext ? SISrcMods::SEXT : 0u;
93  return Operand;
94  }
95 
96  int64_t getModifiersOperand() const {
97  assert(!(hasFPModifiers() && hasIntModifiers())
98  && "fp and int modifiers should not be used simultaneously");
99  if (hasFPModifiers()) {
100  return getFPModifiersOperand();
101  } else if (hasIntModifiers()) {
102  return getIntModifiersOperand();
103  } else {
104  return 0;
105  }
106  }
107 
108  friend raw_ostream &operator <<(raw_ostream &OS, AMDGPUOperand::Modifiers Mods);
109  };

170  // Immediate operand kind.
171  // It helps to identify the location of an offending operand after an error.
172  // Note that regular literals and mandatory literals (KImm) must be handled
173  // differently. When looking for an offending operand, we should usually
174  // ignore mandatory literals because they are part of the instruction and
175  // cannot be changed. Report location of mandatory operands only for VOPD,
176  // when both OpX and OpY have a KImm and there are no other literals.
177  enum ImmKindTy {
178  ImmKindTyNone,
179  ImmKindTyLiteral,
180  ImmKindTyMandatoryLiteral,
181  ImmKindTyConst,
182  };
183 
184 private:
185  struct TokOp {
186  const char *Data;
187  unsigned Length;
188  };
189 
190  struct ImmOp {
191  int64_t Val;
192  ImmTy Type;
193  bool IsFPImm;
194  mutable ImmKindTy Kind;
195  Modifiers Mods;
196  };
197 
198  struct RegOp {
199  unsigned RegNo;
200  Modifiers Mods;
201  };
202 
203  union {
204  TokOp Tok;
205  ImmOp Imm;
206  RegOp Reg;
207  const MCExpr *Expr;
208  };
209 
210 public:
211  bool isToken() const override { return Kind == Token; }
212 
213  bool isSymbolRefExpr() const {
214  return isExpr() && Expr && isa<MCSymbolRefExpr>(Expr);
215  }
216 
217  bool isImm() const override {
218  return Kind == Immediate;
219  }
220 
221  void setImmKindNone() const {
222  assert(isImm());
223  Imm.Kind = ImmKindTyNone;
224  }
225 
226  void setImmKindLiteral() const {
227  assert(isImm());
228  Imm.Kind = ImmKindTyLiteral;
229  }
230 
231  void setImmKindMandatoryLiteral() const {
232  assert(isImm());
233  Imm.Kind = ImmKindTyMandatoryLiteral;
234  }
235 
236  void setImmKindConst() const {
237  assert(isImm());
238  Imm.Kind = ImmKindTyConst;
239  }
240 
241  bool IsImmKindLiteral() const {
242  return isImm() && Imm.Kind == ImmKindTyLiteral;
243  }
244 
245  bool IsImmKindMandatoryLiteral() const {
246  return isImm() && Imm.Kind == ImmKindTyMandatoryLiteral;
247  }
248 
249  bool isImmKindConst() const {
250  return isImm() && Imm.Kind == ImmKindTyConst;
251  }
252 
253  bool isInlinableImm(MVT type) const;
254  bool isLiteralImm(MVT type) const;
255 
256  bool isRegKind() const {
257  return Kind == Register;
258  }
259 
260  bool isReg() const override {
261  return isRegKind() && !hasModifiers();
262  }

264  bool isRegOrInline(unsigned RCID, MVT type) const {
265  return isRegClass(RCID) || isInlinableImm(type);
266  }

269  return isRegOrInline(RCID, type) || isLiteralImm(type);

970  void addRegOrImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
971  if (isRegKind())
972  addRegOperands(Inst, N);
973  else if (isExpr())
974  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(Expr));
975  else
976  addImmOperands(Inst, N);
977  }

979  void addRegOrImmWithInputModsOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
980  Modifiers Mods = getModifiers();
981  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Mods.getModifiersOperand()));
982  if (isRegKind()) {
983  addRegOperands(Inst, N);
984  } else {
985  addImmOperands(Inst, N, false);
986  }
987  }

991  addRegOrImmWithInputModsOperands(Inst, N);
992  }

1000  Modifiers Mods = getModifiers();
1001  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Mods.getModifiersOperand()));
1002  assert(isRegKind());
1003  addRegOperands(Inst, N);
1004  }
1005 
1006  void addRegWithFPInputModsOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1007  assert(!hasIntModifiers());
1008  addRegWithInputModsOperands(Inst, N);
1009  }
1010 
1011  void addRegWithIntInputModsOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1012  assert(!hasFPModifiers());
1013  addRegWithInputModsOperands(Inst, N);
1014  }

1016  void addSoppBrTargetOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
1017  if (isImm())
1018  addImmOperands(Inst, N);
1019  else {
1020  assert(isExpr());
1021  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createExpr(Expr));
1022  }
1023  }

1085 
1086  void print(raw_ostream &OS) const override {
1087  switch (Kind) {
1088  case Register:
1089  OS << "<register " << getReg() << " mods: " << Reg.Mods << '>';
1090  break;
1091  case Immediate:
1092  OS << '<' << getImm();
1093  if (getImmTy() != ImmTyNone) {
1094  OS << " type: "; printImmTy(OS, getImmTy());
1095  }
1096  OS << " mods: " << Imm.Mods << '>';
1097  break;
1098  case Token:
1099  OS << '\'' << getToken() << '\'';
1100  break;
1101  case Expression:
1102  OS << "<expr " << *Expr << '>';
1103  break;
1104  }
1105  }

1107  static AMDGPUOperand::Ptr CreateImm(const AMDGPUAsmParser *AsmParser,
1108  int64_t Val, SMLoc Loc,
1109  ImmTy Type = ImmTyNone,
1110  bool IsFPImm = false) {
1111  auto Op = std::make_unique<AMDGPUOperand>(Immediate, AsmParser);
1112  Op->Imm.Val = Val;
1113  Op->Imm.IsFPImm = IsFPImm;
1114  Op->Imm.Kind = ImmKindTyNone;
1115  Op->Imm.Type = Type;
1116  Op->Imm.Mods = Modifiers();
1117  Op->StartLoc = Loc;
1118  Op->EndLoc = Loc;
1119  return Op;
1120  }
1121 
1122  static AMDGPUOperand::Ptr CreateToken(const AMDGPUAsmParser *AsmParser,
1123  StringRef Str, SMLoc Loc,
1124  bool HasExplicitEncodingSize = true) {
1125  auto Res = std::make_unique<AMDGPUOperand>(Token, AsmParser);
1126  Res->Tok.Data = Str.data();
1127  Res->Tok.Length = Str.size();
1128  Res->StartLoc = Loc;
1129  Res->EndLoc = Loc;
1130  return Res;
1131  }
1132 
1133  static AMDGPUOperand::Ptr CreateReg(const AMDGPUAsmParser *AsmParser,
1134  unsigned RegNo, SMLoc S,
1135  SMLoc E) {
1136  auto Op = std::make_unique<AMDGPUOperand>(Register, AsmParser);
1137  Op->Reg.RegNo = RegNo;
1138  Op->Reg.Mods = Modifiers();
1139  Op->StartLoc = S;
1140  Op->EndLoc = E;
1141  return Op;
1142  }
1143 
1144  static AMDGPUOperand::Ptr CreateExpr(const AMDGPUAsmParser *AsmParser,
1145  const class MCExpr *Expr, SMLoc S) {
1146  auto Op = std::make_unique<AMDGPUOperand>(Expression, AsmParser);
1147  Op->Expr = Expr;
1148  Op->StartLoc = S;
1149  Op->EndLoc = S;
1150  return Op;
1151  }
1152 };

1154 raw_ostream &operator <<(raw_ostream &OS, AMDGPUOperand::Modifiers Mods) {
1155  OS << "abs:" << Mods.Abs << " neg: " << Mods.Neg << " sext:" << Mods.Sext;
1156  return OS;
1157 }

1159 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

1162 
1163 // Holds info related to the current kernel, e.g. count of SGPRs used.
1164 // Kernel scope begins at .amdgpu_hsa_kernel directive, ends at next
1165 // .amdgpu_hsa_kernel or at EOF.
1166 class KernelScopeInfo {
1167  int SgprIndexUnusedMin = -1;
1168  int VgprIndexUnusedMin = -1;
1169  int AgprIndexUnusedMin = -1;
1170  MCContext *Ctx = nullptr;
1171  MCSubtargetInfo const *MSTI = nullptr;
1172 
1173  void usesSgprAt(int i) {
1174  if (i >= SgprIndexUnusedMin) {
1175  SgprIndexUnusedMin = ++i;
1176  if (Ctx) {
1177  MCSymbol* const Sym =
1178  Ctx->getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".kernel.sgpr_count"));
1179  Sym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(SgprIndexUnusedMin, *Ctx));
1180  }
1181  }
1182  }
1183 
1184  void usesVgprAt(int i) {
1185  if (i >= VgprIndexUnusedMin) {
1186  VgprIndexUnusedMin = ++i;
1187  if (Ctx) {
1188  MCSymbol* const Sym =
1189  Ctx->getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".kernel.vgpr_count"));
1190  int totalVGPR = getTotalNumVGPRs(isGFX90A(*MSTI), AgprIndexUnusedMin,
1191  VgprIndexUnusedMin);
1192  Sym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(totalVGPR, *Ctx));
1193  }
1194  }
1195  }
1196 
1197  void usesAgprAt(int i) {
1198  // Instruction will error in AMDGPUAsmParser::MatchAndEmitInstruction
1199  if (!hasMAIInsts(*MSTI))
1200  return;
1201 
1202  if (i >= AgprIndexUnusedMin) {
1203  AgprIndexUnusedMin = ++i;
1204  if (Ctx) {
1205  MCSymbol* const Sym =
1206  Ctx->getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".kernel.agpr_count"));
1207  Sym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(AgprIndexUnusedMin, *Ctx));
1208 
1209  // Also update vgpr_count (dependent on agpr_count for gfx908/gfx90a)
1210  MCSymbol* const vSym =
1211  Ctx->getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".kernel.vgpr_count"));
1212  int totalVGPR = getTotalNumVGPRs(isGFX90A(*MSTI), AgprIndexUnusedMin,
1213  VgprIndexUnusedMin);
1214  vSym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(totalVGPR, *Ctx));
1215  }
1216  }
1217  }
1218 
1219 public:
1220  KernelScopeInfo() = default;
1221 
1222  void initialize(MCContext &Context) {
1223  Ctx = &Context;
1224  MSTI = Ctx->getSubtargetInfo();
1225 
1226  usesSgprAt(SgprIndexUnusedMin = -1);
1227  usesVgprAt(VgprIndexUnusedMin = -1);
1228  if (hasMAIInsts(*MSTI)) {
1229  usesAgprAt(AgprIndexUnusedMin = -1);
1230  }
1231  }
1232 
1233  void usesRegister(RegisterKind RegKind, unsigned DwordRegIndex,
1234  unsigned RegWidth) {
1235  switch (RegKind) {
1236  case IS_SGPR:
1237  usesSgprAt(DwordRegIndex + divideCeil(RegWidth, 32) - 1);
1238  break;
1239  case IS_AGPR:
1240  usesAgprAt(DwordRegIndex + divideCeil(RegWidth, 32) - 1);
1241  break;
1242  case IS_VGPR:
1243  usesVgprAt(DwordRegIndex + divideCeil(RegWidth, 32) - 1);
1244  break;
1245  default:
1246  break;
1247  }
1248  }
1249 };
1250 
1251 class AMDGPUAsmParser : public MCTargetAsmParser {
1252  MCAsmParser &Parser;
1253 
1254  unsigned ForcedEncodingSize = 0;
1255  bool ForcedDPP = false;
1256  bool ForcedSDWA = false;
1257  KernelScopeInfo KernelScope;
1258 
1259  /// @name Auto-generated Match Functions
1260  /// {
1261 
1262 #define GET_ASSEMBLER_HEADER
1263 #include "AMDGPUGenAsmMatcher.inc"
1264 
1265  /// }
1266 
1267 private:
1268  bool ParseAsAbsoluteExpression(uint32_t &Ret);
1269  bool OutOfRangeError(SMRange Range);
1270  /// Calculate VGPR/SGPR blocks required for given target, reserved
1271  /// registers, and user-specified NextFreeXGPR values.
1272  ///
1273  /// \param Features [in] Target features, used for bug corrections.
1274  /// \param VCCUsed [in] Whether VCC special SGPR is reserved.
1275  /// \param FlatScrUsed [in] Whether FLAT_SCRATCH special SGPR is reserved.

1278  /// descriptor field, if valid.
1279  /// \param NextFreeVGPR [in] Max VGPR number referenced, plus one.
1280  /// \param VGPRRange [in] Token range, used for VGPR diagnostics.
1281  /// \param NextFreeSGPR [in] Max SGPR number referenced, plus one.
1282  /// \param SGPRRange [in] Token range, used for SGPR diagnostics.
1283  /// \param VGPRBlocks [out] Result VGPR block count.
1284  /// \param SGPRBlocks [out] Result SGPR block count.

1356  using OptionalImmIndexMap = std::map<AMDGPUOperand::ImmTy, unsigned>;
1357 
1358  AMDGPUAsmParser(const MCSubtargetInfo &STI, MCAsmParser &_Parser,
1359  const MCInstrInfo &MII,
1360  const MCTargetOptions &Options)
1361  : MCTargetAsmParser(Options, STI, MII), Parser(_Parser) {
1362  MCAsmParserExtension::Initialize(Parser);
1363 
1364  if (getFeatureBits().none()) {
1365  // Set default features.
1366  copySTI().ToggleFeature("southern-islands");
1367  }
1368 
1369  setAvailableFeatures(ComputeAvailableFeatures(getFeatureBits()));
1370 
1371  {
1372  // TODO: make those pre-defined variables read-only.
1373  // Currently there is none suitable machinery in the core llvm-mc for this.
1374  // MCSymbol::isRedefinable is intended for another purpose, and
1375  // AsmParser::parseDirectiveSet() cannot be specialized for specific target.
1376  AMDGPU::IsaVersion ISA = AMDGPU::getIsaVersion(getSTI().getCPU());
1377  MCContext &Ctx = getContext();
1378  if (ISA.Major >= 6 && isHsaAbiVersion3AndAbove(&getSTI())) {
1379  MCSymbol *Sym =
1380  Ctx.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".amdgcn.gfx_generation_number"));
1381  Sym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(ISA.Major, Ctx));
1382  Sym = Ctx.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".amdgcn.gfx_generation_minor"));
1383  Sym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(ISA.Minor, Ctx));
1384  Sym = Ctx.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".amdgcn.gfx_generation_stepping"));
1385  Sym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(ISA.Stepping, Ctx));
1386  } else {
1387  MCSymbol *Sym =
1388  Ctx.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".option.machine_version_major"));
1389  Sym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(ISA.Major, Ctx));
1390  Sym = Ctx.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".option.machine_version_minor"));
1391  Sym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(ISA.Minor, Ctx));
1392  Sym = Ctx.getOrCreateSymbol(Twine(".option.machine_version_stepping"));
1393  Sym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(ISA.Stepping, Ctx));
1394  }
1395  if (ISA.Major >= 6 && isHsaAbiVersion3AndAbove(&getSTI())) {
1396  initializeGprCountSymbol(IS_VGPR);
1397  initializeGprCountSymbol(IS_SGPR);
1398  } else
1399  KernelScope.initialize(getContext());
1400  }
1401  }

1824 // May be called with integer type with equivalent bitwidth.
1825 static const fltSemantics *getFltSemantics(unsigned Size) {
1826  switch (Size) {
1827  case 4:
1828  return &APFloat::IEEEsingle();
1829  case 8:
1830  return &APFloat::IEEEdouble();
1831  case 2:
1832  return &APFloat::IEEEhalf();
1833  default:
1834  llvm_unreachable("unsupported fp type");
1835  }
1836 }
1837 
1838 static const fltSemantics *getFltSemantics(MVT VT) {
1839  return getFltSemantics(VT.getSizeInBits() / 8);
1840 }
1841 
1842 static const fltSemantics *getOpFltSemantics(uint8_t OperandType) {
1843  switch (OperandType) {
1844  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT32:
1845  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP32:
1846  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP32_DEFERRED:
1847  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT32:
1848  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP32:
1849  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_INT32:
1850  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_FP32:
1851  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2FP32:
1852  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2FP32:
1853  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2INT32:
1854  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2INT32:
1855  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_KIMM32:
1856  return &APFloat::IEEEsingle();
1857  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT64:
1858  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP64:
1859  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT64:
1860  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP64:
1861  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_FP64:
1862  return &APFloat::IEEEdouble();
1863  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT16:
1864  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP16:
1865  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP16_DEFERRED:
1866  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT16:
1867  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP16:
1868  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2INT16:
1869  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2FP16:
1870  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_INT16:
1871  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_FP16:
1872  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_V2INT16:
1873  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_V2FP16:
1874  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2INT16:
1875  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2FP16:
1876  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_KIMM16:
1877  return &APFloat::IEEEhalf();
1878  default:
1879  llvm_unreachable("unsupported fp type");
1880  }
1881 }

1886 
1887 static bool canLosslesslyConvertToFPType(APFloat &FPLiteral, MVT VT) {
1888  bool Lost;
1889 
1890  // Convert literal to single precision
1891  APFloat::opStatus Status = FPLiteral.convert(*getFltSemantics(VT),
1892  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven,
1893  &Lost);
1894  // We allow precision lost but not overflow or underflow
1895  if (Status != APFloat::opOK &&
1896  Lost &&
1897  ((Status & APFloat::opOverflow) != 0 ||
1898  (Status & APFloat::opUnderflow) != 0)) {
1899  return false;
1900  }
1901 
1902  return true;
1903 }
1904 
1905 static bool isSafeTruncation(int64_t Val, unsigned Size) {
1906  return isUIntN(Size, Val) || isIntN(Size, Val);
1907 }
1908 
1909 static bool isInlineableLiteralOp16(int64_t Val, MVT VT, bool HasInv2Pi) {
1910  if (VT.getScalarType() == MVT::i16) {
1911  // FP immediate values are broken.
1912  return isInlinableIntLiteral(Val);
1913  }
1914 
1915  // f16/v2f16 operands work correctly for all values.
1916  return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral16(Val, HasInv2Pi);
1917 }
1918 
1919 bool AMDGPUOperand::isInlinableImm(MVT type) const {
1920 
1921  // This is a hack to enable named inline values like
1922  // shared_base with both 32-bit and 64-bit operands.
1923  // Note that these values are defined as
1924  // 32-bit operands only.
1925  if (isInlineValue()) {
1926  return true;
1927  }
1928 
1929  if (!isImmTy(ImmTyNone)) {
1930  // Only plain immediates are inlinable (e.g. "clamp" attribute is not)
1931  return false;
1932  }
1933  // TODO: We should avoid using host float here. It would be better to
1934  // check the float bit values which is what a few other places do.
1935  // We've had bot failures before due to weird NaN support on mips hosts.
1936 
1937  APInt Literal(64, Imm.Val);
1938 
1939  if (Imm.IsFPImm) { // We got fp literal token
1940  if (type == MVT::f64 || type == MVT::i64) { // Expected 64-bit operand
1941  return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral64(Imm.Val,
1942  AsmParser->hasInv2PiInlineImm());
1943  }
1944 
1945  APFloat FPLiteral(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APInt(64, Imm.Val));
1946  if (!canLosslesslyConvertToFPType(FPLiteral, type))
1947  return false;
1948 
1949  if (type.getScalarSizeInBits() == 16) {
1950  return isInlineableLiteralOp16(
1951  static_cast<int16_t>(FPLiteral.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue()),
1952  type, AsmParser->hasInv2PiInlineImm());
1953  }
1954 
1955  // Check if single precision literal is inlinable
1956  return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral32(
1957  static_cast<int32_t>(FPLiteral.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue()),
1958  AsmParser->hasInv2PiInlineImm());
1959  }
1960 
1961  // We got int literal token.
1962  if (type == MVT::f64 || type == MVT::i64) { // Expected 64-bit operand
1963  return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral64(Imm.Val,
1964  AsmParser->hasInv2PiInlineImm());
1965  }
1966 
1967  if (!isSafeTruncation(Imm.Val, type.getScalarSizeInBits())) {
1968  return false;
1969  }
1970 
1971  if (type.getScalarSizeInBits() == 16) {
1972  return isInlineableLiteralOp16(
1973  static_cast<int16_t>(Literal.getLoBits(16).getSExtValue()),
1974  type, AsmParser->hasInv2PiInlineImm());
1975  }
1976 
1977  return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral32(
1978  static_cast<int32_t>(Literal.getLoBits(32).getZExtValue()),
1979  AsmParser->hasInv2PiInlineImm());
1980 }
1981 
1982 bool AMDGPUOperand::isLiteralImm(MVT type) const {
1983  // Check that this immediate can be added as literal
1984  if (!isImmTy(ImmTyNone)) {
1985  return false;
1986  }
1987 
1988  if (!Imm.IsFPImm) {
1989  // We got int literal token.
1990 
1991  if (type == MVT::f64 && hasFPModifiers()) {
1992  // Cannot apply fp modifiers to int literals preserving the same semantics
1993  // for VOP1/2/C and VOP3 because of integer truncation. To avoid ambiguity,
1994  // disable these cases.
1995  return false;
1996  }
1997 
1998  unsigned Size = type.getSizeInBits();
1999  if (Size == 64)
2000  Size = 32;
2001 
2002  // FIXME: 64-bit operands can zero extend, sign extend, or pad zeroes for FP
2003  // types.
2004  return isSafeTruncation(Imm.Val, Size);
2005  }
2006 
2007  // We got fp literal token
2008  if (type == MVT::f64) { // Expected 64-bit fp operand
2009  // We would set low 64-bits of literal to zeroes but we accept this literals
2010  return true;
2011  }
2012 
2013  if (type == MVT::i64) { // Expected 64-bit int operand
2014  // We don't allow fp literals in 64-bit integer instructions. It is
2015  // unclear how we should encode them.
2016  return false;
2017  }
2018 
2019  // We allow fp literals with f16x2 operands assuming that the specified
2020  // literal goes into the lower half and the upper half is zero. We also
2021  // require that the literal may be losslessly converted to f16.
2022  MVT ExpectedType = (type == MVT::v2f16)? MVT::f16 :
2023  (type == MVT::v2i16)? MVT::i16 :
2024  (type == MVT::v2f32)? MVT::f32 : type;
2025 
2026  APFloat FPLiteral(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APInt(64, Imm.Val));
2027  return canLosslesslyConvertToFPType(FPLiteral, ExpectedType);
2028 }

2030 bool AMDGPUOperand::isRegClass(unsigned RCID) const {
2031  return isRegKind() && AsmParser->getMRI()->getRegClass(RCID).contains(getReg());
2032 }

2035  return isRegClass(AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClassID) ||
2036  // GFX90A allows DPP on 64-bit operands.
2037  (isRegClass(AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClassID) &&
2038  AsmParser->getFeatureBits()[AMDGPU::Feature64BitDPP]);
2039 }

2043 }

2045 bool AMDGPUOperand::isSDWAOperand(MVT type) const {
2046  if (AsmParser->isVI())
2047  return isVReg32();
2048  else if (AsmParser->isGFX9Plus())
2049  return isRegClass(AMDGPU::VS_32RegClassID) || isInlinableImm(type);
2050  else
2051  return false;
2052 }

2070 bool AMDGPUOperand::isBoolReg() const {
2071  auto FB = AsmParser->getFeatureBits();
2072  return isReg() && ((FB[AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize64] && isSCSrcB64()) ||
2073  (FB[AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize32] && isSCSrcB32()));
2074 }
2075 
2076 uint64_t AMDGPUOperand::applyInputFPModifiers(uint64_t Val, unsigned Size) const
2077 {
2078  assert(isImmTy(ImmTyNone) && Imm.Mods.hasFPModifiers());
2079  assert(Size == 2 || Size == 4 || Size == 8);
2080 
2081  const uint64_t FpSignMask = (1ULL << (Size * 8 - 1));
2082 
2083  if (Imm.Mods.Abs) {
2084  Val &= ~FpSignMask;
2085  }
2086  if (Imm.Mods.Neg) {
2087  Val ^= FpSignMask;
2088  }
2089 
2090  return Val;
2091 }
2092 
2093 void AMDGPUOperand::addImmOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N, bool ApplyModifiers) const {
2094  if (AMDGPU::isSISrcOperand(AsmParser->getMII()->get(Inst.getOpcode()),
2095  Inst.getNumOperands())) {
2096  addLiteralImmOperand(Inst, Imm.Val,
2097  ApplyModifiers &
2098  isImmTy(ImmTyNone) && Imm.Mods.hasFPModifiers());
2099  } else {
2100  assert(!isImmTy(ImmTyNone) || !hasModifiers());
2101  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Imm.Val));
2102  setImmKindNone();
2103  }
2104 }
2105 
2106 void AMDGPUOperand::addLiteralImmOperand(MCInst &Inst, int64_t Val, bool ApplyModifiers) const {
2107  const auto& InstDesc = AsmParser->getMII()->get(Inst.getOpcode());
2108  auto OpNum = Inst.getNumOperands();
2109  // Check that this operand accepts literals
2110  assert(AMDGPU::isSISrcOperand(InstDesc, OpNum));
2111 
2112  if (ApplyModifiers) {
2113  assert(AMDGPU::isSISrcFPOperand(InstDesc, OpNum));
2114  const unsigned Size = Imm.IsFPImm ? sizeof(double) : getOperandSize(InstDesc, OpNum);
2115  Val = applyInputFPModifiers(Val, Size);
2116  }
2117 
2118  APInt Literal(64, Val);
2119  uint8_t OpTy = InstDesc.operands()[OpNum].OperandType;
2120 
2121  if (Imm.IsFPImm) { // We got fp literal token
2122  switch (OpTy) {
2123  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT64:
2124  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP64:
2125  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT64:
2126  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP64:
2127  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_FP64:
2128  if (AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral64(Literal.getZExtValue(),
2129  AsmParser->hasInv2PiInlineImm())) {
2130  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Literal.getZExtValue()));
2131  setImmKindConst();
2132  return;
2133  }
2134 
2135  // Non-inlineable
2136  if (AMDGPU::isSISrcFPOperand(InstDesc, OpNum)) { // Expected 64-bit fp operand
2137  // For fp operands we check if low 32 bits are zeros
2138  if (Literal.getLoBits(32) != 0) {
2139  const_cast<AMDGPUAsmParser *>(AsmParser)->Warning(Inst.getLoc(),
2140  "Can't encode literal as exact 64-bit floating-point operand. "
2141  "Low 32-bits will be set to zero");
2142  }
2143 
2144  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Literal.lshr(32).getZExtValue()));
2145  setImmKindLiteral();
2146  return;
2147  }
2148 
2149  // We don't allow fp literals in 64-bit integer instructions. It is
2150  // unclear how we should encode them. This case should be checked earlier
2151  // in predicate methods (isLiteralImm())
2152  llvm_unreachable("fp literal in 64-bit integer instruction.");
2153 
2154  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT32:
2155  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP32:
2156  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP32_DEFERRED:
2157  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT32:
2158  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP32:
2159  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_INT32:
2160  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_FP32:
2161  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT16:
2162  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP16:
2163  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP16_DEFERRED:
2164  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT16:
2165  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP16:
2166  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2INT16:
2167  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2FP16:
2168  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_INT16:
2169  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_FP16:
2170  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_V2INT16:
2171  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_V2FP16:
2172  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2INT16:
2173  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2FP16:
2174  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2FP32:
2175  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2FP32:
2176  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2INT32:
2177  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2INT32:
2178  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_KIMM32:
2179  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_KIMM16: {
2180  bool lost;
2181  APFloat FPLiteral(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), Literal);
2182  // Convert literal to single precision
2183  FPLiteral.convert(*getOpFltSemantics(OpTy),
2184  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &lost);
2185  // We allow precision lost but not overflow or underflow. This should be
2186  // checked earlier in isLiteralImm()
2187 
2188  uint64_t ImmVal = FPLiteral.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue();
2189  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(ImmVal));
2190  if (OpTy == AMDGPU::OPERAND_KIMM32 || OpTy == AMDGPU::OPERAND_KIMM16) {
2191  setImmKindMandatoryLiteral();
2192  } else {
2193  setImmKindLiteral();
2194  }
2195  return;
2196  }
2197  default:
2198  llvm_unreachable("invalid operand size");
2199  }
2200 
2201  return;
2202  }
2203 
2204  // We got int literal token.
2205  // Only sign extend inline immediates.
2206  switch (OpTy) {
2207  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT32:
2208  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP32:
2209  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP32_DEFERRED:
2210  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT32:
2211  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP32:
2212  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_INT32:
2213  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_FP32:
2214  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2INT16:
2215  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2FP16:
2216  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2FP32:
2217  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2FP32:
2218  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2INT32:
2219  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2INT32:
2220  if (isSafeTruncation(Val, 32) &&
2221  AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral32(static_cast<int32_t>(Val),
2222  AsmParser->hasInv2PiInlineImm())) {
2223  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val));
2224  setImmKindConst();
2225  return;
2226  }
2227 
2228  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val & 0xffffffff));
2229  setImmKindLiteral();
2230  return;
2231 
2232  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT64:
2233  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP64:
2234  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT64:
2235  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP64:
2236  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_FP64:
2237  if (AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral64(Val, AsmParser->hasInv2PiInlineImm())) {
2238  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val));
2239  setImmKindConst();
2240  return;
2241  }
2242 
2243  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Lo_32(Val)));
2244  setImmKindLiteral();
2245  return;
2246 
2247  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT16:
2248  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP16:
2249  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_FP16_DEFERRED:
2250  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT16:
2251  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_FP16:
2252  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_INT16:
2253  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_FP16:
2254  if (isSafeTruncation(Val, 16) &&
2255  AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral16(static_cast<int16_t>(Val),
2256  AsmParser->hasInv2PiInlineImm())) {
2257  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val));
2258  setImmKindConst();
2259  return;
2260  }
2261 
2262  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val & 0xffff));
2263  setImmKindLiteral();
2264  return;
2265 
2266  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2INT16:
2267  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2FP16:
2268  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_V2INT16:
2269  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_V2FP16: {
2270  assert(isSafeTruncation(Val, 16));
2271  assert(AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral16(static_cast<int16_t>(Val),
2272  AsmParser->hasInv2PiInlineImm()));
2273 
2274  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Val));
2275  return;
2276  }
2277  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_KIMM32:
2278  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Literal.getLoBits(32).getZExtValue()));
2279  setImmKindMandatoryLiteral();
2280  return;
2281  case AMDGPU::OPERAND_KIMM16:
2282  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Literal.getLoBits(16).getZExtValue()));
2283  setImmKindMandatoryLiteral();
2284  return;
2285  default:
2286  llvm_unreachable("invalid operand size");
2287  }
2288 }
2289 
2290 template <unsigned Bitwidth>
2291 void AMDGPUOperand::addKImmFPOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2292  APInt Literal(64, Imm.Val);
2293  setImmKindMandatoryLiteral();
2294 
2295  if (!Imm.IsFPImm) {
2296  // We got int literal token.
2297  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Literal.getLoBits(Bitwidth).getZExtValue()));
2298  return;
2299  }
2300 
2301  bool Lost;
2302  APFloat FPLiteral(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), Literal);
2303  FPLiteral.convert(*getFltSemantics(Bitwidth / 8),
2304  APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &Lost);
2305  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(FPLiteral.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue()));
2306 }
2307 
2308 void AMDGPUOperand::addRegOperands(MCInst &Inst, unsigned N) const {
2309  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AMDGPU::getMCReg(getReg(), AsmParser->getSTI())));
2310 }

2493 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::tryParseRegister(MCRegister &RegNo,
2494  SMLoc &StartLoc,
2495  SMLoc &EndLoc) {
2496  bool Result =
2497  ParseRegister(RegNo, StartLoc, EndLoc, /*RestoreOnFailure=*/true);
2498  bool PendingErrors = getParser().hasPendingError();
2499  getParser().clearPendingErrors();
2500  if (PendingErrors)
2501  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
2502  if (Result)
2503  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
2504  return MatchOperand_Success;
2505 }
2506 
2507 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::AddNextRegisterToList(unsigned &Reg, unsigned &RegWidth,
2508  RegisterKind RegKind, unsigned Reg1,
2509  SMLoc Loc) {
2510  switch (RegKind) {
2511  case IS_SPECIAL:
2512  if (Reg == AMDGPU::EXEC_LO && Reg1 == AMDGPU::EXEC_HI) {
2513  Reg = AMDGPU::EXEC;
2514  RegWidth = 64;
2515  return true;
2516  }
2517  if (Reg == AMDGPU::FLAT_SCR_LO && Reg1 == AMDGPU::FLAT_SCR_HI) {
2518  Reg = AMDGPU::FLAT_SCR;
2519  RegWidth = 64;
2520  return true;
2521  }
2522  if (Reg == AMDGPU::XNACK_MASK_LO && Reg1 == AMDGPU::XNACK_MASK_HI) {
2523  Reg = AMDGPU::XNACK_MASK;
2524  RegWidth = 64;
2525  return true;
2526  }
2527  if (Reg == AMDGPU::VCC_LO && Reg1 == AMDGPU::VCC_HI) {
2528  Reg = AMDGPU::VCC;
2529  RegWidth = 64;
2530  return true;
2531  }
2532  if (Reg == AMDGPU::TBA_LO && Reg1 == AMDGPU::TBA_HI) {
2533  Reg = AMDGPU::TBA;
2534  RegWidth = 64;
2535  return true;
2536  }
2537  if (Reg == AMDGPU::TMA_LO && Reg1 == AMDGPU::TMA_HI) {
2538  Reg = AMDGPU::TMA;
2539  RegWidth = 64;
2540  return true;
2541  }
2542  Error(Loc, "register does not fit in the list");
2543  return false;
2544  case IS_VGPR:
2545  case IS_SGPR:
2546  case IS_AGPR:
2547  case IS_TTMP:
2548  if (Reg1 != Reg + RegWidth / 32) {
2549  Error(Loc, "registers in a list must have consecutive indices");
2550  return false;
2551  }
2552  RegWidth += 32;
2553  return true;
2554  default:
2555  llvm_unreachable("unexpected register kind");
2556  }
2557 }

2559 struct RegInfo {
2560  StringLiteral Name;
2561  RegisterKind Kind;
2562 };
2563 
2564 static constexpr RegInfo RegularRegisters[] = {
2565  {{"v"}, IS_VGPR},
2566  {{"s"}, IS_SGPR},
2567  {{"ttmp"}, IS_TTMP},
2568  {{"acc"}, IS_AGPR},
2569  {{"a"}, IS_AGPR},
2570 };

2572 static bool isRegularReg(RegisterKind Kind) {
2573  return Kind == IS_VGPR ||
2574  Kind == IS_SGPR ||
2575  Kind == IS_TTMP ||
2576  Kind == IS_AGPR;
2577 }
2578 
2579 static const RegInfo* getRegularRegInfo(StringRef Str) {
2580  for (const RegInfo &Reg : RegularRegisters)
2581  if (Str.startswith(Reg.Name))
2582  return &Reg;
2583  return nullptr;
2584 }
2585 
2586 static bool getRegNum(StringRef Str, unsigned& Num) {
2587  return !Str.getAsInteger(10, Num);
2588 }
2589 
2590 bool
2591 AMDGPUAsmParser::isRegister(const AsmToken &Token,
2592  const AsmToken &NextToken) const {
2593 
2594  // A list of consecutive registers: [s0,s1,s2,s3]
2595  if (Token.is(AsmToken::LBrac))
2596  return true;
2597 
2598  if (!Token.is(AsmToken::Identifier))
2599  return false;
2600 
2601  // A single register like s0 or a range of registers like s[0:1]
2602 
2603  StringRef Str = Token.getString();
2604  const RegInfo *Reg = getRegularRegInfo(Str);
2605  if (Reg) {
2606  StringRef RegName = Reg->Name;
2607  StringRef RegSuffix = Str.substr(RegName.size());
2608  if (!RegSuffix.empty()) {
2609  unsigned Num;
2610  // A single register with an index: rXX
2611  if (getRegNum(RegSuffix, Num))
2612  return true;
2613  } else {
2614  // A range of registers: r[XX:YY].
2615  if (NextToken.is(AsmToken::LBrac))
2616  return true;
2617  }
2618  }
2619 
2620  return getSpecialRegForName(Str) != AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2621 }
2622 
2623 bool
2624 AMDGPUAsmParser::isRegister()
2625 {
2626  return isRegister(getToken(), peekToken());
2627 }
2628 
2629 unsigned
2630 AMDGPUAsmParser::getRegularReg(RegisterKind RegKind,
2631  unsigned RegNum,
2632  unsigned RegWidth,
2633  SMLoc Loc) {
2634 
2635  assert(isRegularReg(RegKind));
2636 
2637  unsigned AlignSize = 1;
2638  if (RegKind == IS_SGPR || RegKind == IS_TTMP) {
2639  // SGPR and TTMP registers must be aligned.
2640  // Max required alignment is 4 dwords.
2641  AlignSize = std::min(RegWidth / 32, 4u);
2642  }
2643 
2644  if (RegNum % AlignSize != 0) {
2645  Error(Loc, "invalid register alignment");
2646  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2647  }
2648 
2649  unsigned RegIdx = RegNum / AlignSize;
2650  int RCID = getRegClass(RegKind, RegWidth);
2651  if (RCID == -1) {
2652  Error(Loc, "invalid or unsupported register size");
2653  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2654  }
2655 
2656  const MCRegisterInfo *TRI = getContext().getRegisterInfo();
2657  const MCRegisterClass RC = TRI->getRegClass(RCID);
2658  if (RegIdx >= RC.getNumRegs()) {
2659  Error(Loc, "register index is out of range");
2660  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2661  }
2662 
2663  return RC.getRegister(RegIdx);
2664 }
2665 
2666 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseRegRange(unsigned &Num, unsigned &RegWidth) {
2667  int64_t RegLo, RegHi;
2668  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::LBrac, "missing register index"))
2669  return false;
2670 
2671  SMLoc FirstIdxLoc = getLoc();
2672  SMLoc SecondIdxLoc;
2673 
2674  if (!parseExpr(RegLo))
2675  return false;
2676 
2677  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::Colon)) {
2678  SecondIdxLoc = getLoc();
2679  if (!parseExpr(RegHi))
2680  return false;
2681  } else {
2682  RegHi = RegLo;
2683  }
2684 
2685  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::RBrac, "expected a closing square bracket"))
2686  return false;
2687 
2688  if (!isUInt<32>(RegLo)) {
2689  Error(FirstIdxLoc, "invalid register index");
2690  return false;
2691  }
2692 
2693  if (!isUInt<32>(RegHi)) {
2694  Error(SecondIdxLoc, "invalid register index");
2695  return false;
2696  }
2697 
2698  if (RegLo > RegHi) {
2699  Error(FirstIdxLoc, "first register index should not exceed second index");
2700  return false;
2701  }
2702 
2703  Num = static_cast<unsigned>(RegLo);
2704  RegWidth = 32 * ((RegHi - RegLo) + 1);
2705  return true;
2706 }
2707 
2708 unsigned AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseSpecialReg(RegisterKind &RegKind,
2709  unsigned &RegNum, unsigned &RegWidth,
2710  SmallVectorImpl<AsmToken> &Tokens) {
2711  assert(isToken(AsmToken::Identifier));
2712  unsigned Reg = getSpecialRegForName(getTokenStr());
2713  if (Reg) {
2714  RegNum = 0;
2715  RegWidth = 32;
2716  RegKind = IS_SPECIAL;
2717  Tokens.push_back(getToken());
2718  lex(); // skip register name
2719  }
2720  return Reg;
2721 }
2722 
2723 unsigned AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseRegularReg(RegisterKind &RegKind,
2724  unsigned &RegNum, unsigned &RegWidth,
2725  SmallVectorImpl<AsmToken> &Tokens) {
2726  assert(isToken(AsmToken::Identifier));
2727  StringRef RegName = getTokenStr();
2728  auto Loc = getLoc();
2729 
2730  const RegInfo *RI = getRegularRegInfo(RegName);
2731  if (!RI) {
2732  Error(Loc, "invalid register name");
2733  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2734  }
2735 
2736  Tokens.push_back(getToken());
2737  lex(); // skip register name
2738 
2739  RegKind = RI->Kind;
2740  StringRef RegSuffix = RegName.substr(RI->Name.size());
2741  if (!RegSuffix.empty()) {
2742  // Single 32-bit register: vXX.
2743  if (!getRegNum(RegSuffix, RegNum)) {
2744  Error(Loc, "invalid register index");
2745  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2746  }
2747  RegWidth = 32;
2748  } else {
2749  // Range of registers: v[XX:YY]. ":YY" is optional.
2750  if (!ParseRegRange(RegNum, RegWidth))
2751  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2752  }
2753 
2754  return getRegularReg(RegKind, RegNum, RegWidth, Loc);
2755 }
2756 
2757 unsigned AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseRegList(RegisterKind &RegKind, unsigned &RegNum,
2758  unsigned &RegWidth,
2759  SmallVectorImpl<AsmToken> &Tokens) {
2760  unsigned Reg = AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2761  auto ListLoc = getLoc();
2762 
2763  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::LBrac,
2764  "expected a register or a list of registers")) {
2765  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2766  }
2767 
2768  // List of consecutive registers, e.g.: [s0,s1,s2,s3]
2769 
2770  auto Loc = getLoc();
2771  if (!ParseAMDGPURegister(RegKind, Reg, RegNum, RegWidth))
2772  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2773  if (RegWidth != 32) {
2774  Error(Loc, "expected a single 32-bit register");
2775  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2776  }
2777 
2778  for (; trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma); ) {
2779  RegisterKind NextRegKind;
2780  unsigned NextReg, NextRegNum, NextRegWidth;
2781  Loc = getLoc();
2782 
2783  if (!ParseAMDGPURegister(NextRegKind, NextReg,
2784  NextRegNum, NextRegWidth,
2785  Tokens)) {
2786  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2787  }
2788  if (NextRegWidth != 32) {
2789  Error(Loc, "expected a single 32-bit register");
2790  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2791  }
2792  if (NextRegKind != RegKind) {
2793  Error(Loc, "registers in a list must be of the same kind");
2794  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2795  }
2796  if (!AddNextRegisterToList(Reg, RegWidth, RegKind, NextReg, Loc))
2797  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2798  }
2799 
2800  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::RBrac,
2801  "expected a comma or a closing square bracket")) {
2802  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2803  }
2804 
2805  if (isRegularReg(RegKind))
2806  Reg = getRegularReg(RegKind, RegNum, RegWidth, ListLoc);
2807 
2808  return Reg;
2809 }
2810 
2811 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseAMDGPURegister(RegisterKind &RegKind, unsigned &Reg,
2812  unsigned &RegNum, unsigned &RegWidth,
2813  SmallVectorImpl<AsmToken> &Tokens) {
2814  auto Loc = getLoc();
2815  Reg = AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2816 
2817  if (isToken(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
2818  Reg = ParseSpecialReg(RegKind, RegNum, RegWidth, Tokens);
2819  if (Reg == AMDGPU::NoRegister)
2820  Reg = ParseRegularReg(RegKind, RegNum, RegWidth, Tokens);
2821  } else {
2822  Reg = ParseRegList(RegKind, RegNum, RegWidth, Tokens);
2823  }
2824 
2825  const MCRegisterInfo *TRI = getContext().getRegisterInfo();
2826  if (Reg == AMDGPU::NoRegister) {
2827  assert(Parser.hasPendingError());
2828  return false;
2829  }
2830 
2831  if (!subtargetHasRegister(*TRI, Reg)) {
2832  if (Reg == AMDGPU::SGPR_NULL) {
2833  Error(Loc, "'null' operand is not supported on this GPU");
2834  } else {
2835  Error(Loc, "register not available on this GPU");
2836  }
2837  return false;
2838  }
2839 
2840  return true;
2841 }
2842 
2843 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseAMDGPURegister(RegisterKind &RegKind, unsigned &Reg,
2844  unsigned &RegNum, unsigned &RegWidth,
2845  bool RestoreOnFailure /*=false*/) {
2846  Reg = AMDGPU::NoRegister;
2847 
2848  SmallVector<AsmToken, 1> Tokens;
2849  if (ParseAMDGPURegister(RegKind, Reg, RegNum, RegWidth, Tokens)) {
2850  if (RestoreOnFailure) {
2851  while (!Tokens.empty()) {
2852  getLexer().UnLex(Tokens.pop_back_val());
2853  }
2854  }
2855  return true;
2856  }
2857  return false;
2858 }
2859 
2860 std::optional<StringRef>
2861 AMDGPUAsmParser::getGprCountSymbolName(RegisterKind RegKind) {
2862  switch (RegKind) {
2863  case IS_VGPR:
2864  return StringRef(".amdgcn.next_free_vgpr");
2865  case IS_SGPR:
2866  return StringRef(".amdgcn.next_free_sgpr");
2867  default:
2868  return std::nullopt;
2869  }
2870 }
2871 
2872 void AMDGPUAsmParser::initializeGprCountSymbol(RegisterKind RegKind) {
2873  auto SymbolName = getGprCountSymbolName(RegKind);
2874  assert(SymbolName && "initializing invalid register kind");
2875  MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(*SymbolName);
2876  Sym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(0, getContext()));
2877 }
2878 
2879 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::updateGprCountSymbols(RegisterKind RegKind,
2880  unsigned DwordRegIndex,
2881  unsigned RegWidth) {
2882  // Symbols are only defined for GCN targets
2883  if (AMDGPU::getIsaVersion(getSTI().getCPU()).Major < 6)
2884  return true;
2885 
2886  auto SymbolName = getGprCountSymbolName(RegKind);
2887  if (!SymbolName)
2888  return true;
2889  MCSymbol *Sym = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(*SymbolName);
2890 
2891  int64_t NewMax = DwordRegIndex + divideCeil(RegWidth, 32) - 1;
2892  int64_t OldCount;
2893 
2894  if (!Sym->isVariable())
2895  return !Error(getLoc(),
2896  ".amdgcn.next_free_{v,s}gpr symbols must be variable");
2897  if (!Sym->getVariableValue(false)->evaluateAsAbsolute(OldCount))
2898  return !Error(
2899  getLoc(),
2900  ".amdgcn.next_free_{v,s}gpr symbols must be absolute expressions");
2901 
2902  if (OldCount <= NewMax)
2903  Sym->setVariableValue(MCConstantExpr::create(NewMax + 1, getContext()));
2904 
2905  return true;
2906 }
2907 
2908 std::unique_ptr<AMDGPUOperand>
2909 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseRegister(bool RestoreOnFailure) {
2910  const auto &Tok = getToken();
2911  SMLoc StartLoc = Tok.getLoc();
2912  SMLoc EndLoc = Tok.getEndLoc();
2913  RegisterKind RegKind;
2914  unsigned Reg, RegNum, RegWidth;
2915 
2916  if (!ParseAMDGPURegister(RegKind, Reg, RegNum, RegWidth)) {
2917  return nullptr;
2918  }
2919  if (isHsaAbiVersion3AndAbove(&getSTI())) {
2920  if (!updateGprCountSymbols(RegKind, RegNum, RegWidth))
2921  return nullptr;
2922  } else
2923  KernelScope.usesRegister(RegKind, RegNum, RegWidth);
2924  return AMDGPUOperand::CreateReg(this, Reg, StartLoc, EndLoc);
2925 }
2926 
2927 OperandMatchResultTy
2928 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseImm(OperandVector &Operands, bool HasSP3AbsModifier) {
2929  // TODO: add syntactic sugar for 1/(2*PI)
2930 
2931  if (isRegister())
2932  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
2933  assert(!isModifier());
2934 
2935  const auto& Tok = getToken();
2936  const auto& NextTok = peekToken();
2937  bool IsReal = Tok.is(AsmToken::Real);
2938  SMLoc S = getLoc();
2939  bool Negate = false;
2940 
2941  if (!IsReal && Tok.is(AsmToken::Minus) && NextTok.is(AsmToken::Real)) {
2942  lex();
2943  IsReal = true;
2944  Negate = true;
2945  }
2946 
2947  if (IsReal) {
2948  // Floating-point expressions are not supported.
2949  // Can only allow floating-point literals with an
2950  // optional sign.
2951 
2952  StringRef Num = getTokenStr();
2953  lex();
2954 
2955  APFloat RealVal(APFloat::IEEEdouble());
2956  auto roundMode = APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven;
2957  if (errorToBool(RealVal.convertFromString(Num, roundMode).takeError())) {
2958  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
2959  }
2960  if (Negate)
2961  RealVal.changeSign();
2962 
2963  Operands.push_back(
2964  AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, RealVal.bitcastToAPInt().getZExtValue(), S,
2965  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyNone, true));
2966 
2967  return MatchOperand_Success;
2968 
2969  } else {
2970  int64_t IntVal;
2971  const MCExpr *Expr;
2972  SMLoc S = getLoc();
2973 
2974  if (HasSP3AbsModifier) {
2975  // This is a workaround for handling expressions
2976  // as arguments of SP3 'abs' modifier, for example:
2977  // |1.0|
2978  // |-1|
2979  // |1+x|
2980  // This syntax is not compatible with syntax of standard
2981  // MC expressions (due to the trailing '|').
2982  SMLoc EndLoc;
2983  if (getParser().parsePrimaryExpr(Expr, EndLoc, nullptr))
2984  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
2985  } else {
2986  if (Parser.parseExpression(Expr))
2987  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
2988  }
2989 
2990  if (Expr->evaluateAsAbsolute(IntVal)) {
2991  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, IntVal, S));
2992  } else {
2993  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateExpr(this, Expr, S));
2994  }
2995 
2996  return MatchOperand_Success;
2997  }
2998 
2999  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
3000 }
3001 
3002 OperandMatchResultTy
3003 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseReg(OperandVector &Operands) {
3004  if (!isRegister())
3005  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
3006 
3007  if (auto R = parseRegister()) {
3008  assert(R->isReg());
3009  Operands.push_back(std::move(R));
3010  return MatchOperand_Success;
3011  }
3012  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3013 }

3015 OperandMatchResultTy
3016 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseRegOrImm(OperandVector &Operands, bool HasSP3AbsMod) {
3017  auto res = parseReg(Operands);
3018  if (res != MatchOperand_NoMatch) {
3019  return res;
3020  } else if (isModifier()) {
3021  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
3022  } else {
3023  return parseImm(Operands, HasSP3AbsMod);
3024  }
3025 }

3029  if (Token.is(AsmToken::Identifier) && NextToken.is(AsmToken::LParen)) {
3030  const auto &str = Token.getString();
3031  return str == "abs" || str == "neg" || str == "sext";
3032  }
3033  return false;

3046 bool
3047 AMDGPUAsmParser::isRegOrOperandModifier(const AsmToken &Token, const AsmToken &NextToken) const {
3048  return isRegister(Token, NextToken) || isOperandModifier(Token, NextToken);
3049 }
3050 
3051 // Check if this is an operand modifier or an opcode modifier
3052 // which may look like an expression but it is not. We should
3053 // avoid parsing these modifiers as expressions. Currently
3054 // recognized sequences are:
3055 // |...|
3056 // abs(...)
3057 // neg(...)
3058 // sext(...)
3059 // -reg
3060 // -|...|
3061 // -abs(...)
3062 // name:...
3063 //
3064 bool
3065 AMDGPUAsmParser::isModifier() {
3066 
3067  AsmToken Tok = getToken();
3068  AsmToken NextToken[2];
3069  peekTokens(NextToken);
3070 
3071  return isOperandModifier(Tok, NextToken[0]) ||
3072  (Tok.is(AsmToken::Minus) && isRegOrOperandModifier(NextToken[0], NextToken[1])) ||
3073  isOpcodeModifierWithVal(Tok, NextToken[0]);
3074 }
3075 
3076 // Check if the current token is an SP3 'neg' modifier.
3077 // Currently this modifier is allowed in the following context:
3078 //
3079 // 1. Before a register, e.g. "-v0", "-v[...]" or "-[v0,v1]".
3080 // 2. Before an 'abs' modifier: -abs(...)
3081 // 3. Before an SP3 'abs' modifier: -|...|
3082 //
3083 // In all other cases "-" is handled as a part
3084 // of an expression that follows the sign.
3085 //
3086 // Note: When "-" is followed by an integer literal,
3087 // this is interpreted as integer negation rather
3088 // than a floating-point NEG modifier applied to N.
3089 // Beside being contr-intuitive, such use of floating-point
3090 // NEG modifier would have resulted in different meaning
3091 // of integer literals used with VOP1/2/C and VOP3,
3092 // for example:
3093 // v_exp_f32_e32 v5, -1 // VOP1: src0 = 0xFFFFFFFF
3094 // v_exp_f32_e64 v5, -1 // VOP3: src0 = 0x80000001
3095 // Negative fp literals with preceding "-" are
3096 // handled likewise for uniformity
3097 //
3098 bool
3099 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSP3NegModifier() {
3100 
3101  AsmToken NextToken[2];
3102  peekTokens(NextToken);
3103 
3104  if (isToken(AsmToken::Minus) &&
3105  (isRegister(NextToken[0], NextToken[1]) ||
3106  NextToken[0].is(AsmToken::Pipe) ||
3107  isId(NextToken[0], "abs"))) {
3108  lex();
3109  return true;
3110  }
3111 
3112  return false;
3113 }
3114 
3115 OperandMatchResultTy
3116 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseRegOrImmWithFPInputMods(OperandVector &Operands,
3117  bool AllowImm) {
3118  bool Neg, SP3Neg;
3119  bool Abs, SP3Abs;
3120  SMLoc Loc;
3121 
3122  // Disable ambiguous constructs like '--1' etc. Should use neg(-1) instead.
3123  if (isToken(AsmToken::Minus) && peekToken().is(AsmToken::Minus)) {
3124  Error(getLoc(), "invalid syntax, expected 'neg' modifier");
3125  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3126  }
3127 
3128  SP3Neg = parseSP3NegModifier();
3129 
3130  Loc = getLoc();
3131  Neg = trySkipId("neg");
3132  if (Neg && SP3Neg) {
3133  Error(Loc, "expected register or immediate");
3134  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3135  }
3136  if (Neg && !skipToken(AsmToken::LParen, "expected left paren after neg"))
3137  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3138 
3139  Abs = trySkipId("abs");
3140  if (Abs && !skipToken(AsmToken::LParen, "expected left paren after abs"))
3141  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3142 
3143  Loc = getLoc();
3144  SP3Abs = trySkipToken(AsmToken::Pipe);
3145  if (Abs && SP3Abs) {
3146  Error(Loc, "expected register or immediate");
3147  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3148  }
3149 
3150  OperandMatchResultTy Res;
3151  if (AllowImm) {
3152  Res = parseRegOrImm(Operands, SP3Abs);
3153  } else {
3154  Res = parseReg(Operands);
3155  }
3156  if (Res != MatchOperand_Success) {
3157  return (SP3Neg || Neg || SP3Abs || Abs)? MatchOperand_ParseFail : Res;
3158  }
3159 
3160  if (SP3Abs && !skipToken(AsmToken::Pipe, "expected vertical bar"))
3161  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3162  if (Abs && !skipToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected closing parentheses"))
3163  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3164  if (Neg && !skipToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected closing parentheses"))
3165  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3166 
3167  AMDGPUOperand::Modifiers Mods;
3168  Mods.Abs = Abs || SP3Abs;
3169  Mods.Neg = Neg || SP3Neg;
3170 
3171  if (Mods.hasFPModifiers()) {
3172  AMDGPUOperand &Op = static_cast<AMDGPUOperand &>(*Operands.back());
3173  if (Op.isExpr()) {
3174  Error(Op.getStartLoc(), "expected an absolute expression");
3175  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3176  }
3177  Op.setModifiers(Mods);
3178  }
3179  return MatchOperand_Success;
3180 }
3181 
3182 OperandMatchResultTy
3183 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseRegOrImmWithIntInputMods(OperandVector &Operands,
3184  bool AllowImm) {
3185  bool Sext = trySkipId("sext");
3186  if (Sext && !skipToken(AsmToken::LParen, "expected left paren after sext"))
3187  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3188 
3189  OperandMatchResultTy Res;
3190  if (AllowImm) {
3191  Res = parseRegOrImm(Operands);
3192  } else {
3193  Res = parseReg(Operands);
3194  }
3195  if (Res != MatchOperand_Success) {
3196  return Sext? MatchOperand_ParseFail : Res;
3197  }
3198 
3199  if (Sext && !skipToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected closing parentheses"))
3200  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3201 
3202  AMDGPUOperand::Modifiers Mods;
3203  Mods.Sext = Sext;
3204 
3205  if (Mods.hasIntModifiers()) {
3206  AMDGPUOperand &Op = static_cast<AMDGPUOperand &>(*Operands.back());
3207  if (Op.isExpr()) {
3208  Error(Op.getStartLoc(), "expected an absolute expression");
3209  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
3210  }
3211  Op.setModifiers(Mods);
3212  }
3213 
3214  return MatchOperand_Success;
3215 }

3222 OperandMatchResultTy

3230  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, 0, Loc,
3231  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOff, false));

3248 unsigned AMDGPUAsmParser::checkTargetMatchPredicate(MCInst &Inst) {
3249  uint64_t TSFlags = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode()).TSFlags;
3250 
3251  if ((getForcedEncodingSize() == 32 && (TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::VOP3)) ||
3252  (getForcedEncodingSize() == 64 && !(TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::VOP3)) ||
3253  (isForcedDPP() && !(TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::DPP)) ||
3254  (isForcedSDWA() && !(TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::SDWA)) )
3255  return Match_InvalidOperand;
3256 
3257  if ((TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::VOP3) &&
3258  (TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::VOPAsmPrefer32Bit) &&
3259  getForcedEncodingSize() != 64)
3260  return Match_PreferE32;
3261 
3262  if (Inst.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_MAC_F32_sdwa_vi ||
3263  Inst.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_MAC_F16_sdwa_vi) {
3264  // v_mac_f32/16 allow only dst_sel == DWORD;
3265  auto OpNum =
3266  AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Inst.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::dst_sel);
3267  const auto &Op = Inst.getOperand(OpNum);
3268  if (!Op.isImm() || Op.getImm() != AMDGPU::SDWA::SdwaSel::DWORD) {
3269  return Match_InvalidOperand;
3270  }
3271  }
3272 
3273  return Match_Success;
3274 }

3335 unsigned AMDGPUAsmParser::findImplicitSGPRReadInVOP(const MCInst &Inst) const {
3336  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
3337  for (MCPhysReg Reg : Desc.implicit_uses()) {
3338  switch (Reg) {
3339  case AMDGPU::FLAT_SCR:
3340  case AMDGPU::VCC:
3341  case AMDGPU::VCC_LO:
3342  case AMDGPU::VCC_HI:
3343  case AMDGPU::M0:
3344  return Reg;
3345  default:
3346  break;
3347  }
3348  }
3349  return AMDGPU::NoRegister;
3350 }
3351 
3352 // NB: This code is correct only when used to check constant
3353 // bus limitations because GFX7 support no f16 inline constants.
3354 // Note that there are no cases when a GFX7 opcode violates
3355 // constant bus limitations due to the use of an f16 constant.
3356 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::isInlineConstant(const MCInst &Inst,
3357  unsigned OpIdx) const {
3358  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
3359 
3360  if (!AMDGPU::isSISrcOperand(Desc, OpIdx) ||
3361  AMDGPU::isKImmOperand(Desc, OpIdx)) {
3362  return false;
3363  }
3364 
3365  const MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(OpIdx);
3366 
3367  int64_t Val = MO.getImm();
3368  auto OpSize = AMDGPU::getOperandSize(Desc, OpIdx);
3369 
3370  switch (OpSize) { // expected operand size
3371  case 8:
3372  return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral64(Val, hasInv2PiInlineImm());
3373  case 4:
3374  return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral32(Val, hasInv2PiInlineImm());
3375  case 2: {
3376  const unsigned OperandType = Desc.operands()[OpIdx].OperandType;
3377  if (OperandType == AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_INT16 ||
3378  OperandType == AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_INT16 ||
3379  OperandType == AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_INT16)
3380  return AMDGPU::isInlinableIntLiteral(Val);
3381 
3382  if (OperandType == AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2INT16 ||
3383  OperandType == AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_V2INT16 ||
3384  OperandType == AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2INT16)
3385  return AMDGPU::isInlinableIntLiteralV216(Val);
3386 
3387  if (OperandType == AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_C_V2FP16 ||
3388  OperandType == AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_INLINE_AC_V2FP16 ||
3389  OperandType == AMDGPU::OPERAND_REG_IMM_V2FP16)
3390  return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteralV216(Val, hasInv2PiInlineImm());
3391 
3392  return AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral16(Val, hasInv2PiInlineImm());
3393  }
3394  default:
3395  llvm_unreachable("invalid operand size");
3396  }
3397 }

3399 unsigned AMDGPUAsmParser::getConstantBusLimit(unsigned Opcode) const {
3400  if (!isGFX10Plus())
3401  return 1;
3402 
3403  switch (Opcode) {
3404  // 64-bit shift instructions can use only one scalar value input
3405  case AMDGPU::V_LSHLREV_B64_e64:
3406  case AMDGPU::V_LSHLREV_B64_gfx10:
3407  case AMDGPU::V_LSHLREV_B64_e64_gfx11:
3408  case AMDGPU::V_LSHRREV_B64_e64:
3409  case AMDGPU::V_LSHRREV_B64_gfx10:
3410  case AMDGPU::V_LSHRREV_B64_e64_gfx11:
3411  case AMDGPU::V_ASHRREV_I64_e64:
3412  case AMDGPU::V_ASHRREV_I64_gfx10:
3413  case AMDGPU::V_ASHRREV_I64_e64_gfx11:
3414  case AMDGPU::V_LSHL_B64_e64:
3415  case AMDGPU::V_LSHR_B64_e64:
3416  case AMDGPU::V_ASHR_I64_e64:
3417  return 1;
3418  default:
3419  return 2;
3420  }
3421 }
3422 
3423 constexpr unsigned MAX_SRC_OPERANDS_NUM = 6;
3424 using OperandIndices = SmallVector<int16_t, MAX_SRC_OPERANDS_NUM>;
3425 
3426 // Get regular operand indices in the same order as specified
3427 // in the instruction (but append mandatory literals to the end).
3428 static OperandIndices getSrcOperandIndices(unsigned Opcode,
3429  bool AddMandatoryLiterals = false) {
3430 
3431  int16_t ImmIdx =
3432  AddMandatoryLiterals ? getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, OpName::imm) : -1;
3433 
3434  if (isVOPD(Opcode)) {
3435  int16_t ImmDeferredIdx =
3436  AddMandatoryLiterals ? getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, OpName::immDeferred)
3437  : -1;
3438 
3439  return {getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, OpName::src0X),
3440  getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, OpName::vsrc1X),
3441  getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, OpName::src0Y),
3442  getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, OpName::vsrc1Y),
3443  ImmDeferredIdx,
3444  ImmIdx};
3445  }
3446 
3447  return {getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, OpName::src0),
3448  getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, OpName::src1),
3449  getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, OpName::src2), ImmIdx};
3450 }

3452 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::usesConstantBus(const MCInst &Inst, unsigned OpIdx) {
3453  const MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(OpIdx);
3454  if (MO.isImm()) {
3455  return !isInlineConstant(Inst, OpIdx);
3456  } else if (MO.isReg()) {
3457  auto Reg = MO.getReg();
3458  const MCRegisterInfo *TRI = getContext().getRegisterInfo();
3459  auto PReg = mc2PseudoReg(Reg);
3460  return isSGPR(PReg, TRI) && PReg != SGPR_NULL;
3461  } else {
3462  return true;
3463  }
3464 }
3465 
3466 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateConstantBusLimitations(
3467  const MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands) {
3468  const unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
3469  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opcode);
3470  unsigned LastSGPR = AMDGPU::NoRegister;
3471  unsigned ConstantBusUseCount = 0;
3472  unsigned NumLiterals = 0;
3473  unsigned LiteralSize;
3474 
3475  if (!(Desc.TSFlags &
3476  (SIInstrFlags::VOPC | SIInstrFlags::VOP1 | SIInstrFlags::VOP2 |
3477  SIInstrFlags::VOP3 | SIInstrFlags::VOP3P | SIInstrFlags::SDWA)) &&
3478  !isVOPD(Opcode))
3479  return true;
3480 
3481  // Check special imm operands (used by madmk, etc)
3482  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::imm)) {
3483  ++NumLiterals;
3484  LiteralSize = 4;
3485  }
3486 
3487  SmallDenseSet<unsigned> SGPRsUsed;
3488  unsigned SGPRUsed = findImplicitSGPRReadInVOP(Inst);
3489  if (SGPRUsed != AMDGPU::NoRegister) {
3490  SGPRsUsed.insert(SGPRUsed);
3491  ++ConstantBusUseCount;
3492  }
3493 
3494  OperandIndices OpIndices = getSrcOperandIndices(Opcode);
3495 
3496  for (int OpIdx : OpIndices) {
3497  if (OpIdx == -1)
3498  continue;
3499 
3500  const MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(OpIdx);
3501  if (usesConstantBus(Inst, OpIdx)) {
3502  if (MO.isReg()) {
3503  LastSGPR = mc2PseudoReg(MO.getReg());
3504  // Pairs of registers with a partial intersections like these
3505  // s0, s[0:1]
3506  // flat_scratch_lo, flat_scratch
3507  // flat_scratch_lo, flat_scratch_hi
3508  // are theoretically valid but they are disabled anyway.
3509  // Note that this code mimics SIInstrInfo::verifyInstruction
3510  if (SGPRsUsed.insert(LastSGPR).second) {
3511  ++ConstantBusUseCount;
3512  }
3513  } else { // Expression or a literal
3514 
3515  if (Desc.operands()[OpIdx].OperandType == MCOI::OPERAND_IMMEDIATE)
3516  continue; // special operand like VINTERP attr_chan
3517 
3518  // An instruction may use only one literal.
3519  // This has been validated on the previous step.
3520  // See validateVOPLiteral.
3521  // This literal may be used as more than one operand.
3522  // If all these operands are of the same size,
3523  // this literal counts as one scalar value.
3524  // Otherwise it counts as 2 scalar values.
3525  // See "GFX10 Shader Programming", section 3.6.2.3.
3526 
3527  unsigned Size = AMDGPU::getOperandSize(Desc, OpIdx);
3528  if (Size < 4)
3529  Size = 4;
3530 
3531  if (NumLiterals == 0) {
3532  NumLiterals = 1;
3533  LiteralSize = Size;
3534  } else if (LiteralSize != Size) {
3535  NumLiterals = 2;
3536  }
3537  }
3538  }
3539  }
3540  ConstantBusUseCount += NumLiterals;
3541 
3542  if (ConstantBusUseCount <= getConstantBusLimit(Opcode))
3543  return true;
3544 
3545  SMLoc LitLoc = getLitLoc(Operands);
3546  SMLoc RegLoc = getRegLoc(LastSGPR, Operands);
3547  SMLoc Loc = (LitLoc.getPointer() < RegLoc.getPointer()) ? RegLoc : LitLoc;
3548  Error(Loc, "invalid operand (violates constant bus restrictions)");
3549  return false;
3550 }
3551 
3552 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateVOPDRegBankConstraints(
3553  const MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands) {
3554 
3555  const unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
3556  if (!isVOPD(Opcode))
3557  return true;
3558 
3559  const MCRegisterInfo *TRI = getContext().getRegisterInfo();
3560 
3561  auto getVRegIdx = [&](unsigned, unsigned OperandIdx) {
3562  const MCOperand &Opr = Inst.getOperand(OperandIdx);
3563  return (Opr.isReg() && !isSGPR(mc2PseudoReg(Opr.getReg()), TRI))
3564  ? Opr.getReg()
3565  : MCRegister::NoRegister;
3566  };
3567 
3568  const auto &InstInfo = getVOPDInstInfo(Opcode, &MII);
3569  auto InvalidCompOprIdx = InstInfo.getInvalidCompOperandIndex(getVRegIdx);
3570  if (!InvalidCompOprIdx)
3571  return true;
3572 
3573  auto CompOprIdx = *InvalidCompOprIdx;
3574  auto ParsedIdx =
3575  std::max(InstInfo[VOPD::X].getIndexInParsedOperands(CompOprIdx),
3576  InstInfo[VOPD::Y].getIndexInParsedOperands(CompOprIdx));
3577  assert(ParsedIdx > 0 && ParsedIdx < Operands.size());
3578 
3579  auto Loc = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[ParsedIdx]).getStartLoc();
3580  if (CompOprIdx == VOPD::Component::DST) {
3581  Error(Loc, "one dst register must be even and the other odd");
3582  } else {
3583  auto CompSrcIdx = CompOprIdx - VOPD::Component::DST_NUM;
3584  Error(Loc, Twine("src") + Twine(CompSrcIdx) +
3585  " operands must use different VGPR banks");
3586  }
3587 
3588  return false;
3589 }

3591 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateIntClampSupported(const MCInst &Inst) {
3592 
3593  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
3594  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opc);
3595 
3596  if ((Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::IntClamp) != 0 && !hasIntClamp()) {
3597  int ClampIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::clamp);
3598  assert(ClampIdx != -1);
3599  return Inst.getOperand(ClampIdx).getImm() == 0;
3600  }
3601 
3602  return true;
3603 }
3604 
3605 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateMIMGDataSize(const MCInst &Inst,
3606  const SMLoc &IDLoc) {
3607 
3608  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
3609  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opc);
3610 
3611  if ((Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::MIMG) == 0)
3612  return true;
3613 
3614  int VDataIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::vdata);
3615  int DMaskIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::dmask);
3616  int TFEIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::tfe);
3617 
3618  assert(VDataIdx != -1);
3619 
3620  if ((DMaskIdx == -1 || TFEIdx == -1) && isGFX10_AEncoding()) // intersect_ray
3621  return true;
3622 
3623  unsigned VDataSize = AMDGPU::getRegOperandSize(getMRI(), Desc, VDataIdx);
3624  unsigned TFESize = (TFEIdx != -1 && Inst.getOperand(TFEIdx).getImm()) ? 1 : 0;
3625  unsigned DMask = Inst.getOperand(DMaskIdx).getImm() & 0xf;
3626  if (DMask == 0)
3627  DMask = 1;
3628 
3629  bool IsPackedD16 = false;
3630  unsigned DataSize =
3631  (Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::Gather4) ? 4 : llvm::popcount(DMask);
3632  if (hasPackedD16()) {
3633  int D16Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::d16);
3634  IsPackedD16 = D16Idx >= 0;
3635  if (IsPackedD16 && Inst.getOperand(D16Idx).getImm())
3636  DataSize = (DataSize + 1) / 2;
3637  }
3638 
3639  if ((VDataSize / 4) == DataSize + TFESize)
3640  return true;
3641 
3642  StringRef Modifiers;
3643  if (isGFX90A())
3644  Modifiers = IsPackedD16 ? "dmask and d16" : "dmask";
3645  else
3646  Modifiers = IsPackedD16 ? "dmask, d16 and tfe" : "dmask and tfe";
3647 
3648  Error(IDLoc, Twine("image data size does not match ") + Modifiers);
3649  return false;
3650 }
3651 
3652 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateMIMGAddrSize(const MCInst &Inst) {
3653  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
3654  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opc);
3655 
3656  if ((Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::MIMG) == 0 || !isGFX10Plus())
3657  return true;
3658 
3659  const AMDGPU::MIMGInfo *Info = AMDGPU::getMIMGInfo(Opc);
3660 
3661  const AMDGPU::MIMGBaseOpcodeInfo *BaseOpcode =
3662  AMDGPU::getMIMGBaseOpcodeInfo(Info->BaseOpcode);
3663  int VAddr0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr0);
3664  int SrsrcIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::srsrc);
3665  int DimIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::dim);
3666  int A16Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::a16);
3667 
3668  assert(VAddr0Idx != -1);
3669  assert(SrsrcIdx != -1);
3670  assert(SrsrcIdx > VAddr0Idx);
3671 
3672  if (DimIdx == -1)
3673  return true; // intersect_ray
3674 
3675  unsigned Dim = Inst.getOperand(DimIdx).getImm();
3676  const AMDGPU::MIMGDimInfo *DimInfo = AMDGPU::getMIMGDimInfoByEncoding(Dim);
3677  bool IsNSA = SrsrcIdx - VAddr0Idx > 1;
3678  unsigned ActualAddrSize =
3679  IsNSA ? SrsrcIdx - VAddr0Idx
3680  : AMDGPU::getRegOperandSize(getMRI(), Desc, VAddr0Idx) / 4;
3681  bool IsA16 = (A16Idx != -1 && Inst.getOperand(A16Idx).getImm());
3682 
3683  unsigned ExpectedAddrSize =
3684  AMDGPU::getAddrSizeMIMGOp(BaseOpcode, DimInfo, IsA16, hasG16());
3685 
3686  if (!IsNSA) {
3687  if (ExpectedAddrSize > 12)
3688  ExpectedAddrSize = 16;
3689 
3690  // Allow oversized 8 VGPR vaddr when only 5/6/7 VGPRs are required.
3691  // This provides backward compatibility for assembly created
3692  // before 160b/192b/224b types were directly supported.
3693  if (ActualAddrSize == 8 && (ExpectedAddrSize >= 5 && ExpectedAddrSize <= 7))
3694  return true;
3695  }
3696 
3697  return ActualAddrSize == ExpectedAddrSize;
3698 }
3699 
3700 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateMIMGAtomicDMask(const MCInst &Inst) {
3701 
3702  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
3703  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opc);
3704 
3705  if ((Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::MIMG) == 0)
3706  return true;
3707  if (!Desc.mayLoad() || !Desc.mayStore())
3708  return true; // Not atomic
3709 
3710  int DMaskIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::dmask);
3711  unsigned DMask = Inst.getOperand(DMaskIdx).getImm() & 0xf;
3712 
3713  // This is an incomplete check because image_atomic_cmpswap
3714  // may only use 0x3 and 0xf while other atomic operations
3715  // may use 0x1 and 0x3. However these limitations are
3716  // verified when we check that dmask matches dst size.
3717  return DMask == 0x1 || DMask == 0x3 || DMask == 0xf;
3718 }
3719 
3720 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateMIMGGatherDMask(const MCInst &Inst) {
3721 
3722  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
3723  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opc);
3724 
3725  if ((Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::Gather4) == 0)
3726  return true;
3727 
3728  int DMaskIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::dmask);
3729  unsigned DMask = Inst.getOperand(DMaskIdx).getImm() & 0xf;
3730 
3731  // GATHER4 instructions use dmask in a different fashion compared to
3732  // other MIMG instructions. The only useful DMASK values are
3733  // 1=red, 2=green, 4=blue, 8=alpha. (e.g. 1 returns
3734  // (red,red,red,red) etc.) The ISA document doesn't mention
3735  // this.
3736  return DMask == 0x1 || DMask == 0x2 || DMask == 0x4 || DMask == 0x8;
3737 }
3738 
3739 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateMIMGMSAA(const MCInst &Inst) {
3740  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
3741  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opc);
3742 
3743  if ((Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::MIMG) == 0)
3744  return true;
3745 
3746  const AMDGPU::MIMGInfo *Info = AMDGPU::getMIMGInfo(Opc);
3747  const AMDGPU::MIMGBaseOpcodeInfo *BaseOpcode =
3748  AMDGPU::getMIMGBaseOpcodeInfo(Info->BaseOpcode);
3749 
3750  if (!BaseOpcode->MSAA)
3751  return true;
3752 
3753  int DimIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::dim);
3754  assert(DimIdx != -1);
3755 
3756  unsigned Dim = Inst.getOperand(DimIdx).getImm();
3757  const AMDGPU::MIMGDimInfo *DimInfo = AMDGPU::getMIMGDimInfoByEncoding(Dim);
3758 
3759  return DimInfo->MSAA;
3760 }

3762 static bool IsMovrelsSDWAOpcode(const unsigned Opcode)
3763 {
3764  switch (Opcode) {
3765  case AMDGPU::V_MOVRELS_B32_sdwa_gfx10:
3766  case AMDGPU::V_MOVRELSD_B32_sdwa_gfx10:
3767  case AMDGPU::V_MOVRELSD_2_B32_sdwa_gfx10:
3768  return true;
3769  default:
3770  return false;
3771  }
3772 }
3773 
3774 // movrels* opcodes should only allow VGPRS as src0.
3775 // This is specified in .td description for vop1/vop3,
3776 // but sdwa is handled differently. See isSDWAOperand.
3777 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateMovrels(const MCInst &Inst,
3778  const OperandVector &Operands) {
3779 
3780  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
3781  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opc);
3782 
3783  if ((Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::SDWA) == 0 || !IsMovrelsSDWAOpcode(Opc))
3784  return true;
3785 
3786  const int Src0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src0);
3787  assert(Src0Idx != -1);
3788 
3789  SMLoc ErrLoc;
3790  const MCOperand &Src0 = Inst.getOperand(Src0Idx);
3791  if (Src0.isReg()) {
3792  auto Reg = mc2PseudoReg(Src0.getReg());
3793  const MCRegisterInfo *TRI = getContext().getRegisterInfo();
3794  if (!isSGPR(Reg, TRI))
3795  return true;
3796  ErrLoc = getRegLoc(Reg, Operands);
3797  } else {
3798  ErrLoc = getConstLoc(Operands);
3799  }
3800 
3801  Error(ErrLoc, "source operand must be a VGPR");
3802  return false;
3803 }

3805 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateMAIAccWrite(const MCInst &Inst,
3806  const OperandVector &Operands) {
3807 
3808  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
3809 
3810  if (Opc != AMDGPU::V_ACCVGPR_WRITE_B32_vi)
3811  return true;
3812 
3813  const int Src0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src0);
3814  assert(Src0Idx != -1);
3815 
3816  const MCOperand &Src0 = Inst.getOperand(Src0Idx);
3817  if (!Src0.isReg())
3818  return true;
3819 
3820  auto Reg = mc2PseudoReg(Src0.getReg());
3821  const MCRegisterInfo *TRI = getContext().getRegisterInfo();
3822  if (!isGFX90A() && isSGPR(Reg, TRI)) {
3823  Error(getRegLoc(Reg, Operands),
3824  "source operand must be either a VGPR or an inline constant");
3825  return false;
3826  }
3827 
3828  return true;
3829 }

3831 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateMAISrc2(const MCInst &Inst,
3832  const OperandVector &Operands) {
3833  unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
3834  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opcode);
3835 
3836  if (!(Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::IsMAI) ||
3837  !getFeatureBits()[FeatureMFMAInlineLiteralBug])
3838  return true;
3839 
3840  const int Src2Idx = getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, OpName::src2);
3841  if (Src2Idx == -1)
3842  return true;
3843 
3844  if (Inst.getOperand(Src2Idx).isImm() && isInlineConstant(Inst, Src2Idx)) {
3845  Error(getConstLoc(Operands),
3846  "inline constants are not allowed for this operand");
3847  return false;
3848  }
3849 
3850  return true;

3853 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateMFMA(const MCInst &Inst,
3854  const OperandVector &Operands) {
3855  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
3856  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opc);
3857 
3858  if ((Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::IsMAI) == 0)
3859  return true;
3860 
3861  const int Src2Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src2);
3862  if (Src2Idx == -1)
3863  return true;
3864 
3865  const MCOperand &Src2 = Inst.getOperand(Src2Idx);
3866  if (!Src2.isReg())
3867  return true;
3868 
3869  MCRegister Src2Reg = Src2.getReg();
3870  MCRegister DstReg = Inst.getOperand(0).getReg();
3871  if (Src2Reg == DstReg)
3872  return true;
3873 
3874  const MCRegisterInfo *TRI = getContext().getRegisterInfo();
3875  if (TRI->getRegClass(Desc.operands()[0].RegClass).getSizeInBits() <= 128)
3876  return true;
3877 
3878  if (TRI->regsOverlap(Src2Reg, DstReg)) {
3879  Error(getRegLoc(mc2PseudoReg(Src2Reg), Operands),
3880  "source 2 operand must not partially overlap with dst");
3881  return false;
3882  }
3883 
3884  return true;
3885 }

3903  AMDGPU::OpName::src2_modifiers,
3904  AMDGPU::OpName::src2_modifiers}) {

3906  .getImm() &
3907  SISrcMods::ABS) {
3908  return false;
