4046  case AMDGPU::V_PK_LSHLREV_B16_gfx10:
4047  case AMDGPU::V_PK_LSHLREV_B16_vi:
4048 
4049  case AMDGPU::V_PK_LSHRREV_B16:
4050  case AMDGPU::V_PK_LSHRREV_B16_gfx10:
4051  case AMDGPU::V_PK_LSHRREV_B16_vi:
4052  case AMDGPU::V_PK_ASHRREV_I16:
4053  case AMDGPU::V_PK_ASHRREV_I16_gfx10:
4054  case AMDGPU::V_PK_ASHRREV_I16_vi:
4055  return true;
4056  default:
4057  return false;
4058  }
4059 }
4060 
4061 std::optional<StringRef>
4062 AMDGPUAsmParser::validateLdsDirect(const MCInst &Inst) {
4063 
4064  using namespace SIInstrFlags;
4065  const unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
4066  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opcode);
4067 
4068  // lds_direct register is defined so that it can be used
4069  // with 9-bit operands only. Ignore encodings which do not accept these.
4070  const auto Enc = VOP1 | VOP2 | VOP3 | VOPC | VOP3P | SIInstrFlags::SDWA;
4071  if ((Desc.TSFlags & Enc) == 0)
4072  return std::nullopt;
4073 
4074  for (auto SrcName : {OpName::src0, OpName::src1, OpName::src2}) {
4075  auto SrcIdx = getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, SrcName);
4076  if (SrcIdx == -1)
4077  break;
4078  const auto &Src = Inst.getOperand(SrcIdx);
4079  if (Src.isReg() && Src.getReg() == LDS_DIRECT) {
4080 
4081  if (isGFX90A() || isGFX11Plus())
4082  return StringRef("lds_direct is not supported on this GPU");
4083 
4084  if (IsRevOpcode(Opcode) || (Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::SDWA))
4085  return StringRef("lds_direct cannot be used with this instruction");
4086 
4087  if (SrcName != OpName::src0)
4088  return StringRef("lds_direct may be used as src0 only");
4089  }
4090  }
4091 
4092  return std::nullopt;
4093 }
4094 
4095 SMLoc AMDGPUAsmParser::getFlatOffsetLoc(const OperandVector &Operands) const {
4096  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4097  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
4098  if (Op.isFlatOffset())
4099  return Op.getStartLoc();
4100  }
4101  return getLoc();
4102 }
4103 
4104 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateFlatOffset(const MCInst &Inst,
4105  const OperandVector &Operands) {
4106  uint64_t TSFlags = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode()).TSFlags;
4107  if ((TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::FLAT) == 0)
4108  return true;
4109 
4110  auto Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
4111  auto OpNum = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::offset);
4112  assert(OpNum != -1);
4113 
4114  const auto &Op = Inst.getOperand(OpNum);
4115  if (!hasFlatOffsets() && Op.getImm() != 0) {
4116  Error(getFlatOffsetLoc(Operands),
4117  "flat offset modifier is not supported on this GPU");
4118  return false;
4119  }
4120 
4121  // For FLAT segment the offset must be positive;
4122  // MSB is ignored and forced to zero.
4123  unsigned OffsetSize = AMDGPU::getNumFlatOffsetBits(getSTI());
4124  bool AllowNegative =
4125  TSFlags & (SIInstrFlags::FlatGlobal | SIInstrFlags::FlatScratch);
4126  if (!isIntN(OffsetSize, Op.getImm()) || (!AllowNegative && Op.getImm() < 0)) {
4127  Error(getFlatOffsetLoc(Operands),
4128  Twine("expected a ") +
4129  (AllowNegative ? Twine(OffsetSize) + "-bit signed offset"
4130  : Twine(OffsetSize - 1) + "-bit unsigned offset"));
4131  return false;
4132  }
4133 
4134  return true;
4135 }
4136 
4137 SMLoc AMDGPUAsmParser::getSMEMOffsetLoc(const OperandVector &Operands) const {
4138  // Start with second operand because SMEM Offset cannot be dst or src0.
4139  for (unsigned i = 2, e = Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4140  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
4141  if (Op.isSMEMOffset())
4142  return Op.getStartLoc();
4143  }
4144  return getLoc();
4145 }
4146 
4147 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateSMEMOffset(const MCInst &Inst,
4148  const OperandVector &Operands) {
4149  if (isCI() || isSI())
4150  return true;
4151 
4152  uint64_t TSFlags = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode()).TSFlags;
4153  if ((TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::SMRD) == 0)
4154  return true;
4155 
4156  auto Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
4157  auto OpNum = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::offset);
4158  if (OpNum == -1)
4159  return true;
4160 
4161  const auto &Op = Inst.getOperand(OpNum);
4162  if (!Op.isImm())
4163  return true;
4164 
4165  uint64_t Offset = Op.getImm();
4166  bool IsBuffer = AMDGPU::getSMEMIsBuffer(Opcode);
4167  if (AMDGPU::isLegalSMRDEncodedUnsignedOffset(getSTI(), Offset) ||
4168  AMDGPU::isLegalSMRDEncodedSignedOffset(getSTI(), Offset, IsBuffer))
4169  return true;
4170 
4171  Error(getSMEMOffsetLoc(Operands),
4172  (isVI() || IsBuffer) ? "expected a 20-bit unsigned offset" :
4173  "expected a 21-bit signed offset");
4174 
4175  return false;
4176 }
4177 
4178 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateSOPLiteral(const MCInst &Inst) const {
4179  unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
4180  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opcode);
4181  if (!(Desc.TSFlags & (SIInstrFlags::SOP2 | SIInstrFlags::SOPC)))
4182  return true;
4183 
4184  const int Src0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::src0);
4185  const int Src1Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::src1);
4186 
4187  const int OpIndices[] = { Src0Idx, Src1Idx };
4188 
4189  unsigned NumExprs = 0;
4190  unsigned NumLiterals = 0;
4191  uint32_t LiteralValue;
4192 
4193  for (int OpIdx : OpIndices) {
4194  if (OpIdx == -1) break;
4195 
4196  const MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(OpIdx);
4197  // Exclude special imm operands (like that used by s_set_gpr_idx_on)
4198  if (AMDGPU::isSISrcOperand(Desc, OpIdx)) {
4199  if (MO.isImm() && !isInlineConstant(Inst, OpIdx)) {
4200  uint32_t Value = static_cast<uint32_t>(MO.getImm());
4201  if (NumLiterals == 0 || LiteralValue != Value) {
4202  LiteralValue = Value;
4203  ++NumLiterals;
4204  }
4205  } else if (MO.isExpr()) {
4206  ++NumExprs;
4207  }
4208  }
4209  }
4210 
4211  return NumLiterals + NumExprs <= 1;
4212 }
4213 
4214 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateOpSel(const MCInst &Inst) {
4215  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
4216  if (isPermlane16(Opc)) {
4217  int OpSelIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::op_sel);
4218  unsigned OpSel = Inst.getOperand(OpSelIdx).getImm();
4219 
4220  if (OpSel & ~3)
4221  return false;
4222  }
4223 
4224  uint64_t TSFlags = MII.get(Opc).TSFlags;
4225 
4226  if (isGFX940() && (TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::IsDOT)) {
4227  int OpSelIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::op_sel);
4228  if (OpSelIdx != -1) {
4229  if (Inst.getOperand(OpSelIdx).getImm() != 0)
4230  return false;
4231  }
4232  int OpSelHiIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::op_sel_hi);
4233  if (OpSelHiIdx != -1) {
4234  if (Inst.getOperand(OpSelHiIdx).getImm() != -1)
4235  return false;
4236  }
4237  }
4238 
4239  // op_sel[0:1] must be 0 for v_dot2_bf16_bf16 and v_dot2_f16_f16 (VOP3 Dot).
4240  if (isGFX11Plus() && (TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::IsDOT) &&
4241  (TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::VOP3) && !(TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::VOP3P)) {
4242  int OpSelIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::op_sel);
4243  unsigned OpSel = Inst.getOperand(OpSelIdx).getImm();
4244  if (OpSel & 3)
4245  return false;
4246  }
4247 
4248  return true;
4249 }
4250 
4251 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateDPP(const MCInst &Inst,
4252  const OperandVector &Operands) {
4253  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
4254  int DppCtrlIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::dpp_ctrl);
4255  if (DppCtrlIdx < 0)
4256  return true;
4257  unsigned DppCtrl = Inst.getOperand(DppCtrlIdx).getImm();
4258 
4259  if (!AMDGPU::isLegal64BitDPPControl(DppCtrl)) {
4260  // DPP64 is supported for row_newbcast only.
4261  int Src0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src0);
4262  if (Src0Idx >= 0 &&
4263  getMRI()->getSubReg(Inst.getOperand(Src0Idx).getReg(), AMDGPU::sub1)) {
4264  SMLoc S = getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppCtrl, Operands);
4265  Error(S, "64 bit dpp only supports row_newbcast");
4266  return false;
4267  }
4268  }
4269 
4270  return true;
4271 }

4273 // Check if VCC register matches wavefront size
4274 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateVccOperand(unsigned Reg) const {
4275  auto FB = getFeatureBits();
4276  return (FB[AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize64] && Reg == AMDGPU::VCC) ||
4277  (FB[AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize32] && Reg == AMDGPU::VCC_LO);
4278 }
4279 
4280 // One unique literal can be used. VOP3 literal is only allowed in GFX10+
4281 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateVOPLiteral(const MCInst &Inst,
4282  const OperandVector &Operands) {
4283  unsigned Opcode = Inst.getOpcode();
4284  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opcode);
4285  bool HasMandatoryLiteral = getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, OpName::imm) != -1;
4286  if (!(Desc.TSFlags & (SIInstrFlags::VOP3 | SIInstrFlags::VOP3P)) &&
4287  !HasMandatoryLiteral && !isVOPD(Opcode))
4288  return true;
4289 
4290  OperandIndices OpIndices = getSrcOperandIndices(Opcode, HasMandatoryLiteral);
4291 
4292  unsigned NumExprs = 0;
4293  unsigned NumLiterals = 0;
4294  uint32_t LiteralValue;
4295 
4296  for (int OpIdx : OpIndices) {
4297  if (OpIdx == -1)
4298  continue;
4299 
4300  const MCOperand &MO = Inst.getOperand(OpIdx);
4301  if (!MO.isImm() && !MO.isExpr())
4302  continue;
4303  if (!isSISrcOperand(Desc, OpIdx))
4304  continue;
4305 
4306  if (MO.isImm() && !isInlineConstant(Inst, OpIdx)) {
4307  uint32_t Value = static_cast<uint32_t>(MO.getImm());
4308  if (NumLiterals == 0 || LiteralValue != Value) {
4309  LiteralValue = Value;
4310  ++NumLiterals;
4311  }
4312  } else if (MO.isExpr()) {
4313  ++NumExprs;
4314  }
4315  }
4316  NumLiterals += NumExprs;
4317 
4318  if (!NumLiterals)
4319  return true;
4320 
4321  if (!HasMandatoryLiteral && !getFeatureBits()[FeatureVOP3Literal]) {
4322  Error(getLitLoc(Operands), "literal operands are not supported");
4323  return false;
4324  }
4325 
4326  if (NumLiterals > 1) {
4327  Error(getLitLoc(Operands, true), "only one unique literal operand is allowed");
4328  return false;
4329  }
4330 
4331  return true;
4332 }
4333 
4334 // Returns -1 if not a register, 0 if VGPR and 1 if AGPR.
4335 static int IsAGPROperand(const MCInst &Inst, uint16_t NameIdx,
4336  const MCRegisterInfo *MRI) {
4337  int OpIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Inst.getOpcode(), NameIdx);
4338  if (OpIdx < 0)
4339  return -1;
4340 
4341  const MCOperand &Op = Inst.getOperand(OpIdx);
4342  if (!Op.isReg())
4343  return -1;
4344 
4345  unsigned Sub = MRI->getSubReg(Op.getReg(), AMDGPU::sub0);
4346  auto Reg = Sub ? Sub : Op.getReg();
4347  const MCRegisterClass &AGPR32 = MRI->getRegClass(AMDGPU::AGPR_32RegClassID);
4348  return AGPR32.contains(Reg) ? 1 : 0;
4349 }
4350 
4351 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateAGPRLdSt(const MCInst &Inst) const {
4352  uint64_t TSFlags = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode()).TSFlags;
4353  if ((TSFlags & (SIInstrFlags::FLAT | SIInstrFlags::MUBUF |
4354  SIInstrFlags::MTBUF | SIInstrFlags::MIMG |
4355  SIInstrFlags::DS)) == 0)
4356  return true;
4357 
4358  uint16_t DataNameIdx = (TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::DS) ? AMDGPU::OpName::data0
4359  : AMDGPU::OpName::vdata;
4360 
4361  const MCRegisterInfo *MRI = getMRI();
4362  int DstAreg = IsAGPROperand(Inst, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst, MRI);
4363  int DataAreg = IsAGPROperand(Inst, DataNameIdx, MRI);
4364 
4365  if ((TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::DS) && DataAreg >= 0) {
4366  int Data2Areg = IsAGPROperand(Inst, AMDGPU::OpName::data1, MRI);
4367  if (Data2Areg >= 0 && Data2Areg != DataAreg)
4368  return false;
4369  }
4370 
4371  auto FB = getFeatureBits();
4372  if (FB[AMDGPU::FeatureGFX90AInsts]) {
4373  if (DataAreg < 0 || DstAreg < 0)
4374  return true;
4375  return DstAreg == DataAreg;
4376  }
4377 
4378  return DstAreg < 1 && DataAreg < 1;
4379 }
4380 
4381 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateVGPRAlign(const MCInst &Inst) const {
4382  auto FB = getFeatureBits();
4383  if (!FB[AMDGPU::FeatureGFX90AInsts])
4384  return true;
4385 
4386  const MCRegisterInfo *MRI = getMRI();
4387  const MCRegisterClass &VGPR32 = MRI->getRegClass(AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClassID);
4388  const MCRegisterClass &AGPR32 = MRI->getRegClass(AMDGPU::AGPR_32RegClassID);
4389  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Inst.getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) {
4390  const MCOperand &Op = Inst.getOperand(I);
4391  if (!Op.isReg())
4392  continue;
4393 
4394  unsigned Sub = MRI->getSubReg(Op.getReg(), AMDGPU::sub0);
4395  if (!Sub)
4396  continue;
4397 
4398  if (VGPR32.contains(Sub) && ((Sub - AMDGPU::VGPR0) & 1))
4399  return false;
4400  if (AGPR32.contains(Sub) && ((Sub - AMDGPU::AGPR0) & 1))
4401  return false;
4402  }
4403 
4404  return true;
4405 }

4407 SMLoc AMDGPUAsmParser::getBLGPLoc(const OperandVector &Operands) const {
4408  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
4409  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
4410  if (Op.isBLGP())
4411  return Op.getStartLoc();
4412  }
4413  return SMLoc();
4414 }
4415 
4416 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateBLGP(const MCInst &Inst,
4417  const OperandVector &Operands) {
4418  unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
4419  int BlgpIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::blgp);
4420  if (BlgpIdx == -1)
4421  return true;
4422  SMLoc BLGPLoc = getBLGPLoc(Operands);
4423  if (!BLGPLoc.isValid())
4424  return true;
4425  bool IsNeg = StringRef(BLGPLoc.getPointer()).startswith("neg:");
4426  auto FB = getFeatureBits();
4427  bool UsesNeg = false;
4428  if (FB[AMDGPU::FeatureGFX940Insts]) {
4429  switch (Opc) {
4430  case AMDGPU::V_MFMA_F64_16X16X4F64_gfx940_acd:
4431  case AMDGPU::V_MFMA_F64_16X16X4F64_gfx940_vcd:
4432  case AMDGPU::V_MFMA_F64_4X4X4F64_gfx940_acd:
4433  case AMDGPU::V_MFMA_F64_4X4X4F64_gfx940_vcd:
4434  UsesNeg = true;
4435  }
4436  }
4437 
4438  if (IsNeg == UsesNeg)
4439  return true;
4440 
4441  Error(BLGPLoc,
4442  UsesNeg ? "invalid modifier: blgp is not supported"
4443  : "invalid modifier: neg is not supported");
4444 
4445  return false;
4446 }
4447 
4448 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateWaitCnt(const MCInst &Inst,
4449  const OperandVector &Operands) {
4450  if (!isGFX11Plus())
4451  return true;
4452 
4453  unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
4454  if (Opc != AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_EXPCNT_gfx11 &&
4455  Opc != AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_LGKMCNT_gfx11 &&
4456  Opc != AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_VMCNT_gfx11 &&
4457  Opc != AMDGPU::S_WAITCNT_VSCNT_gfx11)
4458  return true;
4459 
4460  int Src0Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::sdst);
4461  assert(Src0Idx >= 0 && Inst.getOperand(Src0Idx).isReg());
4462  auto Reg = mc2PseudoReg(Inst.getOperand(Src0Idx).getReg());
4463  if (Reg == AMDGPU::SGPR_NULL)
4464  return true;
4465 
4466  SMLoc RegLoc = getRegLoc(Reg, Operands);
4467  Error(RegLoc, "src0 must be null");
4468  return false;
4469 }

4471 // gfx90a has an undocumented limitation:
4472 // DS_GWS opcodes must use even aligned registers.
4473 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateGWS(const MCInst &Inst,
4474  const OperandVector &Operands) {
4475  if (!getFeatureBits()[AMDGPU::FeatureGFX90AInsts])
4476  return true;
4477 
4478  int Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
4479  if (Opc != AMDGPU::DS_GWS_INIT_vi && Opc != AMDGPU::DS_GWS_BARRIER_vi &&
4480  Opc != AMDGPU::DS_GWS_SEMA_BR_vi)
4481  return true;
4482 
4483  const MCRegisterInfo *MRI = getMRI();
4484  const MCRegisterClass &VGPR32 = MRI->getRegClass(AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClassID);
4485  int Data0Pos =
4486  AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Inst.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::data0);
4487  assert(Data0Pos != -1);
4488  auto Reg = Inst.getOperand(Data0Pos).getReg();
4489  auto RegIdx = Reg - (VGPR32.contains(Reg) ? AMDGPU::VGPR0 : AMDGPU::AGPR0);
4490  if (RegIdx & 1) {
4491  SMLoc RegLoc = getRegLoc(Reg, Operands);
4492  Error(RegLoc, "vgpr must be even aligned");
4493  return false;
4494  }
4495 
4496  return true;
4497 }
4498 
4499 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateCoherencyBits(const MCInst &Inst,
4500  const OperandVector &Operands,
4501  const SMLoc &IDLoc) {
4502  int CPolPos = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Inst.getOpcode(),
4503  AMDGPU::OpName::cpol);
4504  if (CPolPos == -1)
4505  return true;
4506 
4507  unsigned CPol = Inst.getOperand(CPolPos).getImm();
4508 
4509  uint64_t TSFlags = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode()).TSFlags;
4510  if (TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::SMRD) {
4511  if (CPol && (isSI() || isCI())) {
4512  SMLoc S = getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyCPol, Operands);
4513  Error(S, "cache policy is not supported for SMRD instructions");
4514  return false;
4515  }
4516  if (CPol & ~(AMDGPU::CPol::GLC | AMDGPU::CPol::DLC)) {
4517  Error(IDLoc, "invalid cache policy for SMEM instruction");
4518  return false;
4519  }
4520  }
4521 
4522  if (isGFX90A() && !isGFX940() && (CPol & CPol::SCC)) {
4523  SMLoc S = getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyCPol, Operands);
4524  StringRef CStr(S.getPointer());
4525  S = SMLoc::getFromPointer(&CStr.data()[CStr.find("scc")]);
4526  Error(S, "scc is not supported on this GPU");
4527  return false;
4528  }
4529 
4530  if (!(TSFlags & (SIInstrFlags::IsAtomicNoRet | SIInstrFlags::IsAtomicRet)))
4531  return true;
4532 
4533  if (TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::IsAtomicRet) {
4534  if (!(TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::MIMG) && !(CPol & CPol::GLC)) {
4535  Error(IDLoc, isGFX940() ? "instruction must use sc0"
4536  : "instruction must use glc");
4537  return false;
4538  }
4539  } else {
4540  if (CPol & CPol::GLC) {
4541  SMLoc S = getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyCPol, Operands);
4542  StringRef CStr(S.getPointer());
4543  S = SMLoc::getFromPointer(
4544  &CStr.data()[CStr.find(isGFX940() ? "sc0" : "glc")]);
4545  Error(S, isGFX940() ? "instruction must not use sc0"
4546  : "instruction must not use glc");
4547  return false;
4548  }
4549  }
4550 
4551  return true;
4552 }
4553 
4554 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateExeczVcczOperands(const OperandVector &Operands) {
4555  if (!isGFX11Plus())
4556  return true;
4557  for (auto &Operand : Operands) {
4558  if (!Operand->isReg())
4559  continue;
4560  unsigned Reg = Operand->getReg();
4561  if (Reg == SRC_EXECZ || Reg == SRC_VCCZ) {
4562  Error(getRegLoc(Reg, Operands),
4563  "execz and vccz are not supported on this GPU");
4564  return false;
4565  }
4566  }
4567  return true;
4568 }
4569 
4570 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateTFE(const MCInst &Inst,
4571  const OperandVector &Operands) {
4572  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
4573  if (Desc.mayStore() &&
4574  (Desc.TSFlags & (SIInstrFlags::MUBUF | SIInstrFlags::MTBUF))) {
4575  SMLoc Loc = getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyTFE, Operands);
4576  if (Loc != getInstLoc(Operands)) {
4577  Error(Loc, "TFE modifier has no meaning for store instructions");
4578  return false;
4579  }
4580  }
4581 
4582  return true;
4583 }
4584 
4585 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::validateInstruction(const MCInst &Inst,
4586  const SMLoc &IDLoc,
4587  const OperandVector &Operands) {
4588  if (auto ErrMsg = validateLdsDirect(Inst)) {
4589  Error(getRegLoc(LDS_DIRECT, Operands), *ErrMsg);
4590  return false;
4591  }
4592  if (!validateSOPLiteral(Inst)) {
4593  Error(getLitLoc(Operands),
4594  "only one unique literal operand is allowed");
4595  return false;
4596  }
4597  if (!validateVOPLiteral(Inst, Operands)) {
4598  return false;
4599  }
4600  if (!validateConstantBusLimitations(Inst, Operands)) {
4601  return false;
4602  }
4603  if (!validateVOPDRegBankConstraints(Inst, Operands)) {
4604  return false;
4605  }
4606  if (!validateIntClampSupported(Inst)) {
4607  Error(getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyClampSI, Operands),
4608  "integer clamping is not supported on this GPU");
4609  return false;
4610  }
4611  if (!validateOpSel(Inst)) {
4612  Error(getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOpSel, Operands),
4613  "invalid op_sel operand");
4614  return false;
4615  }
4616  if (!validateDPP(Inst, Operands)) {
4617  return false;
4618  }
4619  // For MUBUF/MTBUF d16 is a part of opcode, so there is nothing to validate.
4620  if (!validateMIMGD16(Inst)) {
4621  Error(getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyD16, Operands),
4622  "d16 modifier is not supported on this GPU");
4623  return false;
4624  }
4625  if (!validateMIMGMSAA(Inst)) {
4626  Error(getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDim, Operands),
4627  "invalid dim; must be MSAA type");
4628  return false;
4629  }
4630  if (!validateMIMGDataSize(Inst, IDLoc)) {
4631  return false;
4632  }
4633  if (!validateMIMGAddrSize(Inst)) {
4634  Error(IDLoc,
4635  "image address size does not match dim and a16");
4636  return false;
4637  }
4638  if (!validateMIMGAtomicDMask(Inst)) {
4639  Error(getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDMask, Operands),
4640  "invalid atomic image dmask");
4641  return false;
4642  }
4643  if (!validateMIMGGatherDMask(Inst)) {
4644  Error(getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDMask, Operands),
4645  "invalid image_gather dmask: only one bit must be set");
4646  return false;
4647  }
4648  if (!validateMovrels(Inst, Operands)) {
4649  return false;
4650  }
4651  if (!validateFlatOffset(Inst, Operands)) {
4652  return false;
4653  }
4654  if (!validateSMEMOffset(Inst, Operands)) {
4655  return false;
4656  }
4657  if (!validateMAIAccWrite(Inst, Operands)) {
4658  return false;
4659  }
4660  if (!validateMAISrc2(Inst, Operands)) {
4661  return false;
4662  }
4663  if (!validateMFMA(Inst, Operands)) {
4664  return false;
4665  }
4666  if (!validateCoherencyBits(Inst, Operands, IDLoc)) {
4667  return false;
4668  }
4669 
4670  if (!validateAGPRLdSt(Inst)) {
4671  Error(IDLoc, getFeatureBits()[AMDGPU::FeatureGFX90AInsts]
4672  ? "invalid register class: data and dst should be all VGPR or AGPR"
4673  : "invalid register class: agpr loads and stores not supported on this GPU"
4674  );
4675  return false;
4676  }
4677  if (!validateVGPRAlign(Inst)) {
4678  Error(IDLoc,
4679  "invalid register class: vgpr tuples must be 64 bit aligned");
4680  return false;
4681  }
4682  if (!validateGWS(Inst, Operands)) {
4683  return false;
4684  }
4685 
4686  if (!validateBLGP(Inst, Operands)) {
4687  return false;
4688  }
4689 
4690  if (!validateDivScale(Inst)) {
4691  Error(IDLoc, "ABS not allowed in VOP3B instructions");
4692  return false;
4693  }
4694  if (!validateWaitCnt(Inst, Operands)) {
4695  return false;
4696  }
4697  if (!validateExeczVcczOperands(Operands)) {
4698  return false;
4699  }
4700  if (!validateTFE(Inst, Operands)) {
4701  return false;
4702  }
4703 
4704  return true;
4705 }
4706 
4707 static std::string AMDGPUMnemonicSpellCheck(StringRef S,
4708  const FeatureBitset &FBS,
4709  unsigned VariantID = 0);
4710 
4711 static bool AMDGPUCheckMnemonic(StringRef Mnemonic,
4712  const FeatureBitset &AvailableFeatures,
4713  unsigned VariantID);
4714 
4715 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::isSupportedMnemo(StringRef Mnemo,
4716  const FeatureBitset &FBS) {
4717  return isSupportedMnemo(Mnemo, FBS, getAllVariants());
4718 }
4719 
4720 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::isSupportedMnemo(StringRef Mnemo,
4721  const FeatureBitset &FBS,
4722  ArrayRef<unsigned> Variants) {
4723  for (auto Variant : Variants) {
4724  if (AMDGPUCheckMnemonic(Mnemo, FBS, Variant))
4725  return true;
4726  }
4727 
4728  return false;
4729 }
4730 
4731 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::checkUnsupportedInstruction(StringRef Mnemo,
4732  const SMLoc &IDLoc) {
4733  FeatureBitset FBS = ComputeAvailableFeatures(getFeatureBits());
4734 
4735  // Check if requested instruction variant is supported.
4736  if (isSupportedMnemo(Mnemo, FBS, getMatchedVariants()))
4737  return false;
4738 
4739  // This instruction is not supported.
4740  // Clear any other pending errors because they are no longer relevant.
4741  getParser().clearPendingErrors();
4742 
4743  // Requested instruction variant is not supported.
4744  // Check if any other variants are supported.
4745  StringRef VariantName = getMatchedVariantName();
4746  if (!VariantName.empty() && isSupportedMnemo(Mnemo, FBS)) {
4747  return Error(IDLoc,
4748  Twine(VariantName,
4749  " variant of this instruction is not supported"));
4750  }
4751 
4752  // Check if this instruction may be used with a different wavesize.
4753  if (isGFX10Plus() && getFeatureBits()[AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize64] &&
4754  !getFeatureBits()[AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize32]) {
4755 
4756  FeatureBitset FeaturesWS32 = getFeatureBits();
4757  FeaturesWS32.flip(AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize64)
4758  .flip(AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize32);
4759  FeatureBitset AvailableFeaturesWS32 =
4760  ComputeAvailableFeatures(FeaturesWS32);
4761 
4762  if (isSupportedMnemo(Mnemo, AvailableFeaturesWS32, getMatchedVariants()))
4763  return Error(IDLoc, "instruction requires wavesize=32");
4764  }
4765 
4766  // Finally check if this instruction is supported on any other GPU.
4767  if (isSupportedMnemo(Mnemo, FeatureBitset().set())) {
4768  return Error(IDLoc, "instruction not supported on this GPU");
4769  }
4770 
4771  // Instruction not supported on any GPU. Probably a typo.
4772  std::string Suggestion = AMDGPUMnemonicSpellCheck(Mnemo, FBS);
4773  return Error(IDLoc, "invalid instruction" + Suggestion);
4774 }
4775 
4776 static bool isInvalidVOPDY(const OperandVector &Operands,
4777  uint64_t InvalidOprIdx) {
4778  assert(InvalidOprIdx < Operands.size());
4779  const auto &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[InvalidOprIdx]);
4780  if (Op.isToken() && InvalidOprIdx > 1) {
4781  const auto &PrevOp = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[InvalidOprIdx - 1]);
4782  return PrevOp.isToken() && PrevOp.getToken() == "::";
4783  }
4784  return false;
4785 }
4786 
4787 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::MatchAndEmitInstruction(SMLoc IDLoc, unsigned &Opcode,
4788  OperandVector &Operands,
4789  MCStreamer &Out,
4790  uint64_t &ErrorInfo,
4791  bool MatchingInlineAsm) {
4792  MCInst Inst;
4793  unsigned Result = Match_Success;
4794  for (auto Variant : getMatchedVariants()) {
4795  uint64_t EI;
4796  auto R = MatchInstructionImpl(Operands, Inst, EI, MatchingInlineAsm,
4797  Variant);
4798  // We order match statuses from least to most specific. We use most specific
4799  // status as resulting
4800  // Match_MnemonicFail < Match_InvalidOperand < Match_MissingFeature < Match_PreferE32
4801  if ((R == Match_Success) ||
4802  (R == Match_PreferE32) ||
4803  (R == Match_MissingFeature && Result != Match_PreferE32) ||
4804  (R == Match_InvalidOperand && Result != Match_MissingFeature
4805  && Result != Match_PreferE32) ||
4806  (R == Match_MnemonicFail && Result != Match_InvalidOperand
4807  && Result != Match_MissingFeature
4808  && Result != Match_PreferE32)) {
4809  Result = R;
4810  ErrorInfo = EI;
4811  }
4812  if (R == Match_Success)
4813  break;
4814  }
4815 
4816  if (Result == Match_Success) {
4817  if (!validateInstruction(Inst, IDLoc, Operands)) {
4818  return true;
4819  }
4820  Inst.setLoc(IDLoc);
4821  Out.emitInstruction(Inst, getSTI());
4822  return false;
4823  }
4824 
4825  StringRef Mnemo = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[0]).getToken();
4826  if (checkUnsupportedInstruction(Mnemo, IDLoc)) {
4827  return true;
4828  }
4829 
4830  switch (Result) {
4831  default: break;
4832  case Match_MissingFeature:
4833  // It has been verified that the specified instruction
4834  // mnemonic is valid. A match was found but it requires
4835  // features which are not supported on this GPU.
4836  return Error(IDLoc, "operands are not valid for this GPU or mode");
4837 
4838  case Match_InvalidOperand: {
4839  SMLoc ErrorLoc = IDLoc;
4840  if (ErrorInfo != ~0ULL) {
4841  if (ErrorInfo >= Operands.size()) {
4842  return Error(IDLoc, "too few operands for instruction");
4843  }
4844  ErrorLoc = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[ErrorInfo]).getStartLoc();
4845  if (ErrorLoc == SMLoc())
4846  ErrorLoc = IDLoc;
4847 
4848  if (isInvalidVOPDY(Operands, ErrorInfo))
4849  return Error(ErrorLoc, "invalid VOPDY instruction");
4850  }
4851  return Error(ErrorLoc, "invalid operand for instruction");
4852  }
4853 
4854  case Match_PreferE32:
4855  return Error(IDLoc, "internal error: instruction without _e64 suffix "
4856  "should be encoded as e32");
4857  case Match_MnemonicFail:
4858  llvm_unreachable("Invalid instructions should have been handled already");
4859  }
4860  llvm_unreachable("Implement any new match types added!");
4861 }
4862 
4863 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseAsAbsoluteExpression(uint32_t &Ret) {
4864  int64_t Tmp = -1;
4865  if (!isToken(AsmToken::Integer) && !isToken(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
4866  return true;
4867  }
4868  if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(Tmp)) {
4869  return true;
4870  }
4871  Ret = static_cast<uint32_t>(Tmp);
4872  return false;
4873 }
4874 
4875 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectiveMajorMinor(uint32_t &Major,
4876  uint32_t &Minor) {
4877  if (ParseAsAbsoluteExpression(Major))
4878  return TokError("invalid major version");
4879 
4880  if (!trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma))
4881  return TokError("minor version number required, comma expected");
4882 
4883  if (ParseAsAbsoluteExpression(Minor))
4884  return TokError("invalid minor version");
4885 
4886  return false;
4887 }

4889 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectiveAMDGCNTarget() {
4890  if (getSTI().getTargetTriple().getArch() != Triple::amdgcn)
4891  return TokError("directive only supported for amdgcn architecture");
4892 
4893  std::string TargetIDDirective;
4894  SMLoc TargetStart = getTok().getLoc();
4895  if (getParser().parseEscapedString(TargetIDDirective))
4896  return true;
4897 
4898  SMRange TargetRange = SMRange(TargetStart, getTok().getLoc());
4899  if (getTargetStreamer().getTargetID()->toString() != TargetIDDirective)
4900  return getParser().Error(TargetRange.Start,
4901  (Twine(".amdgcn_target directive's target id ") +
4902  Twine(TargetIDDirective) +
4903  Twine(" does not match the specified target id ") +
4904  Twine(getTargetStreamer().getTargetID()->toString())).str());
4905 
4906  return false;
4907 }

4909 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::OutOfRangeError(SMRange Range) {
4910  return Error(Range.Start, "value out of range", Range);
4911 }
4912 
4913 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::calculateGPRBlocks(
4914  const FeatureBitset &Features, bool VCCUsed, bool FlatScrUsed,
4915  bool XNACKUsed, std::optional<bool> EnableWavefrontSize32,
4916  unsigned NextFreeVGPR, SMRange VGPRRange, unsigned NextFreeSGPR,
4917  SMRange SGPRRange, unsigned &VGPRBlocks, unsigned &SGPRBlocks) {
4918  // TODO(scott.linder): These calculations are duplicated from
4919  // AMDGPUAsmPrinter::getSIProgramInfo and could be unified.
4920  IsaVersion Version = getIsaVersion(getSTI().getCPU());
4921 
4922  unsigned NumVGPRs = NextFreeVGPR;
4923  unsigned NumSGPRs = NextFreeSGPR;
4924 
4925  if (Version.Major >= 10)
4926  NumSGPRs = 0;
4927  else {
4928  unsigned MaxAddressableNumSGPRs =
4929  IsaInfo::getAddressableNumSGPRs(&getSTI());
4930 
4931  if (Version.Major >= 8 && !Features.test(FeatureSGPRInitBug) &&
4932  NumSGPRs > MaxAddressableNumSGPRs)
4933  return OutOfRangeError(SGPRRange);
4934 
4935  NumSGPRs +=
4936  IsaInfo::getNumExtraSGPRs(&getSTI(), VCCUsed, FlatScrUsed, XNACKUsed);
4937 
4938  if ((Version.Major <= 7 || Features.test(FeatureSGPRInitBug)) &&
4939  NumSGPRs > MaxAddressableNumSGPRs)
4940  return OutOfRangeError(SGPRRange);
4941 
4942  if (Features.test(FeatureSGPRInitBug))
4943  NumSGPRs = IsaInfo::FIXED_NUM_SGPRS_FOR_INIT_BUG;
4944  }
4945 
4946  VGPRBlocks =
4947  IsaInfo::getNumVGPRBlocks(&getSTI(), NumVGPRs, EnableWavefrontSize32);
4948  SGPRBlocks = IsaInfo::getNumSGPRBlocks(&getSTI(), NumSGPRs);
4949 
4950  return false;
4951 }
4952 
4953 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectiveAMDHSAKernel() {
4954  if (getSTI().getTargetTriple().getArch() != Triple::amdgcn)
4955  return TokError("directive only supported for amdgcn architecture");
4956 
4957  if (getSTI().getTargetTriple().getOS() != Triple::AMDHSA)
4958  return TokError("directive only supported for amdhsa OS");
4959 
4960  StringRef KernelName;
4961  if (getParser().parseIdentifier(KernelName))
4962  return true;
4963 
4964  kernel_descriptor_t KD = getDefaultAmdhsaKernelDescriptor(&getSTI());
4965 
4966  StringSet<> Seen;
4967 
4968  IsaVersion IVersion = getIsaVersion(getSTI().getCPU());
4969 
4970  SMRange VGPRRange;
4971  uint64_t NextFreeVGPR = 0;
4972  uint64_t AccumOffset = 0;
4973  uint64_t SharedVGPRCount = 0;
4974  SMRange SGPRRange;
4975  uint64_t NextFreeSGPR = 0;
4976 
4977  // Count the number of user SGPRs implied from the enabled feature bits.
4978  unsigned ImpliedUserSGPRCount = 0;
4979 
4980  // Track if the asm explicitly contains the directive for the user SGPR
4981  // count.
4982  std::optional<unsigned> ExplicitUserSGPRCount;
4983  bool ReserveVCC = true;
4984  bool ReserveFlatScr = true;
4985  std::optional<bool> EnableWavefrontSize32;
4986 
4987  while (true) {
4988  while (trySkipToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement));
4989 
4990  StringRef ID;
4991  SMRange IDRange = getTok().getLocRange();
4992  if (!parseId(ID, "expected .amdhsa_ directive or .end_amdhsa_kernel"))
4993  return true;
4994 
4995  if (ID == ".end_amdhsa_kernel")
4996  break;
4997 
4998  if (!Seen.insert(ID).second)
4999  return TokError(".amdhsa_ directives cannot be repeated");
5000 
5001  SMLoc ValStart = getLoc();
5002  int64_t IVal;
5003  if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(IVal))
5004  return true;
5005  SMLoc ValEnd = getLoc();
5006  SMRange ValRange = SMRange(ValStart, ValEnd);
5007 
5008  if (IVal < 0)
5009  return OutOfRangeError(ValRange);
5010 
5011  uint64_t Val = IVal;
5012 
5013 #define PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(FIELD, ENTRY, VALUE, RANGE) \
5014  if (!isUInt<ENTRY##_WIDTH>(VALUE)) \
5015  return OutOfRangeError(RANGE); \
5016  AMDHSA_BITS_SET(FIELD, ENTRY, VALUE);
5017 
5018  if (ID == ".amdhsa_group_segment_fixed_size") {
5019  if (!isUInt<sizeof(KD.group_segment_fixed_size) * CHAR_BIT>(Val))
5020  return OutOfRangeError(ValRange);
5021  KD.group_segment_fixed_size = Val;
5022  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_private_segment_fixed_size") {
5023  if (!isUInt<sizeof(KD.private_segment_fixed_size) * CHAR_BIT>(Val))
5024  return OutOfRangeError(ValRange);
5025  KD.private_segment_fixed_size = Val;
5026  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_kernarg_size") {
5027  if (!isUInt<sizeof(KD.kernarg_size) * CHAR_BIT>(Val))
5028  return OutOfRangeError(ValRange);
5029  KD.kernarg_size = Val;
5030  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_user_sgpr_count") {
5031  ExplicitUserSGPRCount = Val;
5032  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_user_sgpr_private_segment_buffer") {
5033  if (hasArchitectedFlatScratch())
5034  return Error(IDRange.Start,
5035  "directive is not supported with architected flat scratch",
5036  IDRange);
5037  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.kernel_code_properties,
5038  KERNEL_CODE_PROPERTY_ENABLE_SGPR_PRIVATE_SEGMENT_BUFFER,
5039  Val, ValRange);
5040  if (Val)
5041  ImpliedUserSGPRCount += 4;
5042  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_user_sgpr_dispatch_ptr") {
5043  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.kernel_code_properties,
5044  KERNEL_CODE_PROPERTY_ENABLE_SGPR_DISPATCH_PTR, Val,
5045  ValRange);
5046  if (Val)
5047  ImpliedUserSGPRCount += 2;
5048  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_user_sgpr_queue_ptr") {
5049  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.kernel_code_properties,
5050  KERNEL_CODE_PROPERTY_ENABLE_SGPR_QUEUE_PTR, Val,
5051  ValRange);
5052  if (Val)
5053  ImpliedUserSGPRCount += 2;
5054  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_user_sgpr_kernarg_segment_ptr") {
5055  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.kernel_code_properties,
5056  KERNEL_CODE_PROPERTY_ENABLE_SGPR_KERNARG_SEGMENT_PTR,
5057  Val, ValRange);
5058  if (Val)
5059  ImpliedUserSGPRCount += 2;
5060  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_user_sgpr_dispatch_id") {
5061  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.kernel_code_properties,
5062  KERNEL_CODE_PROPERTY_ENABLE_SGPR_DISPATCH_ID, Val,
5063  ValRange);
5064  if (Val)
5065  ImpliedUserSGPRCount += 2;
5066  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_user_sgpr_flat_scratch_init") {
5067  if (hasArchitectedFlatScratch())
5068  return Error(IDRange.Start,
5069  "directive is not supported with architected flat scratch",
5070  IDRange);
5071  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.kernel_code_properties,
5072  KERNEL_CODE_PROPERTY_ENABLE_SGPR_FLAT_SCRATCH_INIT, Val,
5073  ValRange);
5074  if (Val)
5075  ImpliedUserSGPRCount += 2;
5076  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_user_sgpr_private_segment_size") {
5077  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.kernel_code_properties,
5078  KERNEL_CODE_PROPERTY_ENABLE_SGPR_PRIVATE_SEGMENT_SIZE,
5079  Val, ValRange);
5080  if (Val)
5081  ImpliedUserSGPRCount += 1;
5082  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_wavefront_size32") {
5083  if (IVersion.Major < 10)
5084  return Error(IDRange.Start, "directive requires gfx10+", IDRange);
5085  EnableWavefrontSize32 = Val;
5086  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.kernel_code_properties,
5087  KERNEL_CODE_PROPERTY_ENABLE_WAVEFRONT_SIZE32,
5088  Val, ValRange);
5089  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_uses_dynamic_stack") {
5090  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.kernel_code_properties,
5091  KERNEL_CODE_PROPERTY_USES_DYNAMIC_STACK, Val, ValRange);
5092  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_system_sgpr_private_segment_wavefront_offset") {
5093  if (hasArchitectedFlatScratch())
5094  return Error(IDRange.Start,
5095  "directive is not supported with architected flat scratch",
5096  IDRange);
5097  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5098  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_PRIVATE_SEGMENT, Val, ValRange);
5099  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_enable_private_segment") {
5100  if (!hasArchitectedFlatScratch())
5101  return Error(
5102  IDRange.Start,
5103  "directive is not supported without architected flat scratch",
5104  IDRange);
5105  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5106  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_PRIVATE_SEGMENT, Val, ValRange);
5107  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_system_sgpr_workgroup_id_x") {
5108  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5109  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_SGPR_WORKGROUP_ID_X, Val,
5110  ValRange);
5111  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_system_sgpr_workgroup_id_y") {
5112  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5113  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_SGPR_WORKGROUP_ID_Y, Val,
5114  ValRange);
5115  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_system_sgpr_workgroup_id_z") {
5116  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5117  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_SGPR_WORKGROUP_ID_Z, Val,
5118  ValRange);
5119  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_system_sgpr_workgroup_info") {
5120  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5121  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_SGPR_WORKGROUP_INFO, Val,
5122  ValRange);
5123  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_system_vgpr_workitem_id") {
5124  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5125  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_VGPR_WORKITEM_ID, Val,
5126  ValRange);
5127  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_next_free_vgpr") {
5128  VGPRRange = ValRange;
5129  NextFreeVGPR = Val;
5130  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_next_free_sgpr") {
5131  SGPRRange = ValRange;
5132  NextFreeSGPR = Val;
5133  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_accum_offset") {
5134  if (!isGFX90A())
5135  return Error(IDRange.Start, "directive requires gfx90a+", IDRange);
5136  AccumOffset = Val;
5137  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_reserve_vcc") {
5138  if (!isUInt<1>(Val))
5139  return OutOfRangeError(ValRange);
5140  ReserveVCC = Val;
5141  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_reserve_flat_scratch") {
5142  if (IVersion.Major < 7)
5143  return Error(IDRange.Start, "directive requires gfx7+", IDRange);
5144  if (hasArchitectedFlatScratch())
5145  return Error(IDRange.Start,
5146  "directive is not supported with architected flat scratch",
5147  IDRange);
5148  if (!isUInt<1>(Val))
5149  return OutOfRangeError(ValRange);
5150  ReserveFlatScr = Val;
5151  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_reserve_xnack_mask") {
5152  if (IVersion.Major < 8)
5153  return Error(IDRange.Start, "directive requires gfx8+", IDRange);
5154  if (!isUInt<1>(Val))
5155  return OutOfRangeError(ValRange);
5156  if (Val != getTargetStreamer().getTargetID()->isXnackOnOrAny())
5157  return getParser().Error(IDRange.Start, ".amdhsa_reserve_xnack_mask does not match target id",
5158  IDRange);
5159  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_float_round_mode_32") {
5160  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1,
5161  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_FLOAT_ROUND_MODE_32, Val, ValRange);
5162  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_float_round_mode_16_64") {
5163  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1,
5164  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_FLOAT_ROUND_MODE_16_64, Val, ValRange);
5165  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_float_denorm_mode_32") {
5166  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1,
5167  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_FLOAT_DENORM_MODE_32, Val, ValRange);
5168  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_float_denorm_mode_16_64") {
5169  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1,
5170  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_FLOAT_DENORM_MODE_16_64, Val,
5171  ValRange);
5172  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_dx10_clamp") {
5173  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1,
5174  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_ENABLE_DX10_CLAMP, Val, ValRange);
5175  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_ieee_mode") {
5176  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1, COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_ENABLE_IEEE_MODE,
5177  Val, ValRange);
5178  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_fp16_overflow") {
5179  if (IVersion.Major < 9)
5180  return Error(IDRange.Start, "directive requires gfx9+", IDRange);
5181  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1, COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_FP16_OVFL, Val,
5182  ValRange);
5183  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_tg_split") {
5184  if (!isGFX90A())
5185  return Error(IDRange.Start, "directive requires gfx90a+", IDRange);
5186  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc3, COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC3_GFX90A_TG_SPLIT, Val,
5187  ValRange);
5188  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_workgroup_processor_mode") {
5189  if (IVersion.Major < 10)
5190  return Error(IDRange.Start, "directive requires gfx10+", IDRange);
5191  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1, COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_WGP_MODE, Val,
5192  ValRange);
5193  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_memory_ordered") {
5194  if (IVersion.Major < 10)
5195  return Error(IDRange.Start, "directive requires gfx10+", IDRange);
5196  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1, COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_MEM_ORDERED, Val,
5197  ValRange);
5198  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_forward_progress") {
5199  if (IVersion.Major < 10)
5200  return Error(IDRange.Start, "directive requires gfx10+", IDRange);
5201  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1, COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_FWD_PROGRESS, Val,
5202  ValRange);
5203  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_shared_vgpr_count") {
5204  if (IVersion.Major < 10)
5205  return Error(IDRange.Start, "directive requires gfx10+", IDRange);
5206  SharedVGPRCount = Val;
5207  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc3,
5208  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC3_GFX10_PLUS_SHARED_VGPR_COUNT, Val,
5209  ValRange);
5210  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_exception_fp_ieee_invalid_op") {
5211  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(
5212  KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5213  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_EXCEPTION_IEEE_754_FP_INVALID_OPERATION, Val,
5214  ValRange);
5215  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_exception_fp_denorm_src") {
5216  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5217  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_EXCEPTION_FP_DENORMAL_SOURCE,
5218  Val, ValRange);
5219  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_exception_fp_ieee_div_zero") {
5220  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(
5221  KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5222  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_EXCEPTION_IEEE_754_FP_DIVISION_BY_ZERO, Val,
5223  ValRange);
5224  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_exception_fp_ieee_overflow") {
5225  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5226  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_EXCEPTION_IEEE_754_FP_OVERFLOW,
5227  Val, ValRange);
5228  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_exception_fp_ieee_underflow") {
5229  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5230  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_EXCEPTION_IEEE_754_FP_UNDERFLOW,
5231  Val, ValRange);
5232  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_exception_fp_ieee_inexact") {
5233  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5234  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_EXCEPTION_IEEE_754_FP_INEXACT,
5235  Val, ValRange);
5236  } else if (ID == ".amdhsa_exception_int_div_zero") {
5237  PARSE_BITS_ENTRY(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2,
5238  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_ENABLE_EXCEPTION_INT_DIVIDE_BY_ZERO,
5239  Val, ValRange);
5240  } else {
5241  return Error(IDRange.Start, "unknown .amdhsa_kernel directive", IDRange);
5242  }
5243 
5244 #undef PARSE_BITS_ENTRY
5245  }
5246 
5247  if (Seen.find(".amdhsa_next_free_vgpr") == Seen.end())
5248  return TokError(".amdhsa_next_free_vgpr directive is required");
5249 
5250  if (Seen.find(".amdhsa_next_free_sgpr") == Seen.end())
5251  return TokError(".amdhsa_next_free_sgpr directive is required");
5252 
5253  unsigned VGPRBlocks;
5254  unsigned SGPRBlocks;
5255  if (calculateGPRBlocks(getFeatureBits(), ReserveVCC, ReserveFlatScr,
5256  getTargetStreamer().getTargetID()->isXnackOnOrAny(),
5257  EnableWavefrontSize32, NextFreeVGPR,
5258  VGPRRange, NextFreeSGPR, SGPRRange, VGPRBlocks,
5259  SGPRBlocks))
5260  return true;
5261 
5262  if (!isUInt<COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_GRANULATED_WORKITEM_VGPR_COUNT_WIDTH>(
5263  VGPRBlocks))
5264  return OutOfRangeError(VGPRRange);
5265  AMDHSA_BITS_SET(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1,
5266  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_GRANULATED_WORKITEM_VGPR_COUNT, VGPRBlocks);
5267 
5268  if (!isUInt<COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_GRANULATED_WAVEFRONT_SGPR_COUNT_WIDTH>(
5269  SGPRBlocks))
5270  return OutOfRangeError(SGPRRange);
5271  AMDHSA_BITS_SET(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc1,
5272  COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC1_GRANULATED_WAVEFRONT_SGPR_COUNT,
5273  SGPRBlocks);
5274 
5275  if (ExplicitUserSGPRCount && ImpliedUserSGPRCount > *ExplicitUserSGPRCount)
5276  return TokError("amdgpu_user_sgpr_count smaller than than implied by "
5277  "enabled user SGPRs");
5278 
5279  unsigned UserSGPRCount =
5280  ExplicitUserSGPRCount ? *ExplicitUserSGPRCount : ImpliedUserSGPRCount;
5281 
5282  if (!isUInt<COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_USER_SGPR_COUNT_WIDTH>(UserSGPRCount))
5283  return TokError("too many user SGPRs enabled");
5284  AMDHSA_BITS_SET(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc2, COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC2_USER_SGPR_COUNT,
5285  UserSGPRCount);
5286 
5287  if (isGFX90A()) {
5288  if (Seen.find(".amdhsa_accum_offset") == Seen.end())
5289  return TokError(".amdhsa_accum_offset directive is required");
5290  if (AccumOffset < 4 || AccumOffset > 256 || (AccumOffset & 3))
5291  return TokError("accum_offset should be in range [4..256] in "
5292  "increments of 4");
5293  if (AccumOffset > alignTo(std::max((uint64_t)1, NextFreeVGPR), 4))
5294  return TokError("accum_offset exceeds total VGPR allocation");
5295  AMDHSA_BITS_SET(KD.compute_pgm_rsrc3, COMPUTE_PGM_RSRC3_GFX90A_ACCUM_OFFSET,
5296  (AccumOffset / 4 - 1));
5297  }
5298 
5299  if (IVersion.Major == 10) {
5300  // SharedVGPRCount < 16 checked by PARSE_ENTRY_BITS
5301  if (SharedVGPRCount && EnableWavefrontSize32) {
5302  return TokError("shared_vgpr_count directive not valid on "
5303  "wavefront size 32");
5304  }
5305  if (SharedVGPRCount * 2 + VGPRBlocks > 63) {
5306  return TokError("shared_vgpr_count*2 + "
5307  "compute_pgm_rsrc1.GRANULATED_WORKITEM_VGPR_COUNT cannot "
5308  "exceed 63\n");
5309  }
5310  }
5311 
5312  getTargetStreamer().EmitAmdhsaKernelDescriptor(
5313  getSTI(), KernelName, KD, NextFreeVGPR, NextFreeSGPR, ReserveVCC,
5314  ReserveFlatScr, AMDGPU::getAmdhsaCodeObjectVersion());
5315  return false;
5316 }

5318 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectiveHSACodeObjectVersion() {
5319  uint32_t Major;
5320  uint32_t Minor;
5321 
5322  if (ParseDirectiveMajorMinor(Major, Minor))
5323  return true;
5324 
5325  getTargetStreamer().EmitDirectiveHSACodeObjectVersion(Major, Minor);
5326  return false;
5327 }

5329 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectiveHSACodeObjectISA() {
5330  uint32_t Major;
5331  uint32_t Minor;
5332  uint32_t Stepping;
5333  StringRef VendorName;
5334  StringRef ArchName;
5335 
5336  // If this directive has no arguments, then use the ISA version for the
5337  // targeted GPU.
5338  if (isToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
5339  AMDGPU::IsaVersion ISA = AMDGPU::getIsaVersion(getSTI().getCPU());
5340  getTargetStreamer().EmitDirectiveHSACodeObjectISAV2(ISA.Major, ISA.Minor,
5341  ISA.Stepping,
5342  "AMD", "AMDGPU");
5343  return false;
5344  }
5345 
5346  if (ParseDirectiveMajorMinor(Major, Minor))
5347  return true;
5348 
5349  if (!trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma))
5350  return TokError("stepping version number required, comma expected");
5351 
5352  if (ParseAsAbsoluteExpression(Stepping))
5353  return TokError("invalid stepping version");
5354 
5355  if (!trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma))
5356  return TokError("vendor name required, comma expected");
5357 
5358  if (!parseString(VendorName, "invalid vendor name"))
5359  return true;
5360 
5361  if (!trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma))
5362  return TokError("arch name required, comma expected");
5363 
5364  if (!parseString(ArchName, "invalid arch name"))
5365  return true;
5366 
5367  getTargetStreamer().EmitDirectiveHSACodeObjectISAV2(Major, Minor, Stepping,
5368  VendorName, ArchName);
5369  return false;
5370 }

5372 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseAMDKernelCodeTValue(StringRef ID,
5373  amd_kernel_code_t &Header) {
5374  // max_scratch_backing_memory_byte_size is deprecated. Ignore it while parsing
5375  // assembly for backwards compatibility.
5376  if (ID == "max_scratch_backing_memory_byte_size") {
5377  Parser.eatToEndOfStatement();
5378  return false;
5379  }
5380 
5381  SmallString<40> ErrStr;
5382  raw_svector_ostream Err(ErrStr);
5383  if (!parseAmdKernelCodeField(ID, getParser(), Header, Err)) {
5384  return TokError(Err.str());
5385  }
5386  Lex();
5387 
5388  if (ID == "enable_wavefront_size32") {
5389  if (Header.code_properties & AMD_CODE_PROPERTY_ENABLE_WAVEFRONT_SIZE32) {
5390  if (!isGFX10Plus())
5391  return TokError("enable_wavefront_size32=1 is only allowed on GFX10+");
5392  if (!getFeatureBits()[AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize32])
5393  return TokError("enable_wavefront_size32=1 requires +WavefrontSize32");
5394  } else {
5395  if (!getFeatureBits()[AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize64])
5396  return TokError("enable_wavefront_size32=0 requires +WavefrontSize64");
5397  }
5398  }
5399 
5400  if (ID == "wavefront_size") {
5401  if (Header.wavefront_size == 5) {
5402  if (!isGFX10Plus())
5403  return TokError("wavefront_size=5 is only allowed on GFX10+");
5404  if (!getFeatureBits()[AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize32])
5405  return TokError("wavefront_size=5 requires +WavefrontSize32");
5406  } else if (Header.wavefront_size == 6) {
5407  if (!getFeatureBits()[AMDGPU::FeatureWavefrontSize64])
5408  return TokError("wavefront_size=6 requires +WavefrontSize64");
5409  }
5410  }
5411 
5412  if (ID == "enable_wgp_mode") {
5413  if (G_00B848_WGP_MODE(Header.compute_pgm_resource_registers) &&
5414  !isGFX10Plus())
5415  return TokError("enable_wgp_mode=1 is only allowed on GFX10+");
5416  }
5417 
5418  if (ID == "enable_mem_ordered") {
5419  if (G_00B848_MEM_ORDERED(Header.compute_pgm_resource_registers) &&
5420  !isGFX10Plus())
5421  return TokError("enable_mem_ordered=1 is only allowed on GFX10+");
5422  }
5423 
5424  if (ID == "enable_fwd_progress") {
5425  if (G_00B848_FWD_PROGRESS(Header.compute_pgm_resource_registers) &&
5426  !isGFX10Plus())
5427  return TokError("enable_fwd_progress=1 is only allowed on GFX10+");
5428  }
5429 
5430  return false;
5431 }
5432 
5433 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectiveAMDKernelCodeT() {
5434  amd_kernel_code_t Header;
5435  AMDGPU::initDefaultAMDKernelCodeT(Header, &getSTI());
5436 
5437  while (true) {
5438  // Lex EndOfStatement. This is in a while loop, because lexing a comment
5439  // will set the current token to EndOfStatement.
5440  while(trySkipToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement));
5441 
5442  StringRef ID;
5443  if (!parseId(ID, "expected value identifier or .end_amd_kernel_code_t"))
5444  return true;
5445 
5446  if (ID == ".end_amd_kernel_code_t")
5447  break;
5448 
5449  if (ParseAMDKernelCodeTValue(ID, Header))
5450  return true;
5451  }
5452 
5453  getTargetStreamer().EmitAMDKernelCodeT(Header);
5454 
5455  return false;
5456 }

5458 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectiveAMDGPUHsaKernel() {
5459  StringRef KernelName;
5460  if (!parseId(KernelName, "expected symbol name"))
5461  return true;
5462 
5463  getTargetStreamer().EmitAMDGPUSymbolType(KernelName,
5464  ELF::STT_AMDGPU_HSA_KERNEL);
5465 
5466  KernelScope.initialize(getContext());
5467  return false;
5468 }

5470 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectiveISAVersion() {
5471  if (getSTI().getTargetTriple().getArch() != Triple::amdgcn) {
5472  return Error(getLoc(),
5473  ".amd_amdgpu_isa directive is not available on non-amdgcn "
5474  "architectures");
5475  }
5476 
5477  auto TargetIDDirective = getLexer().getTok().getStringContents();
5478  if (getTargetStreamer().getTargetID()->toString() != TargetIDDirective)
5479  return Error(getParser().getTok().getLoc(), "target id must match options");
5480 
5481  getTargetStreamer().EmitISAVersion();
5482  Lex();
5483 
5484  return false;
5485 }

5487 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectiveHSAMetadata() {
5488  const char *AssemblerDirectiveBegin;
5489  const char *AssemblerDirectiveEnd;
5490  std::tie(AssemblerDirectiveBegin, AssemblerDirectiveEnd) =
5491  isHsaAbiVersion3AndAbove(&getSTI())
5492  ? std::tuple(HSAMD::V3::AssemblerDirectiveBegin,
5493  HSAMD::V3::AssemblerDirectiveEnd)
5494  : std::tuple(HSAMD::AssemblerDirectiveBegin,
5495  HSAMD::AssemblerDirectiveEnd);
5496 
5497  if (getSTI().getTargetTriple().getOS() != Triple::AMDHSA) {
5498  return Error(getLoc(),
5499  (Twine(AssemblerDirectiveBegin) + Twine(" directive is "
5500  "not available on non-amdhsa OSes")).str());
5501  }
5502 
5503  std::string HSAMetadataString;
5504  if (ParseToEndDirective(AssemblerDirectiveBegin, AssemblerDirectiveEnd,
5505  HSAMetadataString))
5506  return true;
5507 
5508  if (isHsaAbiVersion3AndAbove(&getSTI())) {
5509  if (!getTargetStreamer().EmitHSAMetadataV3(HSAMetadataString))
5510  return Error(getLoc(), "invalid HSA metadata");
5511  } else {
5512  if (!getTargetStreamer().EmitHSAMetadataV2(HSAMetadataString))
5513  return Error(getLoc(), "invalid HSA metadata");
5514  }
5515 
5516  return false;
5517 }
5518 
5519 /// Common code to parse out a block of text (typically YAML) between start and
5520 /// end directives.
5521 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseToEndDirective(const char *AssemblerDirectiveBegin,
5522  const char *AssemblerDirectiveEnd,
5523  std::string &CollectString) {
5524 
5525  raw_string_ostream CollectStream(CollectString);
5526 
5527  getLexer().setSkipSpace(false);
5528 
5529  bool FoundEnd = false;
5530  while (!isToken(AsmToken::Eof)) {
5531  while (isToken(AsmToken::Space)) {
5532  CollectStream << getTokenStr();
5533  Lex();
5534  }
5535 
5536  if (trySkipId(AssemblerDirectiveEnd)) {
5537  FoundEnd = true;
5538  break;
5539  }
5540 
5541  CollectStream << Parser.parseStringToEndOfStatement()
5542  << getContext().getAsmInfo()->getSeparatorString();
5543 
5544  Parser.eatToEndOfStatement();
5545  }
5546 
5547  getLexer().setSkipSpace(true);
5548 
5549  if (isToken(AsmToken::Eof) && !FoundEnd) {
5550  return TokError(Twine("expected directive ") +
5551  Twine(AssemblerDirectiveEnd) + Twine(" not found"));
5552  }
5553 
5554  CollectStream.flush();
5555  return false;
5556 }
5557 
5558 /// Parse the assembler directive for new MsgPack-format PAL metadata.
5559 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectivePALMetadataBegin() {
5560  std::string String;
5561  if (ParseToEndDirective(AMDGPU::PALMD::AssemblerDirectiveBegin,
5562  AMDGPU::PALMD::AssemblerDirectiveEnd, String))
5563  return true;
5564 
5565  auto PALMetadata = getTargetStreamer().getPALMetadata();
5566  if (!PALMetadata->setFromString(String))
5567  return Error(getLoc(), "invalid PAL metadata");
5568  return false;
5569 }
5570 
5571 /// Parse the assembler directive for old linear-format PAL metadata.
5572 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectivePALMetadata() {
5573  if (getSTI().getTargetTriple().getOS() != Triple::AMDPAL) {
5574  return Error(getLoc(),
5575  (Twine(PALMD::AssemblerDirective) + Twine(" directive is "
5576  "not available on non-amdpal OSes")).str());
5577  }
5578 
5579  auto PALMetadata = getTargetStreamer().getPALMetadata();
5580  PALMetadata->setLegacy();
5581  for (;;) {
5582  uint32_t Key, Value;
5583  if (ParseAsAbsoluteExpression(Key)) {
5584  return TokError(Twine("invalid value in ") +
5585  Twine(PALMD::AssemblerDirective));
5586  }
5587  if (!trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
5588  return TokError(Twine("expected an even number of values in ") +
5589  Twine(PALMD::AssemblerDirective));
5590  }
5591  if (ParseAsAbsoluteExpression(Value)) {
5592  return TokError(Twine("invalid value in ") +
5593  Twine(PALMD::AssemblerDirective));
5594  }
5595  PALMetadata->setRegister(Key, Value);
5596  if (!trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma))
5597  break;
5598  }
5599  return false;
5600 }
5601 
5602 /// ParseDirectiveAMDGPULDS
5603 /// ::= .amdgpu_lds identifier ',' size_expression [',' align_expression]
5604 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirectiveAMDGPULDS() {
5605  if (getParser().checkForValidSection())
5606  return true;
5607 
5608  StringRef Name;
5609  SMLoc NameLoc = getLoc();
5610  if (getParser().parseIdentifier(Name))
5611  return TokError("expected identifier in directive");
5612 
5613  MCSymbol *Symbol = getContext().getOrCreateSymbol(Name);
5614  if (getParser().parseComma())
5615  return true;
5616 
5617  unsigned LocalMemorySize = AMDGPU::IsaInfo::getLocalMemorySize(&getSTI());
5618 
5619  int64_t Size;
5620  SMLoc SizeLoc = getLoc();
5621  if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(Size))
5622  return true;
5623  if (Size < 0)
5624  return Error(SizeLoc, "size must be non-negative");
5625  if (Size > LocalMemorySize)
5626  return Error(SizeLoc, "size is too large");
5627 
5628  int64_t Alignment = 4;
5629  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
5630  SMLoc AlignLoc = getLoc();
5631  if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(Alignment))
5632  return true;
5633  if (Alignment < 0 || !isPowerOf2_64(Alignment))
5634  return Error(AlignLoc, "alignment must be a power of two");
5635 
5636  // Alignment larger than the size of LDS is possible in theory, as long
5637  // as the linker manages to place to symbol at address 0, but we do want
5638  // to make sure the alignment fits nicely into a 32-bit integer.
5639  if (Alignment >= 1u << 31)
5640  return Error(AlignLoc, "alignment is too large");
5641  }
5642 
5643  if (parseEOL())
5644  return true;
5645 
5646  Symbol->redefineIfPossible();
5647  if (!Symbol->isUndefined())
5648  return Error(NameLoc, "invalid symbol redefinition");
5649 
5650  getTargetStreamer().emitAMDGPULDS(Symbol, Size, Align(Alignment));
5651  return false;
5652 }
5653 
5654 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseDirective(AsmToken DirectiveID) {
5655  StringRef IDVal = DirectiveID.getString();
5656 
5657  if (isHsaAbiVersion3AndAbove(&getSTI())) {
5658  if (IDVal == ".amdhsa_kernel")
5659  return ParseDirectiveAMDHSAKernel();
5660 
5661  // TODO: Restructure/combine with PAL metadata directive.
5662  if (IDVal == AMDGPU::HSAMD::V3::AssemblerDirectiveBegin)
5663  return ParseDirectiveHSAMetadata();
5664  } else {
5665  if (IDVal == ".hsa_code_object_version")
5666  return ParseDirectiveHSACodeObjectVersion();
5667 
5668  if (IDVal == ".hsa_code_object_isa")
5669  return ParseDirectiveHSACodeObjectISA();
5670 
5671  if (IDVal == ".amd_kernel_code_t")
5672  return ParseDirectiveAMDKernelCodeT();
5673 
5674  if (IDVal == ".amdgpu_hsa_kernel")
5675  return ParseDirectiveAMDGPUHsaKernel();
5676 
5677  if (IDVal == ".amd_amdgpu_isa")
5678  return ParseDirectiveISAVersion();
5679 
5680  if (IDVal == AMDGPU::HSAMD::AssemblerDirectiveBegin)
5681  return ParseDirectiveHSAMetadata();
5682  }
5683 
5684  if (IDVal == ".amdgcn_target")
5685  return ParseDirectiveAMDGCNTarget();
5686 
5687  if (IDVal == ".amdgpu_lds")
5688  return ParseDirectiveAMDGPULDS();
5689 
5690  if (IDVal == PALMD::AssemblerDirectiveBegin)
5691  return ParseDirectivePALMetadataBegin();
5692 
5693  if (IDVal == PALMD::AssemblerDirective)
5694  return ParseDirectivePALMetadata();
5695 
5696  return true;
5697 }
5698 
5699 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::subtargetHasRegister(const MCRegisterInfo &MRI,
5700  unsigned RegNo) {
5701 
5702  if (MRI.regsOverlap(AMDGPU::TTMP12_TTMP13_TTMP14_TTMP15, RegNo))
5703  return isGFX9Plus();
5704 
5705  // GFX10+ has 2 more SGPRs 104 and 105.
5706  if (MRI.regsOverlap(AMDGPU::SGPR104_SGPR105, RegNo))
5707  return hasSGPR104_SGPR105();
5708 
5709  switch (RegNo) {
5710  case AMDGPU::SRC_SHARED_BASE_LO:
5711  case AMDGPU::SRC_SHARED_BASE:
5712  case AMDGPU::SRC_SHARED_LIMIT_LO:
5713  case AMDGPU::SRC_SHARED_LIMIT:
5714  case AMDGPU::SRC_PRIVATE_BASE_LO:
5715  case AMDGPU::SRC_PRIVATE_BASE:
5716  case AMDGPU::SRC_PRIVATE_LIMIT_LO:
5717  case AMDGPU::SRC_PRIVATE_LIMIT:
5718  return isGFX9Plus();
5719  case AMDGPU::SRC_POPS_EXITING_WAVE_ID:
5720  return isGFX9Plus() && !isGFX11Plus();
5721  case AMDGPU::TBA:
5722  case AMDGPU::TBA_LO:
5723  case AMDGPU::TBA_HI:
5724  case AMDGPU::TMA:
5725  case AMDGPU::TMA_LO:
5726  case AMDGPU::TMA_HI:
5727  return !isGFX9Plus();
5728  case AMDGPU::XNACK_MASK:
5729  case AMDGPU::XNACK_MASK_LO:
5730  case AMDGPU::XNACK_MASK_HI:
5731  return (isVI() || isGFX9()) && getTargetStreamer().getTargetID()->isXnackSupported();
5732  case AMDGPU::SGPR_NULL:
5733  return isGFX10Plus();
5734  default:
5735  break;
5736  }
5737 
5738  if (isCI())
5739  return true;
5740 
5741  if (isSI() || isGFX10Plus()) {
5742  // No flat_scr on SI.
5743  // On GFX10Plus flat scratch is not a valid register operand and can only be
5744  // accessed with s_setreg/s_getreg.
5745  switch (RegNo) {
5746  case AMDGPU::FLAT_SCR:
5747  case AMDGPU::FLAT_SCR_LO:
5748  case AMDGPU::FLAT_SCR_HI:
5749  return false;
5750  default:
5751  return true;
5752  }
5753  }
5754 
5755  // VI only has 102 SGPRs, so make sure we aren't trying to use the 2 more that
5756  // SI/CI have.
5757  if (MRI.regsOverlap(AMDGPU::SGPR102_SGPR103, RegNo))
5758  return hasSGPR102_SGPR103();
5759 
5760  return true;
5761 }
5762 
5763 OperandMatchResultTy
5764 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseOperand(OperandVector &Operands, StringRef Mnemonic,
5765  OperandMode Mode) {
5766  OperandMatchResultTy ResTy = parseVOPD(Operands);
5767  if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success || ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail ||
5768  isToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
5769  return ResTy;
5770 
5771  // Try to parse with a custom parser
5772  ResTy = MatchOperandParserImpl(Operands, Mnemonic);
5773 
5774  // If we successfully parsed the operand or if there as an error parsing,
5775  // we are done.
5776  //
5777  // If we are parsing after we reach EndOfStatement then this means we
5778  // are appending default values to the Operands list. This is only done
5779  // by custom parser, so we shouldn't continue on to the generic parsing.
5780  if (ResTy == MatchOperand_Success || ResTy == MatchOperand_ParseFail ||
5781  isToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement))
5782  return ResTy;
5783 
5784  SMLoc RBraceLoc;
5785  SMLoc LBraceLoc = getLoc();
5786  if (Mode == OperandMode_NSA && trySkipToken(AsmToken::LBrac)) {
5787  unsigned Prefix = Operands.size();
5788 
5789  for (;;) {
5790  auto Loc = getLoc();
5791  ResTy = parseReg(Operands);
5792  if (ResTy == MatchOperand_NoMatch)
5793  Error(Loc, "expected a register");
5794  if (ResTy != MatchOperand_Success)
5795  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5796 
5797  RBraceLoc = getLoc();
5798  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::RBrac))
5799  break;
5800 
5801  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::Comma,
5802  "expected a comma or a closing square bracket")) {
5803  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5804  }
5805  }
5806 
5807  if (Operands.size() - Prefix > 1) {
5808  Operands.insert(Operands.begin() + Prefix,
5809  AMDGPUOperand::CreateToken(this, "[", LBraceLoc));
5810  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateToken(this, "]", RBraceLoc));
5811  }
5812 
5813  return MatchOperand_Success;
5814  }
5815 
5816  return parseRegOrImm(Operands);
5817 }
5818 
5819 StringRef AMDGPUAsmParser::parseMnemonicSuffix(StringRef Name) {
5820  // Clear any forced encodings from the previous instruction.
5821  setForcedEncodingSize(0);
5822  setForcedDPP(false);
5823  setForcedSDWA(false);
5824 
5825  if (Name.endswith("_e64_dpp")) {
5826  setForcedDPP(true);
5827  setForcedEncodingSize(64);
5828  return Name.substr(0, Name.size() - 8);
5829  } else if (Name.endswith("_e64")) {
5830  setForcedEncodingSize(64);
5831  return Name.substr(0, Name.size() - 4);
5832  } else if (Name.endswith("_e32")) {
5833  setForcedEncodingSize(32);
5834  return Name.substr(0, Name.size() - 4);
5835  } else if (Name.endswith("_dpp")) {
5836  setForcedDPP(true);
5837  return Name.substr(0, Name.size() - 4);
5838  } else if (Name.endswith("_sdwa")) {
5839  setForcedSDWA(true);
5840  return Name.substr(0, Name.size() - 5);
5841  }
5842  return Name;
5843 }
5844 
5845 static void applyMnemonicAliases(StringRef &Mnemonic,
5846  const FeatureBitset &Features,
5847  unsigned VariantID);
5848 
5849 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::ParseInstruction(ParseInstructionInfo &Info,
5850  StringRef Name,
5851  SMLoc NameLoc, OperandVector &Operands) {
5852  // Add the instruction mnemonic
5853  Name = parseMnemonicSuffix(Name);
5854 
5855  // If the target architecture uses MnemonicAlias, call it here to parse
5856  // operands correctly.
5857  applyMnemonicAliases(Name, getAvailableFeatures(), 0);
5858 
5859  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateToken(this, Name, NameLoc));
5860 
5861  bool IsMIMG = Name.startswith("image_");
5862 
5863  while (!trySkipToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
5864  OperandMode Mode = OperandMode_Default;
5865  if (IsMIMG && isGFX10Plus() && Operands.size() == 2)
5866  Mode = OperandMode_NSA;
5867  OperandMatchResultTy Res = parseOperand(Operands, Name, Mode);
5868 
5869  if (Res != MatchOperand_Success) {
5870  checkUnsupportedInstruction(Name, NameLoc);
5871  if (!Parser.hasPendingError()) {
5872  // FIXME: use real operand location rather than the current location.
5873  StringRef Msg =
5874  (Res == MatchOperand_ParseFail) ? "failed parsing operand." :
5875  "not a valid operand.";
5876  Error(getLoc(), Msg);
5877  }
5878  while (!trySkipToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
5879  lex();
5880  }
5881  return true;
5882  }
5883 
5884  // Eat the comma or space if there is one.
5885  trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma);
5886  }
5887 
5888  return false;
5889 }

5891 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5892 // Utility functions
5893 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
5894 
5895 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseTokenOp(StringRef Name,
5896  OperandVector &Operands) {
5897  SMLoc S = getLoc();
5898  if (!trySkipId(Name))
5899  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
5900 
5901  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateToken(this, Name, S));
5902  return MatchOperand_Success;
5903 }
5904 
5905 OperandMatchResultTy
5906 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseIntWithPrefix(const char *Prefix, int64_t &IntVal) {
5907 
5908  if (!trySkipId(Prefix, AsmToken::Colon))
5909  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
5910 
5911  return parseExpr(IntVal) ? MatchOperand_Success : MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5912 }
5913 
5914 OperandMatchResultTy
5915 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseIntWithPrefix(const char *Prefix, OperandVector &Operands,
5916  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTy ImmTy,
5917  bool (*ConvertResult)(int64_t&)) {
5918  SMLoc S = getLoc();
5919  int64_t Value = 0;
5920 
5921  OperandMatchResultTy Res = parseIntWithPrefix(Prefix, Value);
5922  if (Res != MatchOperand_Success)
5923  return Res;
5924 
5925  if (ConvertResult && !ConvertResult(Value)) {
5926  Error(S, "invalid " + StringRef(Prefix) + " value.");
5927  }
5928 
5929  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Value, S, ImmTy));
5930  return MatchOperand_Success;
5931 }
5932 
5933 OperandMatchResultTy
5934 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseOperandArrayWithPrefix(const char *Prefix,
5935  OperandVector &Operands,
5936  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTy ImmTy,
5937  bool (*ConvertResult)(int64_t&)) {
5938  SMLoc S = getLoc();
5939  if (!trySkipId(Prefix, AsmToken::Colon))
5940  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
5941 
5942  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::LBrac, "expected a left square bracket"))
5943  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5944 
5945  unsigned Val = 0;
5946  const unsigned MaxSize = 4;
5947 
5948  // FIXME: How to verify the number of elements matches the number of src
5949  // operands?
5950  for (int I = 0; ; ++I) {
5951  int64_t Op;
5952  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
5953  if (!parseExpr(Op))
5954  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5955 
5956  if (Op != 0 && Op != 1) {
5957  Error(Loc, "invalid " + StringRef(Prefix) + " value.");
5958  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5959  }
5960 
5961  Val |= (Op << I);
5962 
5963  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::RBrac))
5964  break;
5965 
5966  if (I + 1 == MaxSize) {
5967  Error(getLoc(), "expected a closing square bracket");
5968  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5969  }
5970 
5971  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected a comma"))
5972  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5973  }
5974 
5975  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Val, S, ImmTy));
5976  return MatchOperand_Success;
5977 }
5978 
5979 OperandMatchResultTy
5980 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseNamedBit(StringRef Name, OperandVector &Operands,
5981  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTy ImmTy) {
5982  int64_t Bit;
5983  SMLoc S = getLoc();
5984 
5985  if (trySkipId(Name)) {
5986  Bit = 1;
5987  } else if (trySkipId("no", Name)) {
5988  Bit = 0;
5989  } else {
5990  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
5991  }
5992 
5993  if (Name == "r128" && !hasMIMG_R128()) {
5994  Error(S, "r128 modifier is not supported on this GPU");
5995  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
5996  }
5997  if (Name == "a16" && !hasA16()) {
5998  Error(S, "a16 modifier is not supported on this GPU");
5999  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6000  }
6001 
6002  if (isGFX9() && ImmTy == AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyA16)
6003  ImmTy = AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyR128A16;
6004 
6005  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Bit, S, ImmTy));
6006  return MatchOperand_Success;
6007 }
6008 
6009 unsigned AMDGPUAsmParser::getCPolKind(StringRef Id, StringRef Mnemo,
6010  bool &Disabling) const {
6011  Disabling = Id.startswith("no");
6012 
6013  if (isGFX940() && !Mnemo.startswith("s_")) {
6014  return StringSwitch<unsigned>(Id)
6015  .Case("nt", AMDGPU::CPol::NT)
6016  .Case("nont", AMDGPU::CPol::NT)
6017  .Case("sc0", AMDGPU::CPol::SC0)
6018  .Case("nosc0", AMDGPU::CPol::SC0)
6019  .Case("sc1", AMDGPU::CPol::SC1)
6020  .Case("nosc1", AMDGPU::CPol::SC1)
6021  .Default(0);
6022  }
6023 
6024  return StringSwitch<unsigned>(Id)
6025  .Case("dlc", AMDGPU::CPol::DLC)
6026  .Case("nodlc", AMDGPU::CPol::DLC)
6027  .Case("glc", AMDGPU::CPol::GLC)
6028  .Case("noglc", AMDGPU::CPol::GLC)
6029  .Case("scc", AMDGPU::CPol::SCC)
6030  .Case("noscc", AMDGPU::CPol::SCC)
6031  .Case("slc", AMDGPU::CPol::SLC)
6032  .Case("noslc", AMDGPU::CPol::SLC)
6033  .Default(0);
6034 }
6035 
6036 OperandMatchResultTy
6037 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseCPol(OperandVector &Operands) {
6038  StringRef Mnemo = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[0]).getToken();
6039  SMLoc OpLoc = getLoc();
6040  unsigned Enabled = 0, Seen = 0;
6041  for (;;) {
6042  SMLoc S = getLoc();
6043  bool Disabling;
6044  unsigned CPol = getCPolKind(getId(), Mnemo, Disabling);
6045  if (!CPol)
6046  break;
6047 
6048  lex();
6049 
6050  if (!isGFX10Plus() && CPol == AMDGPU::CPol::DLC) {
6051  Error(S, "dlc modifier is not supported on this GPU");
6052  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6053  }
6054 
6055  if (!isGFX90A() && CPol == AMDGPU::CPol::SCC) {
6056  Error(S, "scc modifier is not supported on this GPU");
6057  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6058  }
6059 
6060  if (Seen & CPol) {
6061  Error(S, "duplicate cache policy modifier");
6062  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6063  }
6064 
6065  if (!Disabling)
6066  Enabled |= CPol;
6067 
6068  Seen |= CPol;
6069  }
6070 
6071  if (!Seen)
6072  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6073 
6074  Operands.push_back(
6075  AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Enabled, OpLoc, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyCPol));
6076  return MatchOperand_Success;
6077 }
6078 
6079 static void addOptionalImmOperand(
6080  MCInst& Inst, const OperandVector& Operands,
6081  AMDGPUAsmParser::OptionalImmIndexMap& OptionalIdx,
6082  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTy ImmT,
6083  int64_t Default = 0) {
6084  auto i = OptionalIdx.find(ImmT);
6085  if (i != OptionalIdx.end()) {
6086  unsigned Idx = i->second;
6087  ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[Idx]).addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
6088  } else {
6089  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Default));
6090  }
6091 }

6093 OperandMatchResultTy
6094 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseStringWithPrefix(StringRef Prefix,
6095  StringRef &Value,
6096  SMLoc &StringLoc) {
6097  if (!trySkipId(Prefix, AsmToken::Colon))
6098  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6099 
6100  StringLoc = getLoc();
6101  return parseId(Value, "expected an identifier") ? MatchOperand_Success
6102  : MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6103 }
