6105 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6106 // MTBUF format
6107 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6108 
6109 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::tryParseFmt(const char *Pref,
6110  int64_t MaxVal,
6111  int64_t &Fmt) {
6112  int64_t Val;
6113  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
6114 
6115  auto Res = parseIntWithPrefix(Pref, Val);
6116  if (Res == MatchOperand_ParseFail)
6117  return false;
6118  if (Res == MatchOperand_NoMatch)
6119  return true;
6120 
6121  if (Val < 0 || Val > MaxVal) {
6122  Error(Loc, Twine("out of range ", StringRef(Pref)));
6123  return false;
6124  }
6125 
6126  Fmt = Val;
6127  return true;
6128 }
6129 
6130 // dfmt and nfmt (in a tbuffer instruction) are parsed as one to allow their
6131 // values to live in a joint format operand in the MCInst encoding.
6132 OperandMatchResultTy
6133 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseDfmtNfmt(int64_t &Format) {
6134  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::MTBUFFormat;
6135 
6136  int64_t Dfmt = DFMT_UNDEF;
6137  int64_t Nfmt = NFMT_UNDEF;
6138 
6139  // dfmt and nfmt can appear in either order, and each is optional.
6140  for (int I = 0; I < 2; ++I) {
6141  if (Dfmt == DFMT_UNDEF && !tryParseFmt("dfmt", DFMT_MAX, Dfmt))
6142  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6143 
6144  if (Nfmt == NFMT_UNDEF && !tryParseFmt("nfmt", NFMT_MAX, Nfmt)) {
6145  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6146  }
6147  // Skip optional comma between dfmt/nfmt
6148  // but guard against 2 commas following each other.
6149  if ((Dfmt == DFMT_UNDEF) != (Nfmt == NFMT_UNDEF) &&
6150  !peekToken().is(AsmToken::Comma)) {
6151  trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma);
6152  }
6153  }
6154 
6155  if (Dfmt == DFMT_UNDEF && Nfmt == NFMT_UNDEF)
6156  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6157 
6158  Dfmt = (Dfmt == DFMT_UNDEF) ? DFMT_DEFAULT : Dfmt;
6159  Nfmt = (Nfmt == NFMT_UNDEF) ? NFMT_DEFAULT : Nfmt;
6160 
6161  Format = encodeDfmtNfmt(Dfmt, Nfmt);
6162  return MatchOperand_Success;
6163 }
6164 
6165 OperandMatchResultTy
6166 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseUfmt(int64_t &Format) {
6167  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::MTBUFFormat;
6168 
6169  int64_t Fmt = UFMT_UNDEF;
6170 
6171  if (!tryParseFmt("format", UFMT_MAX, Fmt))
6172  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6173 
6174  if (Fmt == UFMT_UNDEF)
6175  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6176 
6177  Format = Fmt;
6178  return MatchOperand_Success;
6179 }
6180 
6181 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::matchDfmtNfmt(int64_t &Dfmt,
6182  int64_t &Nfmt,
6183  StringRef FormatStr,
6184  SMLoc Loc) {
6185  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::MTBUFFormat;
6186  int64_t Format;
6187 
6188  Format = getDfmt(FormatStr);
6189  if (Format != DFMT_UNDEF) {
6190  Dfmt = Format;
6191  return true;
6192  }
6193 
6194  Format = getNfmt(FormatStr, getSTI());
6195  if (Format != NFMT_UNDEF) {
6196  Nfmt = Format;
6197  return true;
6198  }
6199 
6200  Error(Loc, "unsupported format");
6201  return false;
6202 }
6203 
6204 OperandMatchResultTy
6205 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSymbolicSplitFormat(StringRef FormatStr,
6206  SMLoc FormatLoc,
6207  int64_t &Format) {
6208  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::MTBUFFormat;
6209 
6210  int64_t Dfmt = DFMT_UNDEF;
6211  int64_t Nfmt = NFMT_UNDEF;
6212  if (!matchDfmtNfmt(Dfmt, Nfmt, FormatStr, FormatLoc))
6213  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6214 
6215  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
6216  StringRef Str;
6217  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
6218  if (!parseId(Str, "expected a format string") ||
6219  !matchDfmtNfmt(Dfmt, Nfmt, Str, Loc)) {
6220  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6221  }
6222  if (Dfmt == DFMT_UNDEF) {
6223  Error(Loc, "duplicate numeric format");
6224  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6225  } else if (Nfmt == NFMT_UNDEF) {
6226  Error(Loc, "duplicate data format");
6227  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6228  }
6229  }
6230 
6231  Dfmt = (Dfmt == DFMT_UNDEF) ? DFMT_DEFAULT : Dfmt;
6232  Nfmt = (Nfmt == NFMT_UNDEF) ? NFMT_DEFAULT : Nfmt;
6233 
6234  if (isGFX10Plus()) {
6235  auto Ufmt = convertDfmtNfmt2Ufmt(Dfmt, Nfmt, getSTI());
6236  if (Ufmt == UFMT_UNDEF) {
6237  Error(FormatLoc, "unsupported format");
6238  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6239  }
6240  Format = Ufmt;
6241  } else {
6242  Format = encodeDfmtNfmt(Dfmt, Nfmt);
6243  }
6244 
6245  return MatchOperand_Success;
6246 }
6247 
6248 OperandMatchResultTy
6249 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSymbolicUnifiedFormat(StringRef FormatStr,
6250  SMLoc Loc,
6251  int64_t &Format) {
6252  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::MTBUFFormat;
6253 
6254  auto Id = getUnifiedFormat(FormatStr, getSTI());
6255  if (Id == UFMT_UNDEF)
6256  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6257 
6258  if (!isGFX10Plus()) {
6259  Error(Loc, "unified format is not supported on this GPU");
6260  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6261  }
6262 
6263  Format = Id;
6264  return MatchOperand_Success;
6265 }
6266 
6267 OperandMatchResultTy
6268 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseNumericFormat(int64_t &Format) {
6269  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::MTBUFFormat;
6270  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
6271 
6272  if (!parseExpr(Format))
6273  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6274  if (!isValidFormatEncoding(Format, getSTI())) {
6275  Error(Loc, "out of range format");
6276  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6277  }
6278 
6279  return MatchOperand_Success;
6280 }
6281 
6282 OperandMatchResultTy
6283 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSymbolicOrNumericFormat(int64_t &Format) {
6284  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::MTBUFFormat;
6285 
6286  if (!trySkipId("format", AsmToken::Colon))
6287  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
6288 
6289  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::LBrac)) {
6290  StringRef FormatStr;
6291  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
6292  if (!parseId(FormatStr, "expected a format string"))
6293  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6294 
6295  auto Res = parseSymbolicUnifiedFormat(FormatStr, Loc, Format);
6296  if (Res == MatchOperand_NoMatch)
6297  Res = parseSymbolicSplitFormat(FormatStr, Loc, Format);
6298  if (Res != MatchOperand_Success)
6299  return Res;
6300 
6301  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::RBrac, "expected a closing square bracket"))
6302  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6303 
6304  return MatchOperand_Success;
6305  }
6306 
6307  return parseNumericFormat(Format);
6308 }
6309 
6310 OperandMatchResultTy
6311 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseFORMAT(OperandVector &Operands) {
6312  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::MTBUFFormat;
6313 
6314  int64_t Format = getDefaultFormatEncoding(getSTI());
6315  OperandMatchResultTy Res;
6316  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
6317 
6318  // Parse legacy format syntax.
6319  Res = isGFX10Plus() ? parseUfmt(Format) : parseDfmtNfmt(Format);
6320  if (Res == MatchOperand_ParseFail)
6321  return Res;
6322 
6323  bool FormatFound = (Res == MatchOperand_Success);
6324 
6325  Operands.push_back(
6326  AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Format, Loc, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyFORMAT));
6327 
6328  if (FormatFound)
6329  trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma);
6330 
6331  if (isToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6332  // We are expecting an soffset operand,
6333  // but let matcher handle the error.
6334  return MatchOperand_Success;
6335  }
6336 
6337  // Parse soffset.
6338  Res = parseRegOrImm(Operands);
6339  if (Res != MatchOperand_Success)
6340  return Res;
6341 
6342  trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma);
6343 
6344  if (!FormatFound) {
6345  Res = parseSymbolicOrNumericFormat(Format);
6346  if (Res == MatchOperand_ParseFail)
6347  return Res;
6348  if (Res == MatchOperand_Success) {
6349  auto Size = Operands.size();
6350  AMDGPUOperand &Op = static_cast<AMDGPUOperand &>(*Operands[Size - 2]);
6351  assert(Op.isImm() && Op.getImmTy() == AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyFORMAT);
6352  Op.setImm(Format);
6353  }
6354  return MatchOperand_Success;
6355  }
6356 
6357  if (isId("format") && peekToken().is(AsmToken::Colon)) {
6358  Error(getLoc(), "duplicate format");
6359  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6360  }
6361  return MatchOperand_Success;
6362 }
6363 
6364 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseFlatOffset(OperandVector &Operands) {
6365  OperandMatchResultTy Res =
6366  parseIntWithPrefix("offset", Operands, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOffset);
6367  if (Res == MatchOperand_NoMatch) {
6368  Res = parseIntWithPrefix("inst_offset", Operands,
6369  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyInstOffset);
6370  }
6371  return Res;
6372 }
6373 
6374 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseR128A16(OperandVector &Operands) {
6375  OperandMatchResultTy Res =
6376  parseNamedBit("r128", Operands, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyR128A16);
6377  if (Res == MatchOperand_NoMatch)
6378  Res = parseNamedBit("a16", Operands, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyA16);
6379  return Res;
6380 }

6382 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6383 // ds
6384 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6385 
6386 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtDSOffset01(MCInst &Inst,
6387  const OperandVector &Operands) {
6388  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
6389 
6390  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
6391  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
6392 
6393  // Add the register arguments
6394  if (Op.isReg()) {
6395  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
6396  continue;
6397  }
6398 
6399  // Handle optional arguments
6400  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = i;
6401  }
6402 
6403  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOffset0);
6404  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOffset1);
6405  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyGDS);
6406 
6407  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AMDGPU::M0)); // m0
6408 }
6409 
6410 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtDSImpl(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands,
6411  bool IsGdsHardcoded) {
6412  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
6413  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
6414  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTy OffsetType = AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOffset;
6415 
6416  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
6417  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
6418 
6419  auto TiedTo =
6420  Desc.getOperandConstraint(Inst.getNumOperands(), MCOI::TIED_TO);
6421 
6422  if (TiedTo != -1) {
6423  assert((unsigned)TiedTo < Inst.getNumOperands());
6424  Inst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(TiedTo));
6425  }
6426 
6427  // Add the register arguments
6428  if (Op.isReg()) {
6429  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
6430  continue;
6431  }
6432 
6433  if (Op.isToken() && Op.getToken() == "gds") {
6434  IsGdsHardcoded = true;
6435  continue;
6436  }
6437 
6438  // Handle optional arguments
6439  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = i;
6440 
6441  if (Op.getImmTy() == AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySwizzle)
6442  OffsetType = AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySwizzle;
6443  }
6444 
6445  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, OffsetType);
6446 
6447  if (!IsGdsHardcoded) {
6448  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyGDS);
6449  }
6450  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AMDGPU::M0)); // m0
6451 }
6452 
6453 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtExp(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands) {
6454  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
6455 
6456  unsigned OperandIdx[4];
6457  unsigned EnMask = 0;
6458  int SrcIdx = 0;
6459 
6460  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
6461  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
6462 
6463  // Add the register arguments
6464  if (Op.isReg()) {
6465  assert(SrcIdx < 4);
6466  OperandIdx[SrcIdx] = Inst.size();
6467  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
6468  ++SrcIdx;
6469  continue;
6470  }
6471 
6472  if (Op.isOff()) {
6473  assert(SrcIdx < 4);
6474  OperandIdx[SrcIdx] = Inst.size();
6475  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createReg(AMDGPU::NoRegister));
6476  ++SrcIdx;
6477  continue;
6478  }
6479 
6480  if (Op.isImm() && Op.getImmTy() == AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyExpTgt) {
6481  Op.addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
6482  continue;
6483  }
6484 
6485  if (Op.isToken() && (Op.getToken() == "done" || Op.getToken() == "row_en"))
6486  continue;
6487 
6488  // Handle optional arguments
6489  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = i;
6490  }
6491 
6492  assert(SrcIdx == 4);
6493 
6494  bool Compr = false;
6495  if (OptionalIdx.find(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyExpCompr) != OptionalIdx.end()) {
6496  Compr = true;
6497  Inst.getOperand(OperandIdx[1]) = Inst.getOperand(OperandIdx[2]);
6498  Inst.getOperand(OperandIdx[2]).setReg(AMDGPU::NoRegister);
6499  Inst.getOperand(OperandIdx[3]).setReg(AMDGPU::NoRegister);
6500  }
6501 
6502  for (auto i = 0; i < SrcIdx; ++i) {
6503  if (Inst.getOperand(OperandIdx[i]).getReg() != AMDGPU::NoRegister) {
6504  EnMask |= Compr? (0x3 << i * 2) : (0x1 << i);
6505  }
6506  }
6507 
6508  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyExpVM);
6509  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyExpCompr);
6510 
6511  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(EnMask));
6512 }
6513 
6514 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6515 // s_waitcnt
6516 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6517 
6518 static bool
6519 encodeCnt(
6520  const AMDGPU::IsaVersion ISA,
6521  int64_t &IntVal,
6522  int64_t CntVal,
6523  bool Saturate,
6524  unsigned (*encode)(const IsaVersion &Version, unsigned, unsigned),
6525  unsigned (*decode)(const IsaVersion &Version, unsigned))
6526 {
6527  bool Failed = false;
6528 
6529  IntVal = encode(ISA, IntVal, CntVal);
6530  if (CntVal != decode(ISA, IntVal)) {
6531  if (Saturate) {
6532  IntVal = encode(ISA, IntVal, -1);
6533  } else {
6534  Failed = true;
6535  }
6536  }
6537  return Failed;
6538 }
6539 
6540 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::parseCnt(int64_t &IntVal) {
6541 
6542  SMLoc CntLoc = getLoc();
6543  StringRef CntName = getTokenStr();
6544 
6545  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::Identifier, "expected a counter name") ||
6546  !skipToken(AsmToken::LParen, "expected a left parenthesis"))
6547  return false;
6548 
6549  int64_t CntVal;
6550  SMLoc ValLoc = getLoc();
6551  if (!parseExpr(CntVal))
6552  return false;
6553 
6554  AMDGPU::IsaVersion ISA = AMDGPU::getIsaVersion(getSTI().getCPU());
6555 
6556  bool Failed = true;
6557  bool Sat = CntName.endswith("_sat");
6558 
6559  if (CntName == "vmcnt" || CntName == "vmcnt_sat") {
6560  Failed = encodeCnt(ISA, IntVal, CntVal, Sat, encodeVmcnt, decodeVmcnt);
6561  } else if (CntName == "expcnt" || CntName == "expcnt_sat") {
6562  Failed = encodeCnt(ISA, IntVal, CntVal, Sat, encodeExpcnt, decodeExpcnt);
6563  } else if (CntName == "lgkmcnt" || CntName == "lgkmcnt_sat") {
6564  Failed = encodeCnt(ISA, IntVal, CntVal, Sat, encodeLgkmcnt, decodeLgkmcnt);
6565  } else {
6566  Error(CntLoc, "invalid counter name " + CntName);
6567  return false;
6568  }
6569 
6570  if (Failed) {
6571  Error(ValLoc, "too large value for " + CntName);
6572  return false;
6573  }
6574 
6575  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected a closing parenthesis"))
6576  return false;
6577 
6578  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::Amp) || trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
6579  if (isToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6580  Error(getLoc(), "expected a counter name");
6581  return false;
6582  }
6583  }
6584 
6585  return true;
6586 }
6587 
6588 OperandMatchResultTy
6589 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSWaitCntOps(OperandVector &Operands) {
6590  AMDGPU::IsaVersion ISA = AMDGPU::getIsaVersion(getSTI().getCPU());
6591  int64_t Waitcnt = getWaitcntBitMask(ISA);
6592  SMLoc S = getLoc();
6593 
6594  if (isToken(AsmToken::Identifier) && peekToken().is(AsmToken::LParen)) {
6595  while (!isToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6596  if (!parseCnt(Waitcnt))
6597  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6598  }
6599  } else {
6600  if (!parseExpr(Waitcnt))
6601  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6602  }
6603 
6604  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Waitcnt, S));
6605  return MatchOperand_Success;
6606 }
6607 
6608 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::parseDelay(int64_t &Delay) {
6609  SMLoc FieldLoc = getLoc();
6610  StringRef FieldName = getTokenStr();
6611  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::Identifier, "expected a field name") ||
6612  !skipToken(AsmToken::LParen, "expected a left parenthesis"))
6613  return false;
6614 
6615  SMLoc ValueLoc = getLoc();
6616  StringRef ValueName = getTokenStr();
6617  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::Identifier, "expected a value name") ||
6618  !skipToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected a right parenthesis"))
6619  return false;
6620 
6621  unsigned Shift;
6622  if (FieldName == "instid0") {
6623  Shift = 0;
6624  } else if (FieldName == "instskip") {
6625  Shift = 4;
6626  } else if (FieldName == "instid1") {
6627  Shift = 7;
6628  } else {
6629  Error(FieldLoc, "invalid field name " + FieldName);
6630  return false;
6631  }
6632 
6633  int Value;
6634  if (Shift == 4) {
6635  // Parse values for instskip.
6636  Value = StringSwitch<int>(ValueName)
6637  .Case("SAME", 0)
6638  .Case("NEXT", 1)
6639  .Case("SKIP_1", 2)
6640  .Case("SKIP_2", 3)
6641  .Case("SKIP_3", 4)
6642  .Case("SKIP_4", 5)
6643  .Default(-1);
6644  } else {
6645  // Parse values for instid0 and instid1.
6646  Value = StringSwitch<int>(ValueName)
6647  .Case("NO_DEP", 0)
6648  .Case("VALU_DEP_1", 1)
6649  .Case("VALU_DEP_2", 2)
6650  .Case("VALU_DEP_3", 3)
6651  .Case("VALU_DEP_4", 4)
6652  .Case("TRANS32_DEP_1", 5)
6653  .Case("TRANS32_DEP_2", 6)
6654  .Case("TRANS32_DEP_3", 7)
6655  .Case("FMA_ACCUM_CYCLE_1", 8)
6656  .Case("SALU_CYCLE_1", 9)
6657  .Case("SALU_CYCLE_2", 10)
6658  .Case("SALU_CYCLE_3", 11)
6659  .Default(-1);
6660  }
6661  if (Value < 0) {
6662  Error(ValueLoc, "invalid value name " + ValueName);
6663  return false;
6664  }
6665 
6666  Delay |= Value << Shift;
6667  return true;
6668 }
6669 
6670 OperandMatchResultTy
6671 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSDelayAluOps(OperandVector &Operands) {
6672  int64_t Delay = 0;
6673  SMLoc S = getLoc();
6674 
6675  if (isToken(AsmToken::Identifier) && peekToken().is(AsmToken::LParen)) {
6676  do {
6677  if (!parseDelay(Delay))
6678  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6679  } while (trySkipToken(AsmToken::Pipe));
6680  } else {
6681  if (!parseExpr(Delay))
6682  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6683  }
6684 
6685  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Delay, S));
6686  return MatchOperand_Success;
6687 }

6690 AMDGPUOperand::isSWaitCnt() const {

6692 }
6693 
6694 bool AMDGPUOperand::isSDelayAlu() const { return isImm(); }

6696 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6697 // DepCtr
6698 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6699 
6700 void AMDGPUAsmParser::depCtrError(SMLoc Loc, int ErrorId,
6701  StringRef DepCtrName) {
6702  switch (ErrorId) {
6703  case OPR_ID_UNKNOWN:
6704  Error(Loc, Twine("invalid counter name ", DepCtrName));
6705  return;
6706  case OPR_ID_UNSUPPORTED:
6707  Error(Loc, Twine(DepCtrName, " is not supported on this GPU"));
6708  return;
6709  case OPR_ID_DUPLICATE:
6710  Error(Loc, Twine("duplicate counter name ", DepCtrName));
6711  return;
6712  case OPR_VAL_INVALID:
6713  Error(Loc, Twine("invalid value for ", DepCtrName));
6714  return;
6715  default:
6716  assert(false);
6717  }
6718 }
6719 
6720 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::parseDepCtr(int64_t &DepCtr, unsigned &UsedOprMask) {
6721 
6722  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::DepCtr;
6723 
6724  SMLoc DepCtrLoc = getLoc();
6725  StringRef DepCtrName = getTokenStr();
6726 
6727  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::Identifier, "expected a counter name") ||
6728  !skipToken(AsmToken::LParen, "expected a left parenthesis"))
6729  return false;
6730 
6731  int64_t ExprVal;
6732  if (!parseExpr(ExprVal))
6733  return false;
6734 
6735  unsigned PrevOprMask = UsedOprMask;
6736  int CntVal = encodeDepCtr(DepCtrName, ExprVal, UsedOprMask, getSTI());
6737 
6738  if (CntVal < 0) {
6739  depCtrError(DepCtrLoc, CntVal, DepCtrName);
6740  return false;
6741  }
6742 
6743  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected a closing parenthesis"))
6744  return false;
6745 
6746  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::Amp) || trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
6747  if (isToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6748  Error(getLoc(), "expected a counter name");
6749  return false;
6750  }
6751  }
6752 
6753  unsigned CntValMask = PrevOprMask ^ UsedOprMask;
6754  DepCtr = (DepCtr & ~CntValMask) | CntVal;
6755  return true;
6756 }
6757 
6758 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseDepCtrOps(OperandVector &Operands) {
6759  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::DepCtr;
6760 
6761  int64_t DepCtr = getDefaultDepCtrEncoding(getSTI());
6762  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
6763 
6764  if (isToken(AsmToken::Identifier) && peekToken().is(AsmToken::LParen)) {
6765  unsigned UsedOprMask = 0;
6766  while (!isToken(AsmToken::EndOfStatement)) {
6767  if (!parseDepCtr(DepCtr, UsedOprMask))
6768  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6769  }
6770  } else {
6771  if (!parseExpr(DepCtr))
6772  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6773  }
6774 
6775  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, DepCtr, Loc));
6776  return MatchOperand_Success;
6777 }

6781 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6782 // hwreg
6783 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6784 
6785 bool
6786 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseHwregBody(OperandInfoTy &HwReg,
6787  OperandInfoTy &Offset,
6788  OperandInfoTy &Width) {
6789  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::Hwreg;
6790 
6791  // The register may be specified by name or using a numeric code
6792  HwReg.Loc = getLoc();
6793  if (isToken(AsmToken::Identifier) &&
6794  (HwReg.Id = getHwregId(getTokenStr(), getSTI())) != OPR_ID_UNKNOWN) {
6795  HwReg.IsSymbolic = true;
6796  lex(); // skip register name
6797  } else if (!parseExpr(HwReg.Id, "a register name")) {
6798  return false;
6799  }
6800 
6801  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::RParen))
6802  return true;
6803 
6804  // parse optional params
6805  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected a comma or a closing parenthesis"))
6806  return false;
6807 
6808  Offset.Loc = getLoc();
6809  if (!parseExpr(Offset.Id))
6810  return false;
6811 
6812  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected a comma"))
6813  return false;
6814 
6815  Width.Loc = getLoc();
6816  return parseExpr(Width.Id) &&
6817  skipToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected a closing parenthesis");
6818 }
6819 
6820 bool
6821 AMDGPUAsmParser::validateHwreg(const OperandInfoTy &HwReg,
6822  const OperandInfoTy &Offset,
6823  const OperandInfoTy &Width) {
6824 
6825  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::Hwreg;
6826 
6827  if (HwReg.IsSymbolic) {
6828  if (HwReg.Id == OPR_ID_UNSUPPORTED) {
6829  Error(HwReg.Loc,
6830  "specified hardware register is not supported on this GPU");
6831  return false;
6832  }
6833  } else {
6834  if (!isValidHwreg(HwReg.Id)) {
6835  Error(HwReg.Loc,
6836  "invalid code of hardware register: only 6-bit values are legal");
6837  return false;
6838  }
6839  }
6840  if (!isValidHwregOffset(Offset.Id)) {
6841  Error(Offset.Loc, "invalid bit offset: only 5-bit values are legal");
6842  return false;
6843  }
6844  if (!isValidHwregWidth(Width.Id)) {
6845  Error(Width.Loc,
6846  "invalid bitfield width: only values from 1 to 32 are legal");
6847  return false;
6848  }
6849  return true;
6850 }
6851 
6852 OperandMatchResultTy
6853 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseHwreg(OperandVector &Operands) {
6854  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::Hwreg;
6855 
6856  int64_t ImmVal = 0;
6857  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
6858 
6859  if (trySkipId("hwreg", AsmToken::LParen)) {
6860  OperandInfoTy HwReg(OPR_ID_UNKNOWN);
6861  OperandInfoTy Offset(OFFSET_DEFAULT_);
6862  OperandInfoTy Width(WIDTH_DEFAULT_);
6863  if (parseHwregBody(HwReg, Offset, Width) &&
6864  validateHwreg(HwReg, Offset, Width)) {
6865  ImmVal = encodeHwreg(HwReg.Id, Offset.Id, Width.Id);
6866  } else {
6867  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6868  }
6869  } else if (parseExpr(ImmVal, "a hwreg macro")) {
6870  if (ImmVal < 0 || !isUInt<16>(ImmVal)) {
6871  Error(Loc, "invalid immediate: only 16-bit values are legal");
6872  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6873  }
6874  } else {
6875  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6876  }
6877 
6878  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, ImmVal, Loc, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyHwreg));
6879  return MatchOperand_Success;
6880 }
6881 
6882 bool AMDGPUOperand::isHwreg() const {
6883  return isImmTy(ImmTyHwreg);
6884 }

6886 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6887 // sendmsg
6888 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
6889 
6890 bool
6891 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSendMsgBody(OperandInfoTy &Msg,
6892  OperandInfoTy &Op,
6893  OperandInfoTy &Stream) {
6894  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::SendMsg;
6895 
6896  Msg.Loc = getLoc();
6897  if (isToken(AsmToken::Identifier) &&
6898  (Msg.Id = getMsgId(getTokenStr(), getSTI())) != OPR_ID_UNKNOWN) {
6899  Msg.IsSymbolic = true;
6900  lex(); // skip message name
6901  } else if (!parseExpr(Msg.Id, "a message name")) {
6902  return false;
6903  }
6904 
6905  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
6906  Op.IsDefined = true;
6907  Op.Loc = getLoc();
6908  if (isToken(AsmToken::Identifier) &&
6909  (Op.Id = getMsgOpId(Msg.Id, getTokenStr())) >= 0) {
6910  lex(); // skip operation name
6911  } else if (!parseExpr(Op.Id, "an operation name")) {
6912  return false;
6913  }
6914 
6915  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::Comma)) {
6916  Stream.IsDefined = true;
6917  Stream.Loc = getLoc();
6918  if (!parseExpr(Stream.Id))
6919  return false;
6920  }
6921  }
6922 
6923  return skipToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected a closing parenthesis");
6924 }
6925 
6926 bool
6927 AMDGPUAsmParser::validateSendMsg(const OperandInfoTy &Msg,
6928  const OperandInfoTy &Op,
6929  const OperandInfoTy &Stream) {
6930  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::SendMsg;
6931 
6932  // Validation strictness depends on whether message is specified
6933  // in a symbolic or in a numeric form. In the latter case
6934  // only encoding possibility is checked.
6935  bool Strict = Msg.IsSymbolic;
6936 
6937  if (Strict) {
6938  if (Msg.Id == OPR_ID_UNSUPPORTED) {
6939  Error(Msg.Loc, "specified message id is not supported on this GPU");
6940  return false;
6941  }
6942  } else {
6943  if (!isValidMsgId(Msg.Id, getSTI())) {
6944  Error(Msg.Loc, "invalid message id");
6945  return false;
6946  }
6947  }
6948  if (Strict && (msgRequiresOp(Msg.Id, getSTI()) != Op.IsDefined)) {
6949  if (Op.IsDefined) {
6950  Error(Op.Loc, "message does not support operations");
6951  } else {
6952  Error(Msg.Loc, "missing message operation");
6953  }
6954  return false;
6955  }
6956  if (!isValidMsgOp(Msg.Id, Op.Id, getSTI(), Strict)) {
6957  Error(Op.Loc, "invalid operation id");
6958  return false;
6959  }
6960  if (Strict && !msgSupportsStream(Msg.Id, Op.Id, getSTI()) &&
6961  Stream.IsDefined) {
6962  Error(Stream.Loc, "message operation does not support streams");
6963  return false;
6964  }
6965  if (!isValidMsgStream(Msg.Id, Op.Id, Stream.Id, getSTI(), Strict)) {
6966  Error(Stream.Loc, "invalid message stream id");
6967  return false;
6968  }
6969  return true;
6970 }
6971 
6972 OperandMatchResultTy
6973 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSendMsgOp(OperandVector &Operands) {
6974  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::SendMsg;
6975 
6976  int64_t ImmVal = 0;
6977  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
6978 
6979  if (trySkipId("sendmsg", AsmToken::LParen)) {
6980  OperandInfoTy Msg(OPR_ID_UNKNOWN);
6981  OperandInfoTy Op(OP_NONE_);
6982  OperandInfoTy Stream(STREAM_ID_NONE_);
6983  if (parseSendMsgBody(Msg, Op, Stream) &&
6984  validateSendMsg(Msg, Op, Stream)) {
6985  ImmVal = encodeMsg(Msg.Id, Op.Id, Stream.Id);
6986  } else {
6987  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6988  }
6989  } else if (parseExpr(ImmVal, "a sendmsg macro")) {
6990  if (ImmVal < 0 || !isUInt<16>(ImmVal)) {
6991  Error(Loc, "invalid immediate: only 16-bit values are legal");
6992  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6993  }
6994  } else {
6995  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
6996  }
6997 
6998  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, ImmVal, Loc, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySendMsg));
6999  return MatchOperand_Success;
7000 }
7001 
7002 bool AMDGPUOperand::isSendMsg() const {
7003  return isImmTy(ImmTySendMsg);
7004 }
7005 
7006 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7007 // v_interp
7008 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7009 
7010 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseInterpSlot(OperandVector &Operands) {
7011  StringRef Str;
7012  SMLoc S = getLoc();
7013 
7014  if (!parseId(Str))
7015  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
7016 
7017  int Slot = StringSwitch<int>(Str)
7018  .Case("p10", 0)
7019  .Case("p20", 1)
7020  .Case("p0", 2)
7021  .Default(-1);
7022 
7023  if (Slot == -1) {
7024  Error(S, "invalid interpolation slot");
7025  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
7026  }
7027 
7028  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Slot, S,
7029  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyInterpSlot));
7030  return MatchOperand_Success;
7031 }
7032 
7033 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseInterpAttr(OperandVector &Operands) {
7034  StringRef Str;
7035  SMLoc S = getLoc();
7036 
7037  if (!parseId(Str))
7038  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
7039 
7040  if (!Str.startswith("attr")) {
7041  Error(S, "invalid interpolation attribute");
7042  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
7043  }
7044 
7045  StringRef Chan = Str.take_back(2);
7046  int AttrChan = StringSwitch<int>(Chan)
7047  .Case(".x", 0)
7048  .Case(".y", 1)
7049  .Case(".z", 2)
7050  .Case(".w", 3)
7051  .Default(-1);
7052  if (AttrChan == -1) {
7053  Error(S, "invalid or missing interpolation attribute channel");
7054  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
7055  }
7056 
7057  Str = Str.drop_back(2).drop_front(4);
7058 
7059  uint8_t Attr;
7060  if (Str.getAsInteger(10, Attr)) {
7061  Error(S, "invalid or missing interpolation attribute number");
7062  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
7063  }
7064 
7065  if (Attr > 63) {
7066  Error(S, "out of bounds interpolation attribute number");
7067  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
7068  }
7069 
7070  SMLoc SChan = SMLoc::getFromPointer(Chan.data());
7071 
7072  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Attr, S,
7073  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyInterpAttr));
7074  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, AttrChan, SChan,
7075  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyAttrChan));
7076  return MatchOperand_Success;
7077 }
7078 
7079 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7080 // exp
7081 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7082 
7083 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseExpTgt(OperandVector &Operands) {
7084  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::Exp;
7085 
7086  StringRef Str;
7087  SMLoc S = getLoc();
7088 
7089  if (!parseId(Str))
7090  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
7091 
7092  unsigned Id = getTgtId(Str);
7093  if (Id == ET_INVALID || !isSupportedTgtId(Id, getSTI())) {
7094  Error(S, (Id == ET_INVALID) ?
7095  "invalid exp target" :
7096  "exp target is not supported on this GPU");
7097  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
7098  }
7099 
7100  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Id, S,
7101  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyExpTgt));
7102  return MatchOperand_Success;
7103 }

7128 bool

7130  if (isId(Id)) {
7131  lex();
7132  return true;
7133  }
7134  return false;

7137 bool
7138 AMDGPUAsmParser::trySkipId(const StringRef Pref, const StringRef Id) {
7139  if (isToken(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
7140  StringRef Tok = getTokenStr();
7141  if (Tok.startswith(Pref) && Tok.drop_front(Pref.size()) == Id) {
7142  lex();
7143  return true;
7144  }
7145  }
7146  return false;
7147 }

7149 bool
7150 AMDGPUAsmParser::trySkipId(const StringRef Id, const AsmToken::TokenKind Kind) {
7151  if (isId(Id) && peekToken().is(Kind)) {
7152  lex();
7153  lex();
7154  return true;
7155  }
7156  return false;
7157 }

7159 bool
7160 AMDGPUAsmParser::trySkipToken(const AsmToken::TokenKind Kind) {
7161  if (isToken(Kind)) {
7162  lex();
7163  return true;
7164  }
7165  return false;
7166 }

7168 bool
7169 AMDGPUAsmParser::skipToken(const AsmToken::TokenKind Kind,
7170  const StringRef ErrMsg) {
7171  if (!trySkipToken(Kind)) {
7172  Error(getLoc(), ErrMsg);
7173  return false;

7175  return true;

7178 bool
7179 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseExpr(int64_t &Imm, StringRef Expected) {
7180  SMLoc S = getLoc();
7181 
7182  const MCExpr *Expr;
7183  if (Parser.parseExpression(Expr))
7184  return false;
7185 
7186  if (Expr->evaluateAsAbsolute(Imm))
7187  return true;
7188 
7189  if (Expected.empty()) {
7190  Error(S, "expected absolute expression");
7191  } else {
7192  Error(S, Twine("expected ", Expected) +
7193  Twine(" or an absolute expression"));
7194  }
7195  return false;
7196 }
7197 
7198 bool
7199 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseExpr(OperandVector &Operands) {
7200  SMLoc S = getLoc();
7201 
7202  const MCExpr *Expr;
7203  if (Parser.parseExpression(Expr))
7204  return false;
7205 
7206  int64_t IntVal;
7207  if (Expr->evaluateAsAbsolute(IntVal)) {
7208  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, IntVal, S));
7209  } else {
7210  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateExpr(this, Expr, S));
7211  }
7212  return true;
7213 }

7215 bool
7216 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseString(StringRef &Val, const StringRef ErrMsg) {
7217  if (isToken(AsmToken::String)) {
7218  Val = getToken().getStringContents();
7219  lex();
7220  return true;
7221  } else {
7222  Error(getLoc(), ErrMsg);
7223  return false;
7224  }
7225 }
7226 
7227 bool
7228 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseId(StringRef &Val, const StringRef ErrMsg) {
7229  if (isToken(AsmToken::Identifier)) {
7230  Val = getTokenStr();
7231  lex();
7232  return true;
7233  } else {
7234  if (!ErrMsg.empty())
7235  Error(getLoc(), ErrMsg);
7236  return false;
7237  }
7238 }

7247  ? getToken()
7248  : getLexer().peekTok(ShouldSkipSpace);

7251 void
7252 AMDGPUAsmParser::peekTokens(MutableArrayRef<AsmToken> Tokens) {
7253  auto TokCount = getLexer().peekTokens(Tokens);
7254 
7255  for (auto Idx = TokCount; Idx < Tokens.size(); ++Idx)
7256  Tokens[Idx] = AsmToken(AsmToken::Error, "");
7257 }

7283 SMLoc
7284 AMDGPUAsmParser::getOperandLoc(std::function<bool(const AMDGPUOperand&)> Test,
7285  const OperandVector &Operands) const {
7286  for (unsigned i = Operands.size() - 1; i > 0; --i) {
7287  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
7288  if (Test(Op))
7289  return Op.getStartLoc();
7290  }
7291  return getInstLoc(Operands);
7292 }

7295 AMDGPUAsmParser::getImmLoc(AMDGPUOperand::ImmTy Type,
7296  const OperandVector &Operands) const {
7297  auto Test = [=](const AMDGPUOperand& Op) { return Op.isImmTy(Type); };
7298  return getOperandLoc(Test, Operands);
7299 }

7302 AMDGPUAsmParser::getRegLoc(unsigned Reg,

7304  auto Test = [=](const AMDGPUOperand& Op) {
7305  return Op.isRegKind() && Op.getReg() == Reg;
7306  };

7308 }
7309 
7310 SMLoc AMDGPUAsmParser::getLitLoc(const OperandVector &Operands,
7311  bool SearchMandatoryLiterals) const {
7312  auto Test = [](const AMDGPUOperand& Op) {
7313  return Op.IsImmKindLiteral() || Op.isExpr();
7314  };
7315  SMLoc Loc = getOperandLoc(Test, Operands);
7316  if (SearchMandatoryLiterals && Loc == getInstLoc(Operands))
7317  Loc = getMandatoryLitLoc(Operands);
7318  return Loc;
7319 }
7320 
7321 SMLoc AMDGPUAsmParser::getMandatoryLitLoc(const OperandVector &Operands) const {
7322  auto Test = [](const AMDGPUOperand &Op) {
7323  return Op.IsImmKindMandatoryLiteral();
7324  };
7325  return getOperandLoc(Test, Operands);
7326 }

7328 SMLoc
7329 AMDGPUAsmParser::getConstLoc(const OperandVector &Operands) const {
7330  auto Test = [](const AMDGPUOperand& Op) {
7331  return Op.isImmKindConst();
7332  };
7333  return getOperandLoc(Test, Operands);
7334 }

7336 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7337 // swizzle
7338 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7339 
7340 LLVM_READNONE
7341 static unsigned
7342 encodeBitmaskPerm(const unsigned AndMask,
7343  const unsigned OrMask,
7344  const unsigned XorMask) {
7345  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::Swizzle;
7346 
7347  return BITMASK_PERM_ENC |
7348  (AndMask << BITMASK_AND_SHIFT) |
7349  (OrMask << BITMASK_OR_SHIFT) |
7350  (XorMask << BITMASK_XOR_SHIFT);
7351 }
7352 
7353 bool
7354 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSwizzleOperand(int64_t &Op,
7355  const unsigned MinVal,
7356  const unsigned MaxVal,
7357  const StringRef ErrMsg,
7358  SMLoc &Loc) {
7359  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected a comma")) {
7360  return false;
7361  }
7362  Loc = getLoc();
7363  if (!parseExpr(Op)) {
7364  return false;
7365  }
7366  if (Op < MinVal || Op > MaxVal) {
7367  Error(Loc, ErrMsg);
7368  return false;
7369  }
7370 
7371  return true;
7372 }
7373 
7374 bool
7375 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSwizzleOperands(const unsigned OpNum, int64_t* Op,
7376  const unsigned MinVal,
7377  const unsigned MaxVal,
7378  const StringRef ErrMsg) {
7379  SMLoc Loc;
7380  for (unsigned i = 0; i < OpNum; ++i) {
7381  if (!parseSwizzleOperand(Op[i], MinVal, MaxVal, ErrMsg, Loc))
7382  return false;
7383  }
7384 
7385  return true;
7386 }
7387 
7388 bool
7389 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSwizzleQuadPerm(int64_t &Imm) {
7390  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::Swizzle;
7391 
7392  int64_t Lane[LANE_NUM];
7393  if (parseSwizzleOperands(LANE_NUM, Lane, 0, LANE_MAX,
7394  "expected a 2-bit lane id")) {
7395  Imm = QUAD_PERM_ENC;
7396  for (unsigned I = 0; I < LANE_NUM; ++I) {
7397  Imm |= Lane[I] << (LANE_SHIFT * I);
7398  }
7399  return true;
7400  }
7401  return false;
7402 }
7403 
7404 bool
7405 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSwizzleBroadcast(int64_t &Imm) {
7406  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::Swizzle;
7407 
7408  SMLoc Loc;
7409  int64_t GroupSize;
7410  int64_t LaneIdx;
7411 
7412  if (!parseSwizzleOperand(GroupSize,
7413  2, 32,
7414  "group size must be in the interval [2,32]",
7415  Loc)) {
7416  return false;
7417  }
7418  if (!isPowerOf2_64(GroupSize)) {
7419  Error(Loc, "group size must be a power of two");
7420  return false;
7421  }
7422  if (parseSwizzleOperand(LaneIdx,
7423  0, GroupSize - 1,
7424  "lane id must be in the interval [0,group size - 1]",
7425  Loc)) {
7426  Imm = encodeBitmaskPerm(BITMASK_MAX - GroupSize + 1, LaneIdx, 0);
7427  return true;
7428  }
7429  return false;
7430 }
7431 
7432 bool
7433 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSwizzleReverse(int64_t &Imm) {
7434  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::Swizzle;
7435 
7436  SMLoc Loc;
7437  int64_t GroupSize;
7438 
7439  if (!parseSwizzleOperand(GroupSize,
7440  2, 32,
7441  "group size must be in the interval [2,32]",
7442  Loc)) {
7443  return false;
7444  }
7445  if (!isPowerOf2_64(GroupSize)) {
7446  Error(Loc, "group size must be a power of two");
7447  return false;
7448  }
7449 
7450  Imm = encodeBitmaskPerm(BITMASK_MAX, 0, GroupSize - 1);
7451  return true;
7452 }
7453 
7454 bool
7455 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSwizzleSwap(int64_t &Imm) {
7456  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::Swizzle;
7457 
7458  SMLoc Loc;
7459  int64_t GroupSize;
7460 
7461  if (!parseSwizzleOperand(GroupSize,
7462  1, 16,
7463  "group size must be in the interval [1,16]",
7464  Loc)) {
7465  return false;
7466  }
7467  if (!isPowerOf2_64(GroupSize)) {
7468  Error(Loc, "group size must be a power of two");
7469  return false;
7470  }
7471 
7472  Imm = encodeBitmaskPerm(BITMASK_MAX, 0, GroupSize);
7473  return true;
7474 }
7475 
7476 bool
7477 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSwizzleBitmaskPerm(int64_t &Imm) {
7478  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::Swizzle;
7479 
7480  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected a comma")) {
7481  return false;
7482  }
7483 
7484  StringRef Ctl;
7485  SMLoc StrLoc = getLoc();
7486  if (!parseString(Ctl)) {
7487  return false;
7488  }
7489  if (Ctl.size() != BITMASK_WIDTH) {
7490  Error(StrLoc, "expected a 5-character mask");
7491  return false;
7492  }
7493 
7494  unsigned AndMask = 0;
7495  unsigned OrMask = 0;
7496  unsigned XorMask = 0;
7497 
7498  for (size_t i = 0; i < Ctl.size(); ++i) {
7499  unsigned Mask = 1 << (BITMASK_WIDTH - 1 - i);
7500  switch(Ctl[i]) {
7501  default:
7502  Error(StrLoc, "invalid mask");
7503  return false;
7504  case '0':
7505  break;
7506  case '1':
7507  OrMask |= Mask;
7508  break;
7509  case 'p':
7510  AndMask |= Mask;
7511  break;
7512  case 'i':
7513  AndMask |= Mask;
7514  XorMask |= Mask;
7515  break;
7516  }
7517  }
7518 
7519  Imm = encodeBitmaskPerm(AndMask, OrMask, XorMask);
7520  return true;
7521 }
7522 
7523 bool
7524 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSwizzleOffset(int64_t &Imm) {
7525 
7526  SMLoc OffsetLoc = getLoc();
7527 
7528  if (!parseExpr(Imm, "a swizzle macro")) {
7529  return false;
7530  }
7531  if (!isUInt<16>(Imm)) {
7532  Error(OffsetLoc, "expected a 16-bit offset");
7533  return false;
7534  }
7535  return true;
7536 }
7537 
7538 bool
7539 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSwizzleMacro(int64_t &Imm) {
7540  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::Swizzle;
7541 
7542  if (skipToken(AsmToken::LParen, "expected a left parentheses")) {
7543 
7544  SMLoc ModeLoc = getLoc();
7545  bool Ok = false;
7546 
7547  if (trySkipId(IdSymbolic[ID_QUAD_PERM])) {
7548  Ok = parseSwizzleQuadPerm(Imm);
7549  } else if (trySkipId(IdSymbolic[ID_BITMASK_PERM])) {
7550  Ok = parseSwizzleBitmaskPerm(Imm);
7551  } else if (trySkipId(IdSymbolic[ID_BROADCAST])) {
7552  Ok = parseSwizzleBroadcast(Imm);
7553  } else if (trySkipId(IdSymbolic[ID_SWAP])) {
7554  Ok = parseSwizzleSwap(Imm);
7555  } else if (trySkipId(IdSymbolic[ID_REVERSE])) {
7556  Ok = parseSwizzleReverse(Imm);
7557  } else {
7558  Error(ModeLoc, "expected a swizzle mode");
7559  }
7560 
7561  return Ok && skipToken(AsmToken::RParen, "expected a closing parentheses");
7562  }
7563 
7564  return false;
7565 }
7566 
7567 OperandMatchResultTy
7568 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSwizzleOp(OperandVector &Operands) {
7569  SMLoc S = getLoc();
7570  int64_t Imm = 0;
7571 
7572  if (trySkipId("offset")) {
7573 
7574  bool Ok = false;
7575  if (skipToken(AsmToken::Colon, "expected a colon")) {
7576  if (trySkipId("swizzle")) {
7577  Ok = parseSwizzleMacro(Imm);
7578  } else {
7579  Ok = parseSwizzleOffset(Imm);
7580  }
7581  }
7582 
7583  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Imm, S, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySwizzle));
7584 
7585  return Ok ? MatchOperand_Success : MatchOperand_ParseFail;
7586  }
7587  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
7588 }
7589 
7590 bool
7591 AMDGPUOperand::isSwizzle() const {
7592  return isImmTy(ImmTySwizzle);
7593 }
7594 
7595 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7596 // VGPR Index Mode
7597 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7598 
7599 int64_t AMDGPUAsmParser::parseGPRIdxMacro() {
7600 
7601  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::VGPRIndexMode;
7602 
7603  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::RParen)) {
7604  return OFF;
7605  }
7606 
7607  int64_t Imm = 0;
7608 
7609  while (true) {
7610  unsigned Mode = 0;
7611  SMLoc S = getLoc();
7612 
7613  for (unsigned ModeId = ID_MIN; ModeId <= ID_MAX; ++ModeId) {
7614  if (trySkipId(IdSymbolic[ModeId])) {
7615  Mode = 1 << ModeId;
7616  break;
7617  }
7618  }
7619 
7620  if (Mode == 0) {
7621  Error(S, (Imm == 0)?
7622  "expected a VGPR index mode or a closing parenthesis" :
7623  "expected a VGPR index mode");
7624  return UNDEF;
7625  }
7626 
7627  if (Imm & Mode) {
7628  Error(S, "duplicate VGPR index mode");
7629  return UNDEF;
7630  }
7631  Imm |= Mode;
7632 
7633  if (trySkipToken(AsmToken::RParen))
7634  break;
7635  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::Comma,
7636  "expected a comma or a closing parenthesis"))
7637  return UNDEF;
7638  }
7639 
7640  return Imm;
7641 }
7642 
7643 OperandMatchResultTy
7644 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseGPRIdxMode(OperandVector &Operands) {
7645 
7646  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::VGPRIndexMode;
7647 
7648  int64_t Imm = 0;
7649  SMLoc S = getLoc();
7650 
7651  if (trySkipId("gpr_idx", AsmToken::LParen)) {
7652  Imm = parseGPRIdxMacro();
7653  if (Imm == UNDEF)
7654  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
7655  } else {
7656  if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(Imm))
7657  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
7658  if (Imm < 0 || !isUInt<4>(Imm)) {
7659  Error(S, "invalid immediate: only 4-bit values are legal");
7660  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
7661  }
7662  }
7663 
7664  Operands.push_back(
7665  AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Imm, S, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyGprIdxMode));
7666  return MatchOperand_Success;
7667 }
7668 
7669 bool AMDGPUOperand::isGPRIdxMode() const {
7670  return isImmTy(ImmTyGprIdxMode);
7671 }
7672 
7673 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7674 // sopp branch targets
7675 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7676 
7677 OperandMatchResultTy
7678 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSOppBrTarget(OperandVector &Operands) {
7679 
7680  // Make sure we are not parsing something
7681  // that looks like a label or an expression but is not.
7682  // This will improve error messages.
7683  if (isRegister() || isModifier())
7684  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
7685 
7686  if (!parseExpr(Operands))
7687  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
7688 
7689  AMDGPUOperand &Opr = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[Operands.size() - 1]);
7690  assert(Opr.isImm() || Opr.isExpr());
7691  SMLoc Loc = Opr.getStartLoc();
7692 
7693  // Currently we do not support arbitrary expressions as branch targets.
7694  // Only labels and absolute expressions are accepted.
7695  if (Opr.isExpr() && !Opr.isSymbolRefExpr()) {
7696  Error(Loc, "expected an absolute expression or a label");
7697  } else if (Opr.isImm() && !Opr.isS16Imm()) {
7698  Error(Loc, "expected a 16-bit signed jump offset");
7699  }
7700 
7701  return MatchOperand_Success;
7702 }

7705 // Boolean holding registers
7706 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7707 
7708 OperandMatchResultTy
7709 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseBoolReg(OperandVector &Operands) {
7710  return parseReg(Operands);
7711 }

7714 // mubuf
7715 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//

7717 AMDGPUOperand::Ptr AMDGPUAsmParser::defaultCPol() const {
7718  return AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, 0, SMLoc(), AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyCPol);
7719 }
7720 
7721 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtMubufImpl(MCInst &Inst,
7722  const OperandVector &Operands,
7723  bool IsAtomic) {
7724  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
7725  unsigned FirstOperandIdx = 1;
7726  bool IsAtomicReturn = false;
7727 
7728  if (IsAtomic) {
7729  for (unsigned i = FirstOperandIdx, e = Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
7730  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
7731  if (!Op.isCPol())
7732  continue;
7733  IsAtomicReturn = Op.getImm() & AMDGPU::CPol::GLC;
7734  break;
7735  }
7736 
7737  if (!IsAtomicReturn) {
7738  int NewOpc = AMDGPU::getAtomicNoRetOp(Inst.getOpcode());
7739  if (NewOpc != -1)
7740  Inst.setOpcode(NewOpc);
7741  }
7742 
7743  IsAtomicReturn = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode()).TSFlags &
7744  SIInstrFlags::IsAtomicRet;
7745  }
7746 
7747  for (unsigned i = FirstOperandIdx, e = Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
7748  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
7749 
7750  // Add the register arguments
7751  if (Op.isReg()) {
7752  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
7753  // Insert a tied src for atomic return dst.
7754  // This cannot be postponed as subsequent calls to
7755  // addImmOperands rely on correct number of MC operands.
7756  if (IsAtomicReturn && i == FirstOperandIdx)
7757  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
7758  continue;
7759  }
7760 
7761  // Handle the case where soffset is an immediate
7762  if (Op.isImm() && Op.getImmTy() == AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyNone) {
7763  Op.addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
7764  continue;
7765  }
7766 
7767  // Handle tokens like 'offen' which are sometimes hard-coded into the
7768  // asm string. There are no MCInst operands for these.
7769  if (Op.isToken()) {
7770  continue;
7771  }
7772  assert(Op.isImm());
7773 
7774  // Handle optional arguments
7775  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = i;
7776  }
7777 
7778  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOffset);
7779  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyCPol, 0);
7780  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySWZ);
7781 }
7782 
7783 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtMtbuf(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands) {
7784  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
7785 
7786  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
7787  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
7788 
7789  // Add the register arguments
7790  if (Op.isReg()) {
7791  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
7792  continue;
7793  }
7794 
7795  // Handle the case where soffset is an immediate
7796  if (Op.isImm() && Op.getImmTy() == AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyNone) {
7797  Op.addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
7798  continue;
7799  }
7800 
7801  // Handle tokens like 'offen' which are sometimes hard-coded into the
7802  // asm string. There are no MCInst operands for these.
7803  if (Op.isToken()) {
7804  continue;
7805  }
7806  assert(Op.isImm());
7807 
7808  // Handle optional arguments
7809  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = i;
7810  }
7811 
7812  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx,
7813  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOffset);
7814  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyFORMAT);
7815  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyCPol, 0);
7816  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySWZ);
7817 }

7819 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7820 // mimg
7821 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
7822 
7823 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtMIMG(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands,
7824  bool IsAtomic) {
7825  unsigned I = 1;
7826  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
7827  for (unsigned J = 0; J < Desc.getNumDefs(); ++J) {
7828  ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I++]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
7829  }
7830 
7831  if (IsAtomic) {
7832  // Add src, same as dst
7833  assert(Desc.getNumDefs() == 1);
7834  ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I - 1]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
7835  }
7836 
7837  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
7838 
7839  for (unsigned E = Operands.size(); I != E; ++I) {
7840  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I]);
7841 
7842  // Add the register arguments
7843  if (Op.isReg()) {
7844  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
7845  } else if (Op.isImmModifier()) {
7846  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = I;
7847  } else if (!Op.isToken()) {
7848  llvm_unreachable("unexpected operand type");
7849  }
7850  }
7851 
7852  bool IsGFX10Plus = isGFX10Plus();
7853 
7854  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDMask);
7855  if (IsGFX10Plus)
7856  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDim, -1);
7857  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyUNorm);
7858  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyCPol);
7859  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyR128A16);
7860  if (IsGFX10Plus)
7861  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyA16);
7862  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Inst.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::tfe))
7863  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyTFE);
7864  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyLWE);
7865  if (!IsGFX10Plus)
7866  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDA);
7867  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyD16);
7868 }
7869 
7870 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtMIMGAtomic(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands) {
7871  cvtMIMG(Inst, Operands, true);
7872 }
7873 
7874 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtSMEMAtomic(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands) {
7875  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
7876  bool IsAtomicReturn = false;
7877 
7878  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
7879  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
7880  if (!Op.isCPol())
7881  continue;
7882  IsAtomicReturn = Op.getImm() & AMDGPU::CPol::GLC;
7883  break;
7884  }
7885 
7886  if (!IsAtomicReturn) {
7887  int NewOpc = AMDGPU::getAtomicNoRetOp(Inst.getOpcode());
7888  if (NewOpc != -1)
7889  Inst.setOpcode(NewOpc);
7890  }
7891 
7892  IsAtomicReturn = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode()).TSFlags &
7893  SIInstrFlags::IsAtomicRet;
7894 
7895  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Operands.size(); i != e; ++i) {
7896  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[i]);
7897 
7898  // Add the register arguments
7899  if (Op.isReg()) {
7900  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
7901  if (IsAtomicReturn && i == 1)
7902  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
7903  continue;
7904  }
7905 
7906  // Handle the case where soffset is an immediate
7907  if (Op.isImm() && Op.getImmTy() == AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyNone) {
7908  Op.addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
7909  continue;
7910  }
7911 
7912  // Handle tokens like 'offen' which are sometimes hard-coded into the
7913  // asm string. There are no MCInst operands for these.
7914  if (Op.isToken()) {
7915  continue;
7916  }
7917  assert(Op.isImm());
7918 
7919  // Handle optional arguments
7920  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = i;
7921  }
7922 
7923  if ((int)Inst.getNumOperands() <=
7924  AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Inst.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::offset))
7925  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOffset);
7926  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyCPol, 0);
7927 }

7929 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtIntersectRay(MCInst &Inst,
7930  const OperandVector &Operands) {
7931  for (unsigned I = 1; I < Operands.size(); ++I) {
7932  auto &Operand = (AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I];
7933  if (Operand.isReg())
7934  Operand.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
7935  }
7936 
7937  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(1)); // a16
7938 }

7979 static bool ConvertOmodMul(int64_t &Mul) {
7980  if (Mul != 1 && Mul != 2 && Mul != 4)
7981  return false;
7982 
7983  Mul >>= 1;
7984  return true;
7985 }
7986 
7987 static bool ConvertOmodDiv(int64_t &Div) {
7988  if (Div == 1) {
7989  Div = 0;
7990  return true;
7991  }
7992 
7993  if (Div == 2) {
7994  Div = 3;
7995  return true;
7996  }
7997 
7998  return false;
7999 }
8000 
8001 // Both bound_ctrl:0 and bound_ctrl:1 are encoded as 1.
8002 // This is intentional and ensures compatibility with sp3.
8003 // See bug 35397 for details.
8004 static bool ConvertDppBoundCtrl(int64_t &BoundCtrl) {
8005  if (BoundCtrl == 0 || BoundCtrl == 1) {
8006  BoundCtrl = 1;
8007  return true;
8008  }
8009  return false;
8010 }

8012 void AMDGPUAsmParser::onBeginOfFile() {
8013  if (!getParser().getStreamer().getTargetStreamer() ||
8014  getSTI().getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::r600)
8015  return;
8016 
8017  if (!getTargetStreamer().getTargetID())
8018  getTargetStreamer().initializeTargetID(getSTI(), getSTI().getFeatureString(),
8019  // TODO: Should try to check code object version from directive???
8020  AMDGPU::getAmdhsaCodeObjectVersion());
8021 
8022  if (isHsaAbiVersion3AndAbove(&getSTI()))
8023  getTargetStreamer().EmitDirectiveAMDGCNTarget();
8024 }

8026 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseOModOperand(OperandVector &Operands) {
8027  StringRef Name = getTokenStr();
8028  if (Name == "mul") {
8029  return parseIntWithPrefix("mul", Operands,
8030  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOModSI, ConvertOmodMul);
8031  }
8032 
8033  if (Name == "div") {
8034  return parseIntWithPrefix("div", Operands,
8035  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOModSI, ConvertOmodDiv);
8036  }
8037 
8038  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
8039 }
8040 
8041 // Determines which bit DST_OP_SEL occupies in the op_sel operand according to
8042 // the number of src operands present, then copies that bit into src0_modifiers.
8043 void cvtVOP3DstOpSelOnly(MCInst &Inst) {
8044  int Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
8045  int OpSelIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::op_sel);
8046  if (OpSelIdx == -1)
8047  return;
8048 
8049  int SrcNum;
8050  const int Ops[] = { AMDGPU::OpName::src0,
8051  AMDGPU::OpName::src1,
8052  AMDGPU::OpName::src2 };
8053  for (SrcNum = 0; SrcNum < 3 && AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, Ops[SrcNum]);
8054  ++SrcNum)
8055  ;
8056  assert(SrcNum > 0);
8057 
8058  unsigned OpSel = Inst.getOperand(OpSelIdx).getImm();
8059 
8060  if ((OpSel & (1 << SrcNum)) != 0) {
8061  int ModIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src0_modifiers);
8062  uint32_t ModVal = Inst.getOperand(ModIdx).getImm();
8063  Inst.getOperand(ModIdx).setImm(ModVal | SISrcMods::DST_OP_SEL);
8064  }
8065 }
8066 
8067 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtVOP3OpSel(MCInst &Inst,
8068  const OperandVector &Operands) {
8069  cvtVOP3P(Inst, Operands);
8070  cvtVOP3DstOpSelOnly(Inst);
8071 }
8072 
8073 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtVOP3OpSel(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands,
8074  OptionalImmIndexMap &OptionalIdx) {
8075  cvtVOP3P(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx);
8076  cvtVOP3DstOpSelOnly(Inst);
8077 }
8078 
8079 static bool isRegOrImmWithInputMods(const MCInstrDesc &Desc, unsigned OpNum) {
8080  return
8081  // 1. This operand is input modifiers
8082  Desc.operands()[OpNum].OperandType == AMDGPU::OPERAND_INPUT_MODS
8083  // 2. This is not last operand
8084  && Desc.NumOperands > (OpNum + 1)
8085  // 3. Next operand is register class
8086  && Desc.operands()[OpNum + 1].RegClass != -1
8087  // 4. Next register is not tied to any other operand
8088  && Desc.getOperandConstraint(OpNum + 1,
8089  MCOI::OperandConstraint::TIED_TO) == -1;
8090 }
8091 
8092 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtVOP3Interp(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands)
8093 {
8094  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
8095  unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
8096 
8097  unsigned I = 1;
8098  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
8099  for (unsigned J = 0; J < Desc.getNumDefs(); ++J) {
8100  ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I++]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
8101  }
8102 
8103  for (unsigned E = Operands.size(); I != E; ++I) {
8104  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I]);
8105  if (isRegOrImmWithInputMods(Desc, Inst.getNumOperands())) {
8106  Op.addRegOrImmWithFPInputModsOperands(Inst, 2);
8107  } else if (Op.isInterpSlot() ||
8108  Op.isInterpAttr() ||
8109  Op.isAttrChan()) {
8110  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Op.getImm()));
8111  } else if (Op.isImmModifier()) {
8112  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = I;
8113  } else {
8114  llvm_unreachable("unhandled operand type");
8115  }
8116  }
8117 
8118  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::high))
8119  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx,
8120  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyHigh);
8121 
8122  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::clamp))
8123  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx,
8124  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyClampSI);
8125 
8126  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::omod))
8127  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx,
8128  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOModSI);
8129 }
8130 
8131 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtVINTERP(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands)
8132 {
8133  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
8134  unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
8135 
8136  unsigned I = 1;
8137  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
8138  for (unsigned J = 0; J < Desc.getNumDefs(); ++J) {
8139  ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I++]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
8140  }
8141 
8142  for (unsigned E = Operands.size(); I != E; ++I) {
8143  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I]);
8144  if (isRegOrImmWithInputMods(Desc, Inst.getNumOperands())) {
8145  Op.addRegOrImmWithFPInputModsOperands(Inst, 2);
8146  } else if (Op.isImmModifier()) {
8147  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = I;
8148  } else {
8149  llvm_unreachable("unhandled operand type");
8150  }
8151  }
8152 
8153  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyClampSI);
8154 
8155  int OpSelIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::op_sel);
8156  if (OpSelIdx != -1)
8157  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOpSel);
8158 
8159  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyWaitEXP);
8160 
8161  if (OpSelIdx == -1)
8162  return;
8163 
8164  const int Ops[] = { AMDGPU::OpName::src0,
8165  AMDGPU::OpName::src1,
8166  AMDGPU::OpName::src2 };
8167  const int ModOps[] = { AMDGPU::OpName::src0_modifiers,
8168  AMDGPU::OpName::src1_modifiers,
8169  AMDGPU::OpName::src2_modifiers };
8170 
8171  unsigned OpSel = Inst.getOperand(OpSelIdx).getImm();
8172 
8173  for (int J = 0; J < 3; ++J) {
8174  int OpIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, Ops[J]);
8175  if (OpIdx == -1)
8176  break;
8177 
8178  int ModIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, ModOps[J]);
8179  uint32_t ModVal = Inst.getOperand(ModIdx).getImm();
8180 
8181  if ((OpSel & (1 << J)) != 0)
8182  ModVal |= SISrcMods::OP_SEL_0;
8183  if (ModOps[J] == AMDGPU::OpName::src0_modifiers &&
8184  (OpSel & (1 << 3)) != 0)
8185  ModVal |= SISrcMods::DST_OP_SEL;
8186 
8187  Inst.getOperand(ModIdx).setImm(ModVal);
8188  }
8189 }
8190 
8191 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtVOP3(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands,
8192  OptionalImmIndexMap &OptionalIdx) {
8193  unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
8194 
8195  unsigned I = 1;
8196  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
8197  for (unsigned J = 0; J < Desc.getNumDefs(); ++J) {
8198  ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I++]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
8199  }
8200 
8201  for (unsigned E = Operands.size(); I != E; ++I) {
8202  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I]);
8203  if (isRegOrImmWithInputMods(Desc, Inst.getNumOperands())) {
8204  Op.addRegOrImmWithFPInputModsOperands(Inst, 2);
8205  } else if (Op.isImmModifier()) {
8206  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = I;
8207  } else if (Op.isRegOrImm()) {
8208  Op.addRegOrImmOperands(Inst, 1);
8209  } else {
8210  llvm_unreachable("unhandled operand type");
8211  }
8212  }
8213 
8214  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::clamp))
8215  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx,
8216  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyClampSI);
8217 
8218  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::omod))
8219  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx,
8220  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOModSI);
8221 
8222  // Special case v_mac_{f16, f32} and v_fmac_{f16, f32} (gfx906/gfx10+):
8223  // it has src2 register operand that is tied to dst operand
8224  // we don't allow modifiers for this operand in assembler so src2_modifiers
8225  // should be 0.
8226  if (isMAC(Opc)) {
8227  auto it = Inst.begin();
8228  std::advance(it, AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src2_modifiers));
8229  it = Inst.insert(it, MCOperand::createImm(0)); // no modifiers for src2
8230  ++it;
8231  // Copy the operand to ensure it's not invalidated when Inst grows.
8232  Inst.insert(it, MCOperand(Inst.getOperand(0))); // src2 = dst
8233  }
8234 }
8235 
8236 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtVOP3(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands) {
8237  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
8238  cvtVOP3(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx);
8239 }
8240 
8241 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtVOP3P(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands,
8242  OptionalImmIndexMap &OptIdx) {
8243  const int Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
8244  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Opc);
8245 
8246  const bool IsPacked = (Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::IsPacked) != 0;
8247 
8248  if (Opc == AMDGPU::V_CVT_SR_BF8_F32_vi ||
8249  Opc == AMDGPU::V_CVT_SR_FP8_F32_vi) {
8250  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0)); // Placeholder for src2_mods
8251  Inst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
8252  }
8253 
8254  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::vdst_in)) {
8255  assert(!IsPacked);
8256  Inst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(0));
8257  }
8258 
8259  // FIXME: This is messy. Parse the modifiers as if it was a normal VOP3
8260  // instruction, and then figure out where to actually put the modifiers
8261 
8262  int OpSelIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::op_sel);
8263  if (OpSelIdx != -1) {
8264  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOpSel);
8265  }
8266 
8267  int OpSelHiIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::op_sel_hi);
8268  if (OpSelHiIdx != -1) {
8269  int DefaultVal = IsPacked ? -1 : 0;
8270  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOpSelHi,
8271  DefaultVal);
8272  }
8273 
8274  int NegLoIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::neg_lo);
8275  if (NegLoIdx != -1) {
8276  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyNegLo);
8277  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyNegHi);
8278  }
8279 
8280  const int Ops[] = { AMDGPU::OpName::src0,
8281  AMDGPU::OpName::src1,
8282  AMDGPU::OpName::src2 };
8283  const int ModOps[] = { AMDGPU::OpName::src0_modifiers,
8284  AMDGPU::OpName::src1_modifiers,
8285  AMDGPU::OpName::src2_modifiers };
8286 
8287  unsigned OpSel = 0;
8288  unsigned OpSelHi = 0;
8289  unsigned NegLo = 0;
8290  unsigned NegHi = 0;
8291 
8292  if (OpSelIdx != -1)
8293  OpSel = Inst.getOperand(OpSelIdx).getImm();
8294 
8295  if (OpSelHiIdx != -1)
8296  OpSelHi = Inst.getOperand(OpSelHiIdx).getImm();
8297 
8298  if (NegLoIdx != -1) {
8299  int NegHiIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::neg_hi);
8300  NegLo = Inst.getOperand(NegLoIdx).getImm();
8301  NegHi = Inst.getOperand(NegHiIdx).getImm();
8302  }
8303 
8304  for (int J = 0; J < 3; ++J) {
8305  int OpIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, Ops[J]);
8306  if (OpIdx == -1)
8307  break;
8308 
8309  int ModIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, ModOps[J]);
8310 
8311  if (ModIdx == -1)
8312  continue;
8313 
8314  uint32_t ModVal = 0;
8315 
8316  if ((OpSel & (1 << J)) != 0)
8317  ModVal |= SISrcMods::OP_SEL_0;
8318 
8319  if ((OpSelHi & (1 << J)) != 0)
8320  ModVal |= SISrcMods::OP_SEL_1;
8321 
8322  if ((NegLo & (1 << J)) != 0)
8323  ModVal |= SISrcMods::NEG;
8324 
8325  if ((NegHi & (1 << J)) != 0)
8326  ModVal |= SISrcMods::NEG_HI;
8327 
8328  Inst.getOperand(ModIdx).setImm(Inst.getOperand(ModIdx).getImm() | ModVal);
8329  }
8330 }
8331 
8332 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtVOP3P(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands) {
8333  OptionalImmIndexMap OptIdx;
8334  cvtVOP3(Inst, Operands, OptIdx);
8335  cvtVOP3P(Inst, Operands, OptIdx);
8336 }

8338 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8339 // VOPD
8340 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8341 
8342 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseVOPD(OperandVector &Operands) {
8343  if (!hasVOPD(getSTI()))
8344  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
8345 
8346  if (isToken(AsmToken::Colon) && peekToken(false).is(AsmToken::Colon)) {
8347  SMLoc S = getLoc();
8348  lex();
8349  lex();
8350  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateToken(this, "::", S));
8351  SMLoc OpYLoc = getLoc();
8352  StringRef OpYName;
8353  if (isToken(AsmToken::Identifier) && !Parser.parseIdentifier(OpYName)) {
8354  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateToken(this, OpYName, OpYLoc));
8355  return MatchOperand_Success;
8356  }
8357  Error(OpYLoc, "expected a VOPDY instruction after ::");
8358  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
8359  }
8360  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
8361 }
8362 
8363 // Create VOPD MCInst operands using parsed assembler operands.
8364 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtVOPD(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands) {
8365  auto addOp = [&](uint16_t ParsedOprIdx) { // NOLINT:function pointer
8366  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[ParsedOprIdx]);
8367  if (Op.isReg()) {
8368  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
8369  return;
8370  }
8371  if (Op.isImm()) {
8372  Op.addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
8373  return;
8374  }
8375  llvm_unreachable("Unhandled operand type in cvtVOPD");
8376  };
8377 
8378  const auto &InstInfo = getVOPDInstInfo(Inst.getOpcode(), &MII);
8379 
8380  // MCInst operands are ordered as follows:
8381  // dstX, dstY, src0X [, other OpX operands], src0Y [, other OpY operands]
8382 
8383  for (auto CompIdx : VOPD::COMPONENTS) {
8384  addOp(InstInfo[CompIdx].getIndexOfDstInParsedOperands());
8385  }
8386 
8387  for (auto CompIdx : VOPD::COMPONENTS) {
8388  const auto &CInfo = InstInfo[CompIdx];
8389  auto CompSrcOperandsNum = InstInfo[CompIdx].getCompParsedSrcOperandsNum();
8390  for (unsigned CompSrcIdx = 0; CompSrcIdx < CompSrcOperandsNum; ++CompSrcIdx)
8391  addOp(CInfo.getIndexOfSrcInParsedOperands(CompSrcIdx));
8392  if (CInfo.hasSrc2Acc())
8393  addOp(CInfo.getIndexOfDstInParsedOperands());
8394  }
8395 }

8397 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8398 // dpp
8399 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8400 
8401 bool AMDGPUOperand::isDPP8() const {
8402  return isImmTy(ImmTyDPP8);
8403 }
8404 
8405 bool AMDGPUOperand::isDPPCtrl() const {
8406  using namespace AMDGPU::DPP;
8407 
8408  bool result = isImm() && getImmTy() == ImmTyDppCtrl && isUInt<9>(getImm());
8409  if (result) {
8410  int64_t Imm = getImm();
8411  return (Imm >= DppCtrl::QUAD_PERM_FIRST && Imm <= DppCtrl::QUAD_PERM_LAST) ||
8412  (Imm >= DppCtrl::ROW_SHL_FIRST && Imm <= DppCtrl::ROW_SHL_LAST) ||
8413  (Imm >= DppCtrl::ROW_SHR_FIRST && Imm <= DppCtrl::ROW_SHR_LAST) ||
8414  (Imm >= DppCtrl::ROW_ROR_FIRST && Imm <= DppCtrl::ROW_ROR_LAST) ||
8415  (Imm == DppCtrl::WAVE_SHL1) ||
8416  (Imm == DppCtrl::WAVE_ROL1) ||
8417  (Imm == DppCtrl::WAVE_SHR1) ||
8418  (Imm == DppCtrl::WAVE_ROR1) ||
8419  (Imm == DppCtrl::ROW_MIRROR) ||
8420  (Imm == DppCtrl::ROW_HALF_MIRROR) ||
8421  (Imm == DppCtrl::BCAST15) ||
8422  (Imm == DppCtrl::BCAST31) ||
8423  (Imm >= DppCtrl::ROW_SHARE_FIRST && Imm <= DppCtrl::ROW_SHARE_LAST) ||
8424  (Imm >= DppCtrl::ROW_XMASK_FIRST && Imm <= DppCtrl::ROW_XMASK_LAST);
8425  }
8426  return false;
8427 }

8453 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8454 // dim
8455 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8456 
8457 bool AMDGPUAsmParser::parseDimId(unsigned &Encoding) {
8458  // We want to allow "dim:1D" etc.,
8459  // but the initial 1 is tokenized as an integer.
8460  std::string Token;
8461  if (isToken(AsmToken::Integer)) {
8462  SMLoc Loc = getToken().getEndLoc();
8463  Token = std::string(getTokenStr());
8464  lex();
8465  if (getLoc() != Loc)
8466  return false;
8467  }
8468 
8469  StringRef Suffix;
8470  if (!parseId(Suffix))
8471  return false;
8472  Token += Suffix;
8473 
8474  StringRef DimId = Token;
8475  if (DimId.startswith("SQ_RSRC_IMG_"))
8476  DimId = DimId.drop_front(12);
8477 
8478  const AMDGPU::MIMGDimInfo *DimInfo = AMDGPU::getMIMGDimInfoByAsmSuffix(DimId);
8479  if (!DimInfo)
8480  return false;
8481 
8482  Encoding = DimInfo->Encoding;
8483  return true;
8484 }
8485 
8486 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseDim(OperandVector &Operands) {
8487  if (!isGFX10Plus())
8488  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
8489 
8490  SMLoc S = getLoc();
8491 
8492  if (!trySkipId("dim", AsmToken::Colon))
8493  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
8494 
8495  unsigned Encoding;
8496  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
8497  if (!parseDimId(Encoding)) {
8498  Error(Loc, "invalid dim value");
8499  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
8500  }
8501 
8502  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Encoding, S,
8503  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDim));
8504  return MatchOperand_Success;
8505 }
8506 
8507 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8508 // dpp
8509 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
8510 
8511 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseDPP8(OperandVector &Operands) {
8512  SMLoc S = getLoc();
8513 
8514  if (!isGFX10Plus() || !trySkipId("dpp8", AsmToken::Colon))
8515  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
8516 
8517  // dpp8:[%d,%d,%d,%d,%d,%d,%d,%d]
8518 
8519  int64_t Sels[8];
8520 
8521  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::LBrac, "expected an opening square bracket"))
8522  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
8523 
8524  for (size_t i = 0; i < 8; ++i) {
8525  if (i > 0 && !skipToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected a comma"))
8526  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
8527 
8528  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
8529  if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(Sels[i]))
8530  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
8531  if (0 > Sels[i] || 7 < Sels[i]) {
8532  Error(Loc, "expected a 3-bit value");
8533  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
8534  }
8535  }
8536 
8537  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::RBrac, "expected a closing square bracket"))
8538  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
8539 
8540  unsigned DPP8 = 0;
8541  for (size_t i = 0; i < 8; ++i)
8542  DPP8 |= (Sels[i] << (i * 3));
8543 
8544  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, DPP8, S, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDPP8));
8545  return MatchOperand_Success;
8546 }
8547 
8548 bool
8549 AMDGPUAsmParser::isSupportedDPPCtrl(StringRef Ctrl,
8550  const OperandVector &Operands) {
8551  if (Ctrl == "row_newbcast")
8552  return isGFX90A();
8553 
8554  if (Ctrl == "row_share" ||
8555  Ctrl == "row_xmask")
8556  return isGFX10Plus();
8557 
8558  if (Ctrl == "wave_shl" ||
8559  Ctrl == "wave_shr" ||
8560  Ctrl == "wave_rol" ||
8561  Ctrl == "wave_ror" ||
8562  Ctrl == "row_bcast")
8563  return isVI() || isGFX9();
8564 
8565  return Ctrl == "row_mirror" ||
8566  Ctrl == "row_half_mirror" ||
8567  Ctrl == "quad_perm" ||
8568  Ctrl == "row_shl" ||
8569  Ctrl == "row_shr" ||
8570  Ctrl == "row_ror";
8571 }
8572 
8573 int64_t
8574 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseDPPCtrlPerm() {
8575  // quad_perm:[%d,%d,%d,%d]
8576 
8577  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::LBrac, "expected an opening square bracket"))
8578  return -1;
8579 
8580  int64_t Val = 0;
8581  for (int i = 0; i < 4; ++i) {
8582  if (i > 0 && !skipToken(AsmToken::Comma, "expected a comma"))
8583  return -1;
8584 
8585  int64_t Temp;
8586  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
8587  if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(Temp))
8588  return -1;
8589  if (Temp < 0 || Temp > 3) {
8590  Error(Loc, "expected a 2-bit value");
8591  return -1;
8592  }
8593 
8594  Val += (Temp << i * 2);
8595  }
8596 
8597  if (!skipToken(AsmToken::RBrac, "expected a closing square bracket"))
8598  return -1;
8599 
8600  return Val;
8601 }
8602 
8603 int64_t
8604 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseDPPCtrlSel(StringRef Ctrl) {
8605  using namespace AMDGPU::DPP;
8606 
8607  // sel:%d
8608 
8609  int64_t Val;
8610  SMLoc Loc = getLoc();
8611 
8612  if (getParser().parseAbsoluteExpression(Val))
8613  return -1;
8614 
8615  struct DppCtrlCheck {
8616  int64_t Ctrl;
8617  int Lo;
8618  int Hi;
8619  };
8620 
8621  DppCtrlCheck Check = StringSwitch<DppCtrlCheck>(Ctrl)
8622  .Case("wave_shl", {DppCtrl::WAVE_SHL1, 1, 1})
8623  .Case("wave_rol", {DppCtrl::WAVE_ROL1, 1, 1})
8624  .Case("wave_shr", {DppCtrl::WAVE_SHR1, 1, 1})
8625  .Case("wave_ror", {DppCtrl::WAVE_ROR1, 1, 1})
8626  .Case("row_shl", {DppCtrl::ROW_SHL0, 1, 15})
8627  .Case("row_shr", {DppCtrl::ROW_SHR0, 1, 15})
8628  .Case("row_ror", {DppCtrl::ROW_ROR0, 1, 15})
8629  .Case("row_share", {DppCtrl::ROW_SHARE_FIRST, 0, 15})
8630  .Case("row_xmask", {DppCtrl::ROW_XMASK_FIRST, 0, 15})
8631  .Case("row_newbcast", {DppCtrl::ROW_NEWBCAST_FIRST, 0, 15})
8632  .Default({-1, 0, 0});
8633 
8634  bool Valid;
8635  if (Check.Ctrl == -1) {
8636  Valid = (Ctrl == "row_bcast" && (Val == 15 || Val == 31));
8637  Val = (Val == 15)? DppCtrl::BCAST15 : DppCtrl::BCAST31;
8638  } else {
8639  Valid = Check.Lo <= Val && Val <= Check.Hi;
8640  Val = (Check.Lo == Check.Hi) ? Check.Ctrl : (Check.Ctrl | Val);
8641  }
8642 
8643  if (!Valid) {
8644  Error(Loc, Twine("invalid ", Ctrl) + Twine(" value"));
8645  return -1;
8646  }
8647 
8648  return Val;
8649 }
8650 
8651 OperandMatchResultTy
8652 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseDPPCtrl(OperandVector &Operands) {
8653  using namespace AMDGPU::DPP;
8654 
8655  if (!isToken(AsmToken::Identifier) ||
8656  !isSupportedDPPCtrl(getTokenStr(), Operands))
8657  return MatchOperand_NoMatch;
8658 
8659  SMLoc S = getLoc();
8660  int64_t Val = -1;
8661  StringRef Ctrl;
8662 
8663  parseId(Ctrl);
8664 
8665  if (Ctrl == "row_mirror") {
8666  Val = DppCtrl::ROW_MIRROR;
8667  } else if (Ctrl == "row_half_mirror") {
8668  Val = DppCtrl::ROW_HALF_MIRROR;
8669  } else {
8670  if (skipToken(AsmToken::Colon, "expected a colon")) {
8671  if (Ctrl == "quad_perm") {
8672  Val = parseDPPCtrlPerm();
8673  } else {
8674  Val = parseDPPCtrlSel(Ctrl);
8675  }
8676  }
8677  }
8678 
8679  if (Val == -1)
8680  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
8681 
8682  Operands.push_back(
8683  AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Val, S, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppCtrl));
8684  return MatchOperand_Success;
8685 }
