8706 
8707 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtVOP3DPP(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands,
8708  bool IsDPP8) {
8709  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
8710  unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
8711  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
8712 
8713  // MAC instructions are special because they have 'old'
8714  // operand which is not tied to dst (but assumed to be).
8715  // They also have dummy unused src2_modifiers.
8716  int OldIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::old);
8717  int Src2ModIdx =
8718  AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src2_modifiers);
8719  bool IsMAC = OldIdx != -1 && Src2ModIdx != -1 &&
8720  Desc.getOperandConstraint(OldIdx, MCOI::TIED_TO) == -1;
8721 
8722  unsigned I = 1;
8723  for (unsigned J = 0; J < Desc.getNumDefs(); ++J) {
8724  ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I++]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
8725  }
8726 
8727  int Fi = 0;
8728  for (unsigned E = Operands.size(); I != E; ++I) {
8729 
8730  if (IsMAC) {
8731  int NumOperands = Inst.getNumOperands();
8732  if (OldIdx == NumOperands) {
8733  // Handle old operand
8734  constexpr int DST_IDX = 0;
8735  Inst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(DST_IDX));
8736  } else if (Src2ModIdx == NumOperands) {
8737  // Add unused dummy src2_modifiers
8738  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(0));
8739  }
8740  }
8741 
8742  auto TiedTo = Desc.getOperandConstraint(Inst.getNumOperands(),
8743  MCOI::TIED_TO);
8744  if (TiedTo != -1) {
8745  assert((unsigned)TiedTo < Inst.getNumOperands());
8746  // handle tied old or src2 for MAC instructions
8747  Inst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(TiedTo));
8748  }
8749  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I]);
8750  // Add the register arguments
8751  if (IsDPP8 && Op.isFI()) {
8752  Fi = Op.getImm();
8753  } else if (isRegOrImmWithInputMods(Desc, Inst.getNumOperands())) {
8754  Op.addRegOrImmWithFPInputModsOperands(Inst, 2);
8755  } else if (Op.isReg()) {
8756  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
8757  } else if (Op.isImm() &&
8758  Desc.operands()[Inst.getNumOperands()].RegClass != -1) {
8759  assert(!Op.IsImmKindLiteral() && "Cannot use literal with DPP");
8760  Op.addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
8761  } else if (Op.isImm()) {
8762  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = I;
8763  } else {
8764  llvm_unreachable("unhandled operand type");
8765  }
8766  }
8767  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::clamp))
8768  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyClampSI);
8769 
8770  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::omod))
8771  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOModSI);
8772 
8773  if (Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::VOP3P)
8774  cvtVOP3P(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx);
8775  else if (Desc.TSFlags & SIInstrFlags::VOP3)
8776  cvtVOP3OpSel(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx);
8777  else if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::op_sel)) {
8778  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOpSel);
8779  }
8780 
8781  if (IsDPP8) {
8782  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDPP8);
8783  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::DPP;
8784  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Fi? DPP8_FI_1 : DPP8_FI_0));
8785  } else {
8786  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppCtrl, 0xe4);
8787  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppRowMask, 0xf);
8788  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppBankMask, 0xf);
8789  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppBoundCtrl);
8790 
8791  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Inst.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::fi))
8792  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx,
8793  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppFi);
8794  }
8795 }
8796 
8797 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtDPP(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands, bool IsDPP8) {
8798  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
8799 
8800  unsigned I = 1;
8801  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
8802  for (unsigned J = 0; J < Desc.getNumDefs(); ++J) {
8803  ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I++]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
8804  }
8805 
8806  int Fi = 0;
8807  for (unsigned E = Operands.size(); I != E; ++I) {
8808  auto TiedTo = Desc.getOperandConstraint(Inst.getNumOperands(),
8809  MCOI::TIED_TO);
8810  if (TiedTo != -1) {
8811  assert((unsigned)TiedTo < Inst.getNumOperands());
8812  // handle tied old or src2 for MAC instructions
8813  Inst.addOperand(Inst.getOperand(TiedTo));
8814  }
8815  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I]);
8816  // Add the register arguments
8817  if (Op.isReg() && validateVccOperand(Op.getReg())) {
8818  // VOP2b (v_add_u32, v_sub_u32 ...) dpp use "vcc" token.
8819  // Skip it.
8820  continue;
8821  }
8822 
8823  if (IsDPP8) {
8824  if (Op.isDPP8()) {
8825  Op.addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
8826  } else if (isRegOrImmWithInputMods(Desc, Inst.getNumOperands())) {
8827  Op.addRegWithFPInputModsOperands(Inst, 2);
8828  } else if (Op.isFI()) {
8829  Fi = Op.getImm();
8830  } else if (Op.isReg()) {
8831  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
8832  } else {
8833  llvm_unreachable("Invalid operand type");
8834  }
8835  } else {
8836  if (isRegOrImmWithInputMods(Desc, Inst.getNumOperands())) {
8837  Op.addRegWithFPInputModsOperands(Inst, 2);
8838  } else if (Op.isReg()) {
8839  Op.addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
8840  } else if (Op.isDPPCtrl()) {
8841  Op.addImmOperands(Inst, 1);
8842  } else if (Op.isImm()) {
8843  // Handle optional arguments
8844  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = I;
8845  } else {
8846  llvm_unreachable("Invalid operand type");
8847  }
8848  }
8849  }
8850 
8851  if (IsDPP8) {
8852  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::DPP;
8853  Inst.addOperand(MCOperand::createImm(Fi? DPP8_FI_1 : DPP8_FI_0));
8854  } else {
8855  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppRowMask, 0xf);
8856  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppBankMask, 0xf);
8857  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppBoundCtrl);
8858  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Inst.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::fi)) {
8859  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppFi);
8860  }
8861  }
8862 }

8865 // sdwa

8868 OperandMatchResultTy
8869 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSDWASel(OperandVector &Operands, StringRef Prefix,
8870  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTy Type) {
8871  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::SDWA;
8872 
8873  SMLoc S = getLoc();
8874  StringRef Value;
8875  OperandMatchResultTy res;
8876 
8877  SMLoc StringLoc;
8878  res = parseStringWithPrefix(Prefix, Value, StringLoc);
8879  if (res != MatchOperand_Success) {
8880  return res;
8881  }
8882 
8883  int64_t Int;
8884  Int = StringSwitch<int64_t>(Value)
8885  .Case("BYTE_0", SdwaSel::BYTE_0)
8886  .Case("BYTE_1", SdwaSel::BYTE_1)
8887  .Case("BYTE_2", SdwaSel::BYTE_2)
8888  .Case("BYTE_3", SdwaSel::BYTE_3)
8889  .Case("WORD_0", SdwaSel::WORD_0)
8890  .Case("WORD_1", SdwaSel::WORD_1)
8891  .Case("DWORD", SdwaSel::DWORD)
8892  .Default(0xffffffff);
8893 
8894  if (Int == 0xffffffff) {
8895  Error(StringLoc, "invalid " + Twine(Prefix) + " value");
8896  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
8897  }
8898 
8899  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Int, S, Type));
8900  return MatchOperand_Success;
8901 }
8902 
8903 OperandMatchResultTy
8904 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseSDWADstUnused(OperandVector &Operands) {
8905  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::SDWA;
8906 
8907  SMLoc S = getLoc();
8908  StringRef Value;
8909  OperandMatchResultTy res;
8910 
8911  SMLoc StringLoc;
8912  res = parseStringWithPrefix("dst_unused", Value, StringLoc);
8913  if (res != MatchOperand_Success) {
8914  return res;
8915  }
8916 
8917  int64_t Int;
8918  Int = StringSwitch<int64_t>(Value)
8919  .Case("UNUSED_PAD", DstUnused::UNUSED_PAD)
8920  .Case("UNUSED_SEXT", DstUnused::UNUSED_SEXT)
8921  .Case("UNUSED_PRESERVE", DstUnused::UNUSED_PRESERVE)
8922  .Default(0xffffffff);
8923 
8924  if (Int == 0xffffffff) {
8925  Error(StringLoc, "invalid dst_unused value");
8926  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
8927  }
8928 
8929  Operands.push_back(AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Int, S, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaDstUnused));
8930  return MatchOperand_Success;
8931 }

8952 
8953 void AMDGPUAsmParser::cvtSDWA(MCInst &Inst, const OperandVector &Operands,
8954  uint64_t BasicInstType,
8955  bool SkipDstVcc,
8956  bool SkipSrcVcc) {
8957  using namespace llvm::AMDGPU::SDWA;
8958 
8959  OptionalImmIndexMap OptionalIdx;
8960  bool SkipVcc = SkipDstVcc || SkipSrcVcc;
8961  bool SkippedVcc = false;
8962 
8963  unsigned I = 1;
8964  const MCInstrDesc &Desc = MII.get(Inst.getOpcode());
8965  for (unsigned J = 0; J < Desc.getNumDefs(); ++J) {
8966  ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I++]).addRegOperands(Inst, 1);
8967  }
8968 
8969  for (unsigned E = Operands.size(); I != E; ++I) {
8970  AMDGPUOperand &Op = ((AMDGPUOperand &)*Operands[I]);
8971  if (SkipVcc && !SkippedVcc && Op.isReg() &&
8972  (Op.getReg() == AMDGPU::VCC || Op.getReg() == AMDGPU::VCC_LO)) {
8973  // VOP2b (v_add_u32, v_sub_u32 ...) sdwa use "vcc" token as dst.
8974  // Skip it if it's 2nd (e.g. v_add_i32_sdwa v1, vcc, v2, v3)
8975  // or 4th (v_addc_u32_sdwa v1, vcc, v2, v3, vcc) operand.
8976  // Skip VCC only if we didn't skip it on previous iteration.
8977  // Note that src0 and src1 occupy 2 slots each because of modifiers.
8978  if (BasicInstType == SIInstrFlags::VOP2 &&
8979  ((SkipDstVcc && Inst.getNumOperands() == 1) ||
8980  (SkipSrcVcc && Inst.getNumOperands() == 5))) {
8981  SkippedVcc = true;
8982  continue;
8983  } else if (BasicInstType == SIInstrFlags::VOPC &&
8984  Inst.getNumOperands() == 0) {
8985  SkippedVcc = true;
8986  continue;
8987  }
8988  }
8989  if (isRegOrImmWithInputMods(Desc, Inst.getNumOperands())) {
8990  Op.addRegOrImmWithInputModsOperands(Inst, 2);
8991  } else if (Op.isImm()) {
8992  // Handle optional arguments
8993  OptionalIdx[Op.getImmTy()] = I;
8994  } else {
8995  llvm_unreachable("Invalid operand type");
8996  }
8997  SkippedVcc = false;
8998  }
8999 
9000  const unsigned Opc = Inst.getOpcode();
9001  if (Opc != AMDGPU::V_NOP_sdwa_gfx10 && Opc != AMDGPU::V_NOP_sdwa_gfx9 &&
9002  Opc != AMDGPU::V_NOP_sdwa_vi) {
9003  // v_nop_sdwa_sdwa_vi/gfx9 has no optional sdwa arguments
9004  switch (BasicInstType) {
9005  case SIInstrFlags::VOP1:
9006  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::clamp))
9007  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx,
9008  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyClampSI, 0);
9009 
9010  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::omod))
9011  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx,
9012  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOModSI, 0);
9013 
9014  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::dst_sel))
9015  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx,
9016  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaDstSel, SdwaSel::DWORD);
9017 
9018  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::dst_unused))
9019  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx,
9020  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaDstUnused,
9021  DstUnused::UNUSED_PRESERVE);
9022 
9023  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaSrc0Sel, SdwaSel::DWORD);
9024  break;
9025 
9026  case SIInstrFlags::VOP2:
9027  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyClampSI, 0);
9028 
9029  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Inst.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::omod))
9030  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOModSI, 0);
9031 
9032  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaDstSel, SdwaSel::DWORD);
9033  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaDstUnused, DstUnused::UNUSED_PRESERVE);
9034  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaSrc0Sel, SdwaSel::DWORD);
9035  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaSrc1Sel, SdwaSel::DWORD);
9036  break;
9037 
9038  case SIInstrFlags::VOPC:
9039  if (AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Inst.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::clamp))
9040  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyClampSI, 0);
9041  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaSrc0Sel, SdwaSel::DWORD);
9042  addOptionalImmOperand(Inst, Operands, OptionalIdx, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaSrc1Sel, SdwaSel::DWORD);
9043  break;
9044 
9045  default:
9046  llvm_unreachable("Invalid instruction type. Only VOP1, VOP2 and VOPC allowed");
9047  }
9048  }
9049 
9050  // special case v_mac_{f16, f32}:
9051  // it has src2 register operand that is tied to dst operand
9052  if (Inst.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_MAC_F32_sdwa_vi ||
9053  Inst.getOpcode() == AMDGPU::V_MAC_F16_sdwa_vi) {
9054  auto it = Inst.begin();
9055  std::advance(
9056  it, AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Inst.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::src2));
9057  Inst.insert(it, Inst.getOperand(0)); // src2 = dst
9058  }
9059 }

9089 OperandMatchResultTy
9090 AMDGPUAsmParser::parseCustomOperand(OperandVector &Operands, unsigned MCK) {
9091  switch (MCK) {
9092  case MCK_addr64:
9093  return parseTokenOp("addr64", Operands);
9094  case MCK_done:
9095  return parseTokenOp("done", Operands);
9096  case MCK_idxen:
9097  return parseTokenOp("idxen", Operands);
9098  case MCK_lds:
9099  return parseTokenOp("lds", Operands);
9100  case MCK_offen:
9101  return parseTokenOp("offen", Operands);
9102  case MCK_off:
9103  return parseTokenOp("off", Operands);
9104  case MCK_row_95_en:
9105  return parseTokenOp("row_en", Operands);
9106  case MCK_ImmABID:
9107  return parseIntWithPrefix("abid", Operands, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyABID);
9108  case MCK_ImmBankMask:
9109  return parseIntWithPrefix("bank_mask", Operands,
9110  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppBankMask);
9111  case MCK_ImmBLGP: {
9112  OperandMatchResultTy Res =
9113  parseIntWithPrefix("blgp", Operands, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyBLGP);
9114  if (Res == MatchOperand_NoMatch) {
9115  Res = parseOperandArrayWithPrefix("neg", Operands,
9116  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyBLGP);
9117  }
9118  return Res;
9119  }
9120  case MCK_ImmCBSZ:
9121  return parseIntWithPrefix("cbsz", Operands, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyCBSZ);
9122  case MCK_ImmCPol:
9123  return parseCPol(Operands);
9124  case MCK_ImmFI:
9125  return parseIntWithPrefix("fi", Operands, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppFi);
9126  case MCK_gds:
9127  return parseNamedBit("gds", Operands, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyGDS);
9128  case MCK_ImmNegHi:
9129  return parseOperandArrayWithPrefix("neg_hi", Operands,
9130  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyNegHi);
9131  case MCK_ImmNegLo:
9132  return parseOperandArrayWithPrefix("neg_lo", Operands,
9133  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyNegLo);
9134  case MCK_ImmSMEMOffset:
9135  return parseIntWithPrefix("offset", Operands, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOffset);
9136  case MCK_ImmOModSI:
9137  return parseOModOperand(Operands);
9138  case MCK_ImmOpSel:
9139  return parseOperandArrayWithPrefix("op_sel", Operands,
9140  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOpSel);
9141  case MCK_ImmOpSelHi:
9142  return parseOperandArrayWithPrefix("op_sel_hi", Operands,
9143  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyOpSelHi);
9144  case MCK_ImmRowMask:
9145  return parseIntWithPrefix("row_mask", Operands,
9146  AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyDppRowMask);
9147  case MCK_ImmSDWADstSel:
9148  return parseSDWASel(Operands, "dst_sel", AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaDstSel);
9149  case MCK_ImmSDWADstUnused:
9150  return parseSDWADstUnused(Operands);
9151  case MCK_ImmSDWASrc0Sel:
9152  return parseSDWASel(Operands, "src0_sel", AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaSrc0Sel);
9153  case MCK_ImmSDWASrc1Sel:
9154  return parseSDWASel(Operands, "src1_sel", AMDGPUOperand::ImmTySdwaSrc1Sel);
9155  case MCK_tfe:
9156  return parseNamedBit("tfe", Operands, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyTFE);
9157  }
9158  return tryCustomParseOperand(Operands, MCK);
9159 }
9160 
9161 // This function should be defined after auto-generated include so that we have
9162 // MatchClassKind enum defined
9163 unsigned AMDGPUAsmParser::validateTargetOperandClass(MCParsedAsmOperand &Op,
9164  unsigned Kind) {
9165  // Tokens like "glc" would be parsed as immediate operands in ParseOperand().
9166  // But MatchInstructionImpl() expects to meet token and fails to validate
9167  // operand. This method checks if we are given immediate operand but expect to
9168  // get corresponding token.
9169  AMDGPUOperand &Operand = (AMDGPUOperand&)Op;
9170  switch (Kind) {
9171  case MCK_addr64:
9172  return Operand.isAddr64() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9173  case MCK_gds:
9174  return Operand.isGDS() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9175  case MCK_lds:
9176  return Operand.isLDS() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9177  case MCK_idxen:
9178  return Operand.isIdxen() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9179  case MCK_offen:
9180  return Operand.isOffen() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9181  case MCK_tfe:
9182  return Operand.isTFE() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9183  case MCK_SSrcB32:
9184  // When operands have expression values, they will return true for isToken,
9185  // because it is not possible to distinguish between a token and an
9186  // expression at parse time. MatchInstructionImpl() will always try to
9187  // match an operand as a token, when isToken returns true, and when the
9188  // name of the expression is not a valid token, the match will fail,
9189  // so we need to handle it here.
9190  return Operand.isSSrcB32() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9191  case MCK_SSrcF32:
9192  return Operand.isSSrcF32() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9193  case MCK_SoppBrTarget:
9194  return Operand.isSoppBrTarget() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9195  case MCK_VReg32OrOff:
9196  return Operand.isVReg32OrOff() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9197  case MCK_InterpSlot:
9198  return Operand.isInterpSlot() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9199  case MCK_Attr:
9200  return Operand.isInterpAttr() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9201  case MCK_AttrChan:
9202  return Operand.isAttrChan() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9203  case MCK_ImmSMEMOffset:
9204  return Operand.isSMEMOffset() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9205  case MCK_SReg_64:
9206  case MCK_SReg_64_XEXEC:
9207  // Null is defined as a 32-bit register but
9208  // it should also be enabled with 64-bit operands.
9209  // The following code enables it for SReg_64 operands
9210  // used as source and destination. Remaining source
9211  // operands are handled in isInlinableImm.
9212  return Operand.isNull() ? Match_Success : Match_InvalidOperand;
9213  default:
9214  return Match_InvalidOperand;
9215  }
9216 }

9222 OperandMatchResultTy AMDGPUAsmParser::parseEndpgmOp(OperandVector &Operands) {
9223  SMLoc S = getLoc();
9224  int64_t Imm = 0;
9225 
9226  if (!parseExpr(Imm)) {
9227  // The operand is optional, if not present default to 0
9228  Imm = 0;
9229  }
9230 
9231  if (!isUInt<16>(Imm)) {
9232  Error(S, "expected a 16-bit value");
9233  return MatchOperand_ParseFail;
9234  }
9235 
9236  Operands.push_back(
9237  AMDGPUOperand::CreateImm(this, Imm, S, AMDGPUOperand::ImmTyEndpgm));
9238  return MatchOperand_Success;
9239 }

llvm::MCOperand::isImm
bool isImm() const
Definition: MCInst.h:62
type
AMD64 Optimization Manual has some nice information about optimizing integer multiplication by a constant How much of it applies to Intel s X86 implementation There are definite trade offs to xmm0 cvttss2siq rdx jb L3 subss xmm0 rax cvttss2siq rdx xorq rdx rax ret instead of xmm1 cvttss2siq rcx movaps xmm2 subss xmm2 cvttss2siq rax rdx xorq rax ucomiss xmm0 cmovb rax ret Seems like the jb branch has high likelihood of being taken It would have saved a few instructions It s not possible to reference and DH registers in an instruction requiring REX prefix divb and mulb both produce results in AH If isel emits a CopyFromReg which gets turned into a movb and that can be allocated a r8b r15b To get around isel emits a CopyFromReg from AX and then right shift it down by and truncate it It s not pretty but it works We need some register allocation magic to make the hack go which would often require a callee saved register Callees usually need to keep this value live for most of their body so it doesn t add a significant burden on them We currently implement this in however this is suboptimal because it means that it would be quite awkward to implement the optimization for callers A better implementation would be to relax the LLVM IR rules for sret arguments to allow a function with an sret argument to have a non void return type
